title: spinach squares
directions: Place spinach in wire strainer; rinse under hot water to thaw. Press to remove water.
Melt butter in skillet; add onion and mushrooms; cook until onion is soft.
Beat eggs with a fork.
Add breadcrumbs, soup, 2 tbsp cheese, pepper, basil, oregano, spinach and onion mixture; mix well.
Pour into well greased 9 inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered at 325° for 35 minutes or until firm when touched lightly.
Cool slightly; cover and chill.
Cut into 1 inch squares for appetizers and serve cold or reheat at 325° for 10-12 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Melt margarine. Add brown sugar and bring to a boil. Add nuts. Alternate syrup and biscuits in angel food cake pan or Bundt pan. Bake in 350° oven until deep golden brown.

title: ida's sherry stew
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place beef in black skillet with onion slices on top.
Add soup and sherry.
Cover.
Bake 2 hours. Delicious, tender beef with thick brown gravy.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: tang pie
directions: Combine condensed milk, sour cream and Tang.
Mix well and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: honey apricot bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Mix egg, milk, honey and margarine.
Add flour mixture; stir just until moistened.
Stir in cereal and apricots.
Pour into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan which has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Makes 16 (1/2) slices.

title: barbequed chicken
directions: Put ingredients in a heavy ziplock bag.
Shake to coat well. Refrigerate for 24 hours if possible, turning the bag several times.
When coals are ready, place chicken on the grill, skin side up, basting with the marinade.
Cook until well browned before turning.
(If baking in oven, bake at 400°, skin side down first.)
About 20 minutes before chicken is done, begin using your favorite bottled barbeque sauce or the homemade version below.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix together eggs, mayonnaise, old bay seasoning, pepper, mustard, worcestershire sauce.
Add crabmeat and blend carefully. Add bread crumbs. Shape into 6 cakes.

title: grapefruit aspic
directions: Combine 2 cups of the grapefruit with sugar and salt.
Soften gelatin in the remaining 1/2 cup grapefruit juice, then place over hot water to melt.
Stir melted gelatin thoroughly into grapefruit mixture and turn into a mold rinsed in cold water.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.
Unmold onto plate and surround with crisp lettuce cups.
Serve with lime honey or celery seed or any other sweet dressing.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix by hand.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Will freeze good.
Warm before serving.

title: pineapple-carrot cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Cream the eggs and sugar.
Add dry ingredients alternately with oil.
Mix until blended.
Add pineapple, nuts, raisins, grated carrots and vanilla.
Turn into tube pan.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350° until cake tester comes out dry.
Place on rack for 5 minutes. Remove from pan and let cool.
If desired, frost with cream cheese frosting, but is delicious plain.
Tastes better baked a day ahead!

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as usual.
Drain.
Combine cooked macaroni, tuna, sour cream, cheese and soup.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with dry bread crumbs or chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: bourbon balls(party food)
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls.
Roll balls in granulated sugar and store in an airtight container for at least 1 week before serving.
These will mellow with age and keep for at least 1 month.

title: confection bites(christmas)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Work in flour and pecans.
Add milk, drop by drop.
Add vanilla.
Break and form into small rolls (2 inches long and 1/2 inch thick).
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
When crisp, roll in powdered sugar.

title: cooked pimento cheese
directions: To make sauce, blend together beaten egg yolks, sugar, mustard, butter, vinegar and milk.
Heat, stirring until smooth and hot; stir hot mixture into shredded cheese, stirring until well mixed.
Drain pimentos and dice (reserve liquid).
Add diced pimentos to cheese mixture and pimento liquid if needed to make mixture of spreading consistency.
(Err on the side of too much liquid; will "stiffen up" in the refrigerator.)
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cheese mixture.
Store, covered tightly in the refrigerator.
Will keep "forever."

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Put aside a little more than a cup of crumbs.
Add the remaining 3 ingredients.
Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Pour remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until cake springs back from touch.

title: steamed fish
directions: Rinse cleaned fish.
Leave skin on and trim fish to fit on rack
placed
in
12-inch Dutch oven.
Sprinkle generously with salt, pepper, ginger and onion.
Add sufficient water to Dutch oven
to
steam
fish for 1 hour.
Remove fish and drain off liquid
in Dutch oven.
In a separate pot, heat peanut oil to very hot.
Replace
fish into Dutch oven.
Pour heated oil over fish to sear.
Serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Use 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding milk as needed to create a creamy frosting.

title: shrimp or crawfish dip
directions: Cream together cheese, milk, lemon juice and seasonings. Stir.

title: cheese cake squares
directions: Preheat oven to temperature on crescent roll can.
Spray a 9x 13 inch baking pan lightly with cooking spray.
Mix together cream cheese, 3/4 c. sugar, vanilla, and egg yolk until smooth.
Line the bottom of the baking pan with 1 can of the crescent rolls pressing together the seams.
Spread the cream cheese mixture on top of the rolls.
Top with the remaining can of crescent rolls.
Baste the top with the egg white.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 c. sugar. Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
Allow to cool completely and cut into squares.

title: best ever pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each. Add vanilla flavoring. Add milk, flour and eggs alternatively; mix well. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°. Cool 10 minutes before turning out. Do not open oven door for the first hour.

title: meat balls
directions: Add bread crumbs, eggs, Parmesan cheese to hamburger.
Add oregano, black pepper and garlic salt to taste. Form into balls and brown in skillet.
Add to sauce. Combine brown sugar, sour cream, butter, steak sauce and ketchup.
Cover and cook slowly until done.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and walnuts; set aside.
Mix dough in order (will be sticky).
Chill in fridge.
Dust with flour and cut in 4 equal parts.
Roll each in a circle as with pie, dusting surface with flour.
Sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.
Cut into 16 wedges and roll from wide part of wedge up.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let cool 3 minutes and remove from sheet.

title: cheese drops
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients together until smooth.
Add cereal. Roll into small balls on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop 1/2 cup of popcorn.
Melt margarine, brown sugar, syrup, molasses and salt; bring to boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda; stir.
Caramel will get very foamy. Pour caramel over popcorn; stir.
Bake on cookie sheet at 250° for 20 minutes.
Cool and enjoy!

title: pecan goodies
directions: Beat egg whites; stir in sugar.
Stir in pecans until fully covered.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Cook at 225° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken wings
directions: Marinate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: rice consomme
directions: Brown rice and onion in butter.
Put in casserole, adding consomme and Italian seasoning. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Drain peas, corn and pimento and mix together.
Add celery, bell pepper and onion.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine eggs, milk and oil and beat until well blended.
Add onion, jalapeno peppers, corn and cheese and blend.
Add cornbread mix, sugar and baking powder, blending well.
Pour into well-greased hot pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: neiman marcus cake
directions: Mix the box of cake mix with the eggs and butter. Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

Then layer chocolate chips, coconut, and pecans over cake layer. Mix the confectioners sugar, beaten eggs and the softened cream cheese in a bowl and pour over the pecan layer. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: christmas holly cookies
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter in the top of a double boiler; stir to blend.
Stir in vanilla flavoring and enough food coloring to make a dark green.
Remove from heat and gently stir in corn flakes.
Working quickly, drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Decorate each cookie with 3 red hots for holly berries.
Chill.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: corn custard
directions: Mix and
turn
into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° until firm in center, about 45 minutes.

title: easy mexican dish
directions: Line dish with corn chips.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add other ingredients.
Pour over chips, top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: gourmet chicken breast
directions: Skin and bone chicken breast.
Arrange 1 slice of smoked beef under each.
Wrap slice of bacon around each breast.
Arrange in glass baking dish.
Combine soup, sour cream and flour.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Sprinkle mushrooms on top.
Cover with plastic wrap or dish cover.
(If using plastic, pierce hole for steam to escape.)
Microwave on Roast 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: company broccoli and zucchini saute
directions: Cut broccoli into 2 x 1-inch pieces.
Cut zucchini into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Cut each green onion into 2-inch pieces (if root ends are too thick, cut each lengthwise in half).
In 8-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, in 1/3 cup hot salad oil, cook green onions, stirring frequently, until tender, about 3 minutes.
With rubber spatula stir in broccoli and 1 1/4 teaspoon salt until broccoli is coated with oil.
Add water; cover Dutch oven and cook broccoli 5 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally, until tender-crisp. Remove vegetables and liquid to bowl.
In same Dutch oven over medium heat, in 1/4 cup hot salad oil, cook zucchini, basil and 1 teaspoon salt, stirring occasionally, until tender-crisp.
Return broccoli mixture to Dutch oven; add soy sauce; mix well.

title: barbecue pork and beef sandwiches(makes about 12 large sandwiches.)
directions: To cook in slow cooker:
Combine all ingredients.
Cover and cook on high for 8 hours.
With wire whisk, stir mixture until meat is shredded.

title: brenda's spanish beans
directions: Fill a pot of water with all ingredients in it.
Let beans boil until water is thick like stew.

title: easy corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish. Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in a skillet and cook until done, then put soda and salt in and stir well and pour on greased or buttered platter or countertop.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: easy peach crumble
directions: Place peaches in a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Can use canned apples or cherry pie filling.

title: oysters mosca
directions: Spray 13 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch baking glass pan with Pam.
Layer pan with oysters, cheeses, garlic and onions.
Sprinkle olive oil over entire dish.
Bake covered with aluminum foil for 15 minutes.

title: ham glaze dijon
directions: Bring to a boil and then simmer.
Spoon 1/2 cup onto ham during the last 30 minutes of baking.
Heat remaining mixture and serve with sliced ham.
Don't expect any leftovers.
It's guaranteed to go much faster than the snails.

title: brownie cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour in large bowl.
In saucepan, put oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Bring mixture to a rapid boil. Mix with dry ingredients; then add eggs, vanilla, soda and cinnamon.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: gnocchi parisienne
directions: In medium saucepan, combine 1 c. water, 1/2 c. butter and 1 tsp. salt; bring to boiling.
Remove from heat.
With wooden spoon, beat in 1 c. flour.
Over low heat, beat mixture until it leaves side of pan and forms a ball-1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating with electric mixer or wooden spoon after each addition until well blended; continue beating until dough is shiny and satiny.
Stir in 1/4 c. cheese and the mustard until well blended.

title: fruit salad dessert
directions: Mix together egg, fruit cocktail and vanilla.
Stir together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients.
Blend well. pour into greased 8 inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle on top of dough.
Bake at 350 for 50-60 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Enjoy!

title: sky high biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine the flours, baking powder, sugar, salt and cream of tartar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add egg and milk, stirring quickly and briefly.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Roll or pat gently to 1-inch thickness. Cut into 1-inch to 2-inch biscuits.
Place in a greased 10-inch iron skillet or on a 9-inch square pan.
For crusty biscuits, separate on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yield:
about 20 biscuits.

title: special shortbread cookies
directions: Preparation: Mix together with your hands.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: wiener daffle
directions: Combine gravy mix and water in sauce pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat slowly, stirring frequently until sauce thickens.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine (do not brown).
Mix with 3/4 of dressing and spread on bottom of large baking pan (10 x 16-inch).
Spread layer of chicken, cut in large pieces.
Cover with layer of broccoli and mushrooms.
Thin condensed soup with equal parts of water and pour over.
Spread remaining dressing over top.
Cover and bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour (until bubbly), then uncover and bake 15 minutes more until crisp. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: meatballs
directions: Saute onion until tender in 1 tablespoon butter.
In large bowl mix hamburger, bread crumbs and egg.
Add dash of salt, paprika and 1/2 of garlic clove.
Mix all together and form balls; brown lightly in skillet.
In a large saucepan, place whole tomatoes, paste and sauce.
Add chopped pepper, mushrooms, remaining garlic and celery.
When meatballs are browned, add them to this sauce. Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: nut crisps
directions: Cream shortening and 1/3 cup sifted sugar.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add remaining sifted sugar and continue beating.
Combine the two mixtures and blend until smooth.
Sift dry ingredients together and add chopped nuts.
Chill.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: orange charlotte
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over orange juice to soften.
Heat sugar and water together until sugar dissolves and bubbles break over the surface.
Remove from heat and stir in the softened gelatin until dissolved.
Add grated orange rind and cool in refrigerator until thick.
Whip the cream and beat the egg whites until very stiff. Beat cooled gelatin mixture until frothy.
Fold egg whites, whipped cream and gelatin mixture together with care.
Line oiled 8-inch mold with the ladyfingers and place the orange sections in the bottom of mold; pour in mixture.
When set, carefully invert on plate to serve.

title: chocolate cheesecake muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat until creamy. Stir in 1/4 cup chocolate chips; set aside. Melt 1/2 cup chocolate chips in a double boiler; stir until smooth. Remove from heat.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla, water and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Add flour baking soda, salt and chocolate chips.
Place spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: two-tone chocolate fudge
directions: In saucepan, over low heat, melt semi-sweet chocolate chips with 2/3 cup sweetened condensed milk, 1 tablespoon cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Remove from heat; stir in 1/2 cup walnuts. Spread into aluminum foil lined 9-inch square pan.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: Combine slaw dressing, mayo and dip mix.
Add salt, pepper and celery seed to taste.
Add onion, green pepper, cucumber pickles and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Toss in pasta gently.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: cherry pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine half the sugar, 3/4 cup of the cherry juice and all of the cornstarch; mix well and cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly. Remove from heat and add balance of ingredients. Stir gently to combine and spoon into bottom crust. Moisten edge of crust and add top crust. Cut slits to allow steam to escape. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until crust is brown and filling begins to bubble. If necessary, cover the edge of crust during the last 15 to 20 minutes to prevent overbrowning.

title: meat loaf
directions: Shape into a loaf, with hands a mixture of meat, milk, oats, onions, salt and pepper.
Dot the top with shortening.
Bake in a greased pan in a moderate 350° oven, for 1 hour or until brown. Makes 4 servings.
Pet milk makes the meat loaf extra juicy.
If you like, put tomato paste or catsup on top before cooking. Delicious!

title: hershey's light chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray two 8 or 9-inch round pans with cooking spray.
In a bowl, stir flour, cocoa and baking soda.
In saucepan, melt corn oil or any vegetable oil.
Stir in sugar. Remove from heat. Add milk, vinegar and vanilla to mixture in saucepan.
Stir. Add dry ingredients.
Whisk until well blended. Pour evenly into pans. Bake 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool, fill and frost. Refrigerate. Double for two 9-inch round pans.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: jello fruit `n' juice squares
directions: Stir 1 1/2 cups boiling water into 1 package Jell-O strawberry flavor sugar-free low-calorie gelatin in a large bowl at least 2 minutes until dissolved. Mix 1 cup cold orange juice and ice to make 1 1/4 cups. Stir into gelatin; refrigerate 30 minutes or until thickened.

title: sesame marinade
directions: Brown sesame seed in oil.
Mix ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Marinate overnight.

title: lasagna(microwave)
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Mix sauce, water, meat and salt.
Cook 5 minutes on High, covered.
In a 3-quart casserole, put 1/3 of sauce, layer 1/2 noodles, Ricotta cheese and 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella.
Do this 2 times with sauce on the last layer. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cook on High for 30 to 35 minutes, covered with Saran Wrap, leaving space for steam to escape.
Test noodles for doneness.
Let stand 15 minutes, covered.

title: eclair torte
directions: Melt chocolate and butter and cool.
Mix together with vanilla, powdered sugar and milk.

title: chicken wellington
directions: Thaw pastry for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle chicken with seasoning. In a medium skillet, brown chicken in 3 tablespoons butter; set aside.
Add remaining butter to skillet.
Add onion and mushrooms. Saute until tender and liquid evaporated.
Stir in parsley.

title: apple dapel cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together; mix well.
Pour into a floured long, deep baking pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken mushroom bundles(for the outdoor grill)
directions: Cut potatoes and carrots into 1/2-inch slices.
Thinly slice mushrooms.
Place 6 pieces of heavy foil on counter.
Put piece of chicken and divide vegetables in each bundle.
Add salt and pepper,
2 tablespoons soup and tarragon. Wrap and seal foil. Grill 1 hour.
Serve with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pat's mexicali cornbread
directions: Mix batter thoroughly and add sausage, cheese, pepperoni, onion and hot peppers.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
When cooled, cut into desired sized pieces.
Can be wrapped in Saran Wrap or plastic wrap and then in aluminum foil for freezing.
Great later when warmed in microwave oven.

title: marbled chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, with electric beaters, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Combine flour, soda and salt; gradually beat into butter mixture until well blended.
Scoop about one-third of the dough into a separate bowl.
Mix in cocoa until thoroughly blended; stir in semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Stir vanilla chips into remaining white dough.
Return chocolate dough to mixing bowl; with a wooden spoon, stir the two doughs together just until marbled.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Wash cranberries and chop coarsely.
Add sugar and let drain overnight in refrigerator.
Combine cranberries, apples, grapes, oranges and nuts.
Toss lightly.

title: hominy au gratin
directions: Drain hominy, place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add onion and pimento.
Blend flour and butter, add milk and grated cheese and salt.
Cook over low heat until thick and pour over hominy.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: nadia's oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush 1/2 bag of Oreo cookies in bottom of pan.
Combine softened cream cheese, 1/2 container of Cool Whip and vanilla pudding (after mixing according to package) in large bowl.
Pour over crushed Oreo cookies, then top with remaining Cool Whip.
Now top with other half bag of Oreo cookies.
Refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: waffle and pancake mix
directions: Separate eggs and save whites.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in the batter.
Can be set in the refrigerator overnight and cooked the next day.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick of oleo together. Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan and let stand while mixing rest.

title: tuna-noodle bake
directions: In a casserole dish combine noodles, tuna, sour cream, milk, mushrooms, salt and pepper.

title: diabetic-fizzy punch
directions: In a large mixing bowl or pitcher (3-quart), blend spices with pineapple juice.
Add remaining fruit juices and liquid sweetener. Chill.
Just before serving, add carbonated water.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Pour into well-greased and sugared pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans. Its freezes well.

title: beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: In small bowl, combine the beef broth, soy sauce, cornstarch and mustard and stir until the cornstarch is dissolved.
Set aside.
Cut the broccoli into bite-size pieces.
In a nonstick large skillet, warm the oil over medium-high heat until hot but not smoking.
Add the broccoli, cauliflower, onion and garlic and stir-fry until the vegetables are crisp-tender and the onion begins to brown, 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir cornstarch mixture again and pour into the skillet.
Stir in beef and pepper and stir-fry until the sauce thickens and the beef is heated through, 2 to 3 minutes.
If necessary, reduce heat to keep the sauce from evaporating.

title: frozen yogurt pie
directions: Combine fruit, yogurt and light Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: southern walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, melted butter and syrup.
Add nuts.
Pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven about 50 minutes or until knife inserted about center comes out clean.
This recipe may be used with pecans.

title: best yet pineapple cake
directions: Blend together margarine, cream cheese, sour cream and sugar. Add undrained pineapple and coconut; blend.
Sprinkle with dry pudding mix as it comes in the package.
Fold in whipped topping. Use to fill and frost layers of yellow cake.
Use yellow cake mix and follow directions on package to make layers for cake.
Let frosting set in refrigerator for a while and it will spread better.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Cook chicken.
(I season with Cajun seasoning and garlic flakes.)
Cut cheese into squares and place in microwavable bowl. Add Ro-Tel.
You may need to add a little milk to make it smooth as it melts.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes and stir.
Microwave 2 to 3 more minutes.
Cook pasta.
Drain chicken, pasta and vegetables. Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Season as you desire. Pour into casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake in microwave until hot and bubbly.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream oleo into sugar.
Add beaten eggs, flour, milk and extract.
Beat well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until top is lightly browned.

title: mini-sausage quiches
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese in medium bowl until creamy. Blend in flour; refrigerate 1 hour.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine already cooked beans and peas with the raw vegetables. Toss thoroughly.

title: jade punch
directions: Dissolve soft drink powder and sugar in water.
Add lemonade and pineapple juice; chill.
Before serving, add ginger ale and food coloring.
Serve over ice cubes with thin slices of lemon or lime for garnish.

title: bean pot
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Put in mixing bowl.
Brown onion and bacon; drain off fat.
Combine onion, bacon and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole.
Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Can substitute navy or pinto for other beans.

title: apple pie spaghetti
directions: Brown beef in large skillet; drain.
Fry onions until tender. Add all ingredients.
Simmer to desired temperature.

title: fudge marble cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well and divide batter into halves. Add chocolate syrup and chips to 1/2.
Layer in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan, starting and ending with the chocolate batter.
Swirl with knife to marbleize.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco burgers
directions: Brown beef until crumbly; drain. Add tomatoes and taco seasoning. Stir well. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Spoon beef mixture over bottom halves of buns.
Sprinkle with lettuce and cheese. Cover with tops of buns.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Crumble sausage and beef in a 2-quart casserole.
Stir in onion and green pepper.
Microwave at High for 6 to 7 minutes, or until meat is brown, stirring every 2 minutes.
Drain well.
Add pizza sauce and garlic salt, mixing well.
Microwave at High for 2 to 3 minutes, or until hot, stirring once.
Spoon meat mixture on bottom of hamburger buns; sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave at High for 1 minute and 15 seconds to 1 minutes and 45 seconds, or until cheese begins to melt.
Cover with bun tops.
Microwave at High for 30 to 45 seconds, or until tops are warm.
Serve immediately. Yields 8 servings.

title: quick and easy pie
directions: Add instant pudding mix to undrained pineapple.
Mix and add sour cream.
Mix thoroughly and pour into crust.
Add Cool Whip on top and chill. Will serve about 10 people.

title: charleston wassail
directions: Place all ingredients into large saucepan and bring to boil. Reduce heat, partially cover pot and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Serves 15.

title: butterscotchies
directions: Melt butterscotch in a double boiler.
Mix in peanuts and noodles. Drop by
teaspoon onto wax paper and let set.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: crunchy salad
directions: Remove flavor packets from soup mix; set aside. Crumble noodles. Bake noodles in a shallow pan

at 350° for 10 minutes or until roasted, stirring after 5 minutes. Remove from oven and cool. Cook sliced almonds and 3 tablespoons sugar in a small nonstick skillet over medium-low heat, stirring constantly, 5 to 6 minutes or until sugar is dissolved and almonds are evenly coated. Remove almond mixture from heat and set aside.
Whisk together reserved flavor packet, remaining 2 tablespoons of sugar, oil and the next 5 items for the dressing.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Put about 3/4's of it in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cook onion and zucchini in the margarine for 5 minutes.
Add soup and sour cream to the mixture.
Pour over the stuffing in the pan.
Put the rest of stuffing on top of squash mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until mixture is hot.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper and brown in a small amount of Wesson oil.
(Don't cook all the way.) Place pork chops in a large pan (broiler pan is good).
Pour rice over the pork chops.
Add mashed tomatoes (juice and all).
Place onion and pepper rings on top.
Heat leftover grease and pour out.
Pour a glass of water into pan.
Then pour this over the top of your casserole.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Mix stuffing, 1 cup boiling water and 1 tablespoon margarine. Spoon stuffing across center of a 3-quart shallow baking dish. Place chicken on each side of stuffing. Sprinkle chicken with paprika. Mix soup, milk and parsley. Pour over chicken. Bake covered at 400° for 15 minutes. Bake uncovered 15 more minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. (For moister stuffing, increase water by 1 to 2 tablespoons.) Serves six.

title: puffed rice brittle
directions: Boil together sugar, water and vinegar.
Add butter and salt. Boil until small amount will become brittle in cold water.
Add puffed rice that has been crisped in oven.
Pour out onto buttered sheets.
Let cool and cut into squares or bars.

title: alice's dessert
directions: Combine
Eagle	Brand milk and marshmallows.
Let stand until soft.
Stir.
Add 1 can crushed pineapple, well drained and
1 can
cherry pie filling.
Blend all together.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.	Freeze overnight.

title: buckeyes
directions: Blend first three ingredients well or until moist.
Form together small balls.
Place balls on a cookie sheet and chill about one hour.

title: tossed salad with walnuts(serving size: 6)
directions: Cook and stir walnuts in oil in 8-inch skillet until toasted (about 4 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Remove walnuts with slotted spoon; drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt.
Stir vinegar and sugar into oil in skillet; toss with salad greens and onion until well coated.
Sprinkle with walnuts.

title: company best pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with boiling water; let stand until the next day.
Drain and repeat for next three days.
On the fifth day, drain and slice in 1/4-inch slices.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, peanut butter (I use crunchy), sugar and vanilla on medium speed until well blended. Gently stir in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust. Freeze at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: grandmother's six course dinner
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a baking pan.
Cook in oven at 350° until the meat and vegetables are done.
Serve with hot rolls.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: *Brown lightly in a 300° oven on a cookie sheet for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: lo-fat "cream cheese" pie
directions: Mix crumbs and melted margarine; press into 8-inch pie plate. Bake in 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Whip jello with water until foamy with beaters.
Add pineapple, whipped topping and yogurt.
Pour into large graham cracker shell and refrigerate until set.
You may sprinkle some graham cracker crumbs on top and decorate with a few strawberries, if desired.

title: brittany coq au vin
directions: In skillet, brown cut up chicken in butter or margarine, adding more butter or margarine if needed.
Add sliced onion and garlic to chicken.
Add cognac and heat until just warm.
Sprinkle flour over the chicken; mix and stir.	Pour water and wine over chicken to cover.
Add thyme, bay leaf and prunes.
Bring to boil and simmer 45 minutes.
During the last 15 minutes, add mushrooms and salt and pepper.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve with French bread.
Serves 4.

title: connie's casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion and pepper.
Mix in rest of ingredients, except cheese and onion rings.
Put half of mixture in a casserole.
Top with half of cheese.
Put remaining mixture on cheese and top with remaining cheese and onion rings.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: farmer's cheap fruit cake
directions: Simmer apples and molasses 2 hours. (Much less if applesauce is used.) Let cool. Add spices and soda to flour. Sift 3 times and beat. Add milk and watch for the amount you use--depends on the apple mixture. Lastly, add raisins and beat. Bake at 350°F. in loaf pan or tube pan. It's done when tested with toothpick.

title: vegetable pork chop casserole
directions: Layer beans, onions and potatoes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Repeat layers.
Pour tomatoes over top. Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Place pork chops over tomatoes. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
After 30 minutes of cooking, baste meat and vegetables well.
Yields 6 servings.

title: frozen citrus pie
directions: Beat concentrated juice in large bowl about 30 seconds.
Blend in ice cream.
Fold in Cool Whip until smooth.
Freeze, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into crust and freeze until firm (4 hours or overnight).
Let stand at room temperature 10 minutes before serving.

title: big mama's tea cakes
directions: Beat margarine in a large mixer bowl for 30 seconds.
Add 1 1/4 cups sugar and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt in a mixing bowl. Add to beaten mixture alternately with buttermilk.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Rub flour into roast.
Place in bottom of crockpot and add remaining ingredients except buns.
Cook on low heat for approximately 14-16 hours.
Serve over buns.

title: apple walnut cake(delicious and moist)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat oil and sugar together in electric mixer, while assembling remaining ingredients.
Add the eggs and beat until mixture is creamy.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place each ingredient in order in an 8 x 14 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish or pan.
Seal tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.
Check after 3 hours.
This will serve 6 with additional helpings.

title: peanut butter honey
directions: Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: arizona sugar cookies
directions: Mix well shortening, brown sugar, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Sift and add flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Roll in small balls.
Roll in sugar.
Do not flatten.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend flour and sugar.
Combine with well beaten eggs.
Add syrup and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 40 or 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Blend flour and butter for crust.
Add chopped walnuts to flour and butter mixture.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Combine softened cream cheese with sugar.
Add 1/2 container of Cool Whip to mixture.
Spread gently over crust.
Chill 20 minutes.
Mix instant pudding and milk. Beat until slightly thickened.
Spread over cheese mixture. Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Chill overnight.

title: pineapple whipped cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in glass bowl.
Pour into baked pie crusts. Chill for 3 to 4 hours until firm.

title: german dill pickles
directions: Boil water, vinegar, salt and alum for 5 minutes.
Pack dill and 1 clove garlic into bottom of sterilized jar.
Pack pickles and add more dill.
Pour hot liquid over pickles and seal.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes thoroughly.
Cut a thin slice from top of each tomato; carefully scoop out pulp, reserving pulp for other uses. Invert shells on paper towels to drain.
Combine next 4 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat at low speed until smooth. Spoon about 2 teaspoons turkey mixture into tomato shells. Sprinkle with cheese and garnish with parsley sprig.
Chill. Yields about 24 appetizer servings.

title: golden potato surprise
directions: Cover potatoes with boiling salted water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes, until fork-tender.
Drain.
Set aside.

title: biscotti(italian cookie)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Add the five extracts. Beat well.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add nuts.
Add to butter mixture.

title: economical party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Add juice, ginger ale and sherbet.
(Coordinate flavor of Kool-Aid with sherbet; lemon lime Kool-Aid with lime sherbet, etc.)

title: heavenly divinity
directions: In a medium saucepan, boil sugar, syrup and 1/2 cup water until a little forms soft ball when dropped in cold water.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In bottom of casserole, put 1/2 of Escort cracker crumbs.
Dot with with approximately 1/2 stick butter.
Place cooked chipped up chicken in casserole.
Next, heat in separate boiler both cans of soups, sour cream and water chestnuts.
Pour over chicken.
Then top with other 1/2 box of cracker crumbs.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes.
May need a little bit of chicken broth if seems too dry.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well all ingredients.

title: beans, pork and tomato stew
directions: Wash and pick over beans, discarding bad ones.
Place in a saucepan with the water and bring to the boil.
Turn off heat; cover and allow to soak for 1 hour.
Bring to a simmer and cook on low heat, covered, until beans are tender but not soft (about 45 minutes to 1 1/2 hours).
Add salt after 1/2 hour of cooking. Drain and set aside.

title: toasted coconut pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs, sugar, butter, lemon juice and vanilla extract.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until filling is set.
Cool; garnish with whipped cream and pecans.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat and mix soup and cream cheese.
Dissolve gelatine in cold water, then beat until clear.
Add to soup and cheese mixture.
Add all other ingredients and pour into mold.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: kahlua
directions: Simmer water, sugar and coffee with lid on for 2 hours (do not boil).
Let cool to room temperature.
Add vodka and vanilla.
Let set for 3 to 6 weeks.

title: oven sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In each roll, place 3 ounces chipped ham and 1 slice each of cheese, tomato and onion.
Wrap each sandwich in aluminum foil.
Bake in oven for about 15 minutes. Serves 12.
Can be prepared ahead and refrigerated.
When company arrives, just heat and serve.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and water in a small saucepan.
Cook until thick and clear (about 1 minute); stir while cooking.
Beat egg whites until frothy; add salt and continue beating while slowly pouring cooled mixture over them.
Add flavoring and continue to beat 5 minutes.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: jalapeno cocktail squares
directions: Sprinkle peppers into greased 9-inch square pan.
Cover eggs and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into 1-inch squares.

title: shake the salt habit(recipe for life)
directions: In shaker, mix equal amounts of ingredients.
Use as you would regular salt and in cooking.

title: broccoli-cheese cornbread
directions: Grease pan.
Mix all ingredients.
May cook in glass Pyrex dish or other bread pan.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in medium saucepan.
Add boiling water and instant mashed potatoes; blend well.
Slowly add evaporated milk, stirring constantly to blend well.
Add salt, celery salt and pepper.
Heat mixture just until it begins to boil.
Serve hot, garnished with parsley.
(You may sprinkle grated cheese on top, if desired.)

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine beef, rice, salt and pepper in large bowl until well mixed.
Form into small balls (1 1/2-inch) and place in large baking dish.
Brown onion and bell pepper in shortening.
Add tomato juice, salt and pepper and pour over meatballs.
Cover dish with lid or foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add 3 cups flour and liquids.
Blend thoroughly.
Add 1 cup flour to nuts and fruit.
Coat well and add to batter.
Line a large tube pan with paper and grease well.
Pack cake batter into pan.
Place in water bath canner and steam for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from canner and put in 320° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pump-n-dip
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
Prior to serving, hollow out the pumpernickel, leaving shell intact.
Spoon the dip into the center of the loaf.
Cut the bread into bite-size pieces and use for dipping.
Also great with raw vegetables.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Fry together onion and hamburg.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add this to the hamburg and onion.
Let simmer.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Cream
margarine; add sugar gradually.	Add vanilla and almond extract.
Add
eggs,
one at a time and mix well (don't over mix).
Sift
flour	3 times.
Add alternately with milk. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: melon butter
directions: In a small saucepan, simmer fruit until softened or microwave fruit in a small microwave-safe dish on High for 3 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Place all ingredients in a blender or food processor and process until smooth.
Makes about 2/3 cups.

title: rumaki
directions: Roll up 1 liver and 1 water chestnut in bacon strip; hold together with toothpick.
Bake in oven at 425° for 5 to 10 minutes or until bacon is done (turn once).
Can broil also, being careful not to burn.
Serve hot.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Cut peppers, onions and chicken into thin strips. Saute in nonstick pan until chicken is done. Drain any excess water. Spread tortilla with sour cream. Place chicken and vegetables on top and roll up. Place rolled enchilada in glass baking pan. Top with salsa and cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts. Serve immediately. Serves 1.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water; warm milk and melt margarine in it.
Add sugar, salt and 1 cup of flour when the liquids are lukewarm.
Beat well.
Add egg and yeast and beat well.
Add remaining flour or enough to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and satiny or about 10 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut in half lengthwise.
Boil in salted water until tender.
Drain well.
Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add lemon juice and brown sugar and stir until thick.
Add carrots. Stir until well glazed and heated through.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream the sugar and oil.
Add egg and beat.
Add molasses and beat.
Add spices and salt to flour and sift into mixture.
Beat good, then add hot water to which baking soda has been added. Beat.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
No need to frost.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well. Store in an airtight container.

title: mexican pups
directions: Place one frank in each corn tortilla and roll around the frank.
Place seam side down in a baking dish, 12 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch.
Combine chili and tomato juice and pour over franks. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes more.

title: creamy peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cheese and peanut butter until well combined.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon 1/2 mixture into pie shell.
Top with 1/2 fudge topping.
Repeat, ending with fudge. Top with sprinkled on crushed nuts (peanuts).
Cover and freeze at least 6 hours.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: chicken pasta
directions: Cut chicken breasts into small pieces; cook in skillet in Lipton soup mix until tender.
In a 4-quart saucepan, combine soup and milk.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Cover; cook over low heat for 10 minutes, or until vegetables are done, stirring occasionally.
Cook spaghetti.
Put spaghetti on plate; add the mixture on top.

title: olive butter
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor or blender and process until smooth.
Great mixed with cream cheese to stuff celery.

title: perfect potato salad
directions: Sprinkle potatoes with sugar and vinegar while still warm. Add onion, pickle, seasonings and mayonnaise.
Toss to blend. Carefully fold in egg slices.
Chill.

title: boo bites(child's recipe)
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows together.
Add syrup and peanut butter.
Take off heat and stir in 1/3 cup chocolate chips until melted, then add Rice Krispies cereal.
Roll into balls and bite.

title: coffee cake
directions: Put brown sugar and some nuts in bottom of Bundt pan.
Melt butter.
Roll rolls in butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Put in pan on top of brown sugar.
Make layers (nuts can be put in layers also). Cover with cloth and let sit overnight.
Pour any remaining butter over rolls in morning before you bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: punch recipe
directions: Mix in milk jugs overnight.
Add ginger ale to defrost.

title: venison mincemeat
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over low heat about 1 hour. Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: chicken pastry
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove from liquid.
Set aside to cool.
Mix water and flour together into firm dough.
Roll out thin and cut into squares.
(Keep flour sprinkled onto rolling pin and pastry dough to prevent sticking.) Make sure liquid is boiling hard and drop pastry squares in it.
Cook until done; it doesn't take long.
Remove chicken from bone and put back into pot with pastry.
Note:
If in a hurry, use pastry found in your grocery freezer section.
(I like Atkinson's the best.)

title: bath salts
directions: To make these good smelling bath salts, first measure 1/2 cup of Epsom salt into each jar with a lid.
Add 15 drops of food color to each jar, one color per jar and put on the lids.
Shake the jars until the Epsom salts are dyed evenly.
If you want your colors to be darker, add more food color and shake again.
Take off the lids and let the salts dry overnight.
Now, make sure your pretty jar is all clean and dry.
Then pour the dyed bath salts into the jar, alternating colors (you may want to get colors that go together well).
Add a couple of drops of perfume to the bath salts, put on the lid and tie the jar with your pretty ribbon. Now you have a really nice present to bless someone with.

title: fresh fruit dressing
directions: Mix well.
Fruit can be added to the dressing or served separately and dipped into the side dish of dressing!

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into small sections.
When cooled, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix diced pimentos, potatoes and diced cheese.
Toss together and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter in milk.

title: old fashion butter pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cold water.
Add boiling water and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and add slices of butter. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in moderate oven for about 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix and combine first three ingredients.
Add Pudding (dry). Pour into graham cracker crust or regular baked crust.
Cover with Dream Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in blender or processor; set aside.
In medium bowl, cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
In large bowl, mix milk and instant pudding.
When pudding is set, fold in Cool Whip.
Blend the cream cheese mixture into pudding mixture.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Pour off any fat.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, garlic and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup; mix well.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through. Serve over noodles.

title: lima bean salad
directions: Boil lima beans until tender.
Rinse in cold water.
Mix in mayonnaise, green onions, celery and 3 diced eggs.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Garnish with parsley and sliced egg and paprika. Better flavor if made the day before.

title: macaroni supreme
directions: Cook macaroni according to chart on package; drain and set aside.
In 2-quart microproof casserole or bowl, combine meat and onion.
Cook, covered, on High (max power) another 3 minutes. Stir and cook on High (max power) another 2 minutes or until onion is transparent.
Drain off fat.
Add undrained tomatoes.
With spoon, break up whole tomatoes into pieces.
Add peas, mushrooms, wine, parsley, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, on 50 (Simmer) for 30 minutes.

title: teriyaki orange fillets(serves 4)
directions: In large skillet, arrange halved fillets in single layer.
In small bowl, mix together orange juice and rind, onion, soy sauce, ginger and sugar.
Pour over fish.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 3 to 5 minutes or until fish is opaque and flakes easily with a fork.
Remove fish to a warmed platter (to keep warm).

title: rich beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Cut the fat into small pieces; cook it in a heavy heated Dutch oven until it is crisp and brown.
Add meat; brown it thoroughly on all sides.
Add remaining ingredients, except the potatoes.
Cover tightly; simmer for 1 1/2 hours or longer.
Add potatoes; simmer gently for about another hour.
You may add carrots.

title: individual pizza pies
directions: Brown ground beef and onions and then add the barbecue sauce and the oregano and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Roll the ready-to-bake biscuits into 3-inch circles.
Grease cookie sheet and place biscuits on it and spread with meat mixture.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and place into oven again until cheese has melted.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Put aside 1 cup of the cake mix; you'll use later.
Mix the rest of the cake mix, 1 egg and 1/2 stick butter.
Pat this mix into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the pumpkin pie mix, the evaporated milk, 1/3 cup white sugar, the brown sugar, the cinnamon and the 3 eggs.
Pour this on top of the crust.
Mix the 1 cup reserved cake mix, 1/3 cup white sugar and the 1/2 stick butter.
Crumble this over the top of the pumpkin stuff.
Bake at 350° for at least 50 to 60 minutes; some ovens take as long as 75 minutes.
Cut into squares.
A wonderful change from pumpkin pie for the holidays.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix all together (except 1/2 of morsels and nuts); pour into 9 x 12-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the morsels and put nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: souper enchiladas
directions: Mix soup with sour cream.
In a saucepan, melt butter and saute onions until transparent.
Add chili powder, chicken and chilis. Blend 2 tablespoons soup mixture into chicken mixture.
In middle of tortillas, place 1/4 cup of chicken; roll.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine and pour into baking dish. Crush 14 oz. package of Ritz Crackers and mix with 1 stick melted butter. Sprinkle on top and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: snicker pie
directions: Take frozen Snickers and put in blender.
Chop 3 minutes on high.
In bowl, pour Cool Whip; add Snickers.
Stir and blend. Pour into graham crust.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: yogurt fruit soup
directions: Puree all ingredients (except mint leaves) in food processor or blender.
Chill thoroughly for at least 3 hours.
Garnish with mint leaves prior to serving.
Note: May use frozen (no sugar) peaches, blueberries or frozen mixed fruit.
Thaw fruit before using.
One or two bananas may be substituted for 1 cup of fruit. Yield:
4 servings.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: hot kitchen salad
directions: Mix ingredients in casserole and top with Special K cereal and almonds browned in butter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix oil, sugars, eggs and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and orange rind and stir until thoroughly blended.
Add apples and nuts and mix well.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch tube pan or two 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans and bake about 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Transfer cake to cooling rack. Serve warm or cold.

title: chili cheese ball
directions: Grate American cheese and mix all together with hands.
Put a lot of chili powder on wax paper.
Roll a ball in that, then wrap in same wax paper.

title: old-fashion sugar cookies
directions: Sift the flour with baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg.
In a large bowl, mix with electric mixer at medium speed the butter, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
Beat in sour cream and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating until well combined.
Form dough into a ball.
Wrap in waxed paper or foil. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake at 375°.
May be cut out in any desired shape.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Use equal amounts of cold, boiled potatoes and diced cucumbers. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add enough mayonnaise to mix well.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix the shortening, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and egg together.
In a separate bowl mix the dry ingredients.
Add the flour mixture slowly to the creamed mixture.
Shape cookie dough into balls and press down with fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 375 for 8-10 min.

title: linda's corn relish
directions: Combine peas, green beans, corn, green peppers, celery, green onions and pimentos in a glass bowl.
Let stand.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in water to cover until soft.
Drain and peel potatoes.
Beat potatoes with an electric mixer until creamy. Add butter, orange juice, eggs and sugar, beating well.
Spoon potato mixture into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish. Cover with topping and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: chicken pizzaiola
directions: In deep skillet or wok, heat oil on medium-high heat. Add garlic, tomatoes and basil. Saute until tomatoes are soft (5 to 7 minutes). Mash with potato masher.
Add chicken and mushrooms. Reduce heat to simmer (medium-low to low).
Allow to simmer until chicken is cooked through, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice or angel hair pasta.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: grandmom mclaughlin's scone(aka irish soda bread)
directions: In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Crumble with margarine (stir together to mix margarine; will make small clumps of flour coated margarine).
Add buttermilk, raisins and caraway seed.
Mix. Mixture will be sticky.
Flour hands or mixing spoon.
Grease and flour lightly a black iron frying pan or thick aluminum pan.
Put in mixture, spread into pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.

title: edelweiss fudge pie
directions: In medium saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate and butter, stirring constantly, just until butter is melted and chocolate is softened.
Remove from heat, cool to room temperature.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Melt oleo; add celery, onion and green pepper.
Cook on low until tender, but not brown.
Add seasonings, pimento, mushrooms, soup and cheese.
Continue to cook and stir until cheese melts and all ingredients are well blended.
Add chicken.
Mix and heat well.

title: almond macaroons
directions: Baking time 20 minutes.

title: noodles thai style
directions: In small bowl, combine ketchup, soy sauce, sugar, red pepper and ginger; set aside.
In large, nonstick skillet, over medium heat, heat 1 teaspoon margarine until bubbly.
Add egg product and gently scramble until done; remove to another small bowl.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 475° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Dredge in granulated sugar.
Place on a plate and allow to dry out before serving.

title: philly beef sandwiches
directions: Cook and stir onions until tender.
Set oven to broil.
Place bottom halves of buns on ungreased cookie sheet; top with onions and beef.
Cut cheese slices in half.
Place 4 halves on each sandwich.
Broil until cheese melts for 2 to 3 minutes.
Top each with remaining bun half.

title: aunt ava rainey's peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, milk and salt.
Cook to soft boil. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until peanut butter is melted.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour on platter covered with waxed paper.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: frog-eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple juice and egg over heat.
Stir until thick.
Add lemon juice.
Cool at room temperature.
Bring water to boil and cook acini de pepe done.
Drain and rinse well.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine with egg mixture.
Mix lightly and refrigerate.
Chill well.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve frozen orange juice into the orange soda and 7-Up. Dollop the orange sherbet on top to keep punch cold.
(It looks pretty, too!)

title: congealed salad
directions: Sprinkle with a little strawberry jello for a light pink color.
Mix together and serve.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Cook 30 minutes and put in sterilized jars.
Seal and cool. Makes 5 pints.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Drop in 6 tea bags for 10 minutes and remove.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat and serve.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° until done.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix cherries, milk and pineapple.
Beat Cool Whip in by hand. Refrigerate 4-5 hours before serving.

title: hawaiian meat balls
directions: Brown meat balls; add water and cook.
Combine cornstarch, salt, brown sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce in saucepan, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour over meat balls. Allow to stand 10 minutes.
Stir in onion and pineapple.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: jello berry cake
directions: Tear into pieces the angel food cake and place in oblong pan. Mix Jell-O and pour over angel food cake pieces and add strawberries.
Let jell and top it with whipped cream.

title: old fashion molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Mix in molasses, then water.
Mix and sift remaining ingredients.
Add to molasses mixture about 1 cup at a time.
Stir until well blended dough. Divide dough into 2 equal parts and roll in foil or waxed paper. Refrigerate for about 3 hours.
Take 1 roll at a time, place on floured board and roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out cookies any way you like.
Place on cookie sheet; bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: sweet nothings
directions: Melt together first 3 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix in Rice Chex gradually and carefully so as not to crush.
To cover with sugar, place small amounts of cereal mix into Ziploc bag; add some sugar.
Close and shake.
Repeat until all is covered.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Grate eggs real fine.
Chop pickles real fine.
Add to mayonnaise and chili sauce.
Mix well.
Let set in refrigerator a while before serving.

title: willie's butter rolls
directions: Roll out dough mixture on board.
(Roll thin.)
Dot with butter (or oleo).
Cut with a knife and cover dough.
Roll dough into a roll and cut into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place flat on baking pan (11 x 13-inch oblong).
Pour 2 cups of sugar over this.
Cover completely with milk.
Add vanilla (1 teaspoon).
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter.
Add powdered sugar gradually.
Cream well until smooth.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Blend; mixture is stiff. Pinch off small pieces of dough (about 3/4 inch).
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° about 12 minutes.
Roll cookies in powdered sugar immediately after removing from oven. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: cherry jello
directions: Mix hot water with Jell-O until dissolved in a large bowl or mold.
Place in refrigerator until it starts to jell, about 50 minutes.
Take out and fold in pie filling until well mixed. Makes a large bowl or mold.
This can be cut in half.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, corn syrup and butter or margarine.
Add pecan halves.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.

title: unbaked chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring to a rolling boil the cocoa, sugar, milk and oleo. Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and quick oatmeal. Drop on waxed paper.

title: orange wassail
directions: Combine sugar, water and spices in a saucepan.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Discard juices; add juices to syrup. Heat and serve.
Yields 4 quarts.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crumble graham crackers (either by hand or blender).
Melt margarine and mix with crackers.
Spread in pie pan. Bake crust in oven at 325° for 15 minutes.
Combine water, sugar, cornstarch and Jell-O in saucepan.
Cook until thickened.
Cool slightly; add strawberries.
Pour into cooled crust.
Let chill in refrigerator. Serve.
Use Cool Whip for topping, if desired.

title: german sour cream twists
directions: Sift flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir into flour mixture with sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well with hands.
Cover with damp cloth and refrigerate 2 hours.
Roll half of dough on sugared board into an oblong 8 x 16-inches.
Fold ends toward center, ends overlapping. Sprinkle with sugar; roll again to same size.
Repeat a third time. Roll about 1/4-inch thick (better if a little thicker).
Cut into strips, 1 x 4-inches.
Twist ends in opposite direction, stretching dough slightly. put in shape of horseshoe on ungreased baking sheet of horseshoe on ungreased baking sheet, pressing ends to keep shape.
Heat oven to 375°.
(It's better to turn to 350° after 5 minutes.)
Bake until delicately brown and remove from sheet immediately.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Put a quart of water in a large saucepan; add 2 tablespoons of chicken base, cubed potato, onion, mushrooms, chicken cutlets, Cajun and garlic seasoning. Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Remove chicken and cut into 1-inch cubes. Return to saucepan and add the frozen vegetables; bring to a boil.

title: refrigerator cole slaw
directions: Mix shredded cabbage, chopped onion, salt and water.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain, then add other ingredients and mix well. Will keep up to a month.

title: chevy pinch-penny rolls
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, salt and hot milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in warm water; add sugar and let stand for 20 minutes.
Combine yeast with milk mixture.
Add beaten eggs and as much flour as can be stirred into the dough.
Brush top with melted margarine and let stand in a large bowl in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, cut dough down with a knife.
Shape into small balls, put in greased muffin pans and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Melt cream cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into 2 graham pie shells and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Return unused portion to refrigerator.

title: smoked turkey muffins
directions: Sift together flours, baking powder, celery seed and paprika. Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, measure cereal and milk.
Stir to combine.
Let stand 5 minutes or until cereal is softened.
Add egg substitute and oil.
Beat well.
Stir in onion and turkey. Add dry ingredients to cereal mixture, stirring only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into 6 greased 3 1/4 x 1 1/4-inch jumbo muffin cups or 12 large muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot with 1/3 cup Low-Fat Cheese Sauce per muffin.

title: chicken continental
directions: Saute chicken, mushrooms and garlic in oil, 2 to 3 minutes or until chicken is brown.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice, and bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes or until rice is fluffy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix all ingredients except muffins. Spread mixture on muffins. Cut each muffin into 8 pieces. Freeze and put in plastic bags. To serve, broil 5-10 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; rinse well in cool water.
Drain.
Prepare lite Italian dressing according to package directions.
Add to pasta and mix well.
Add Salad Supreme.
Add roasted peppers, olives, red onion, celery and carrots.
Mix well and chill before serving.

title: hawaiian lemon pie
directions: Combine drained pineapple, brown sugar, 1/4 cup coconut and 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Spread over bottom of pastry shell. Cover edges of pastry with foil. Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes, removing foil after first 5 minutes of baking.
Cool.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Dice bacon and fry slowly until crisp.
Mix vinegar and water together (in a glass).
Add to bacon while still frying and bring to a slow boil.
Break lettuce into small chunks; pour hot mixture of bacon over lettuce.
Add salt, pepper and sugar to taste. Great side dish with Salmon Patties.

title: crispy slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion and pepper in large bowl and set aside. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Pour over vegetables and toss.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: raisin cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place all ingredients into a mixing bowl until batter has no lumps. Place in a baking dish and bake for about 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Let cool about 2 to 3 minutes and serve.

title: apple crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together the flour, oatmeal, cinnamon and brown sugar in mixing bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Slice apples into pan.
Sprinkle mixture on top; bake for 40 minutes.
Makes a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: tasty punch
directions: Freeze the first six ingredients to slush.
Add ginger ale at the time of serving.
Serves 50.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown together the ground beef and onion.
Add the enchilada sauce and soups.
In a greased dish, layer tortillas and soup mixture.
Top with cheese.
Repeat until all mixture is used up. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: old fashion pork n' beans
directions: Brown both sides of desired amount of pork chops, center cut preferred.
Sprinkle on salt, pepper, ground ginger and paprika. Remove pork chops from skillet.
Put baked beans in skillet.
Add Kitchen Bouquet to beans.
Add water.
Place pork chops on top of beans.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Melt margarine and combine with other ingredients, except cheese. Mix well. Pour into an 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until the middle is set and the top is brown if using cheese. Sprinkle it on top and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla and let stand 1 hour, covered.
Cream butter and sugars together.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: sweet 'n sour meat balls(serves a "whole bunch" and goes over well.)
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: maili's lemon raspberry linzer hearts
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Sift together the dry ingredients; add to the butter mixture and beat well.
Add the egg, vanilla and lemon extract and beat again until well mixed. Shape dough into two flattened rounds; wrap and refrigerate at least one hour.
Preheat the oven to 350° and grease cookie sheets or line with parchment paper.
On a well floured board, roll out the dough until 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out large hearts and then cut smaller hearts out of the middles of half of the large hearts (do not discard).
Spread a very small amount of raspberry jam in the middle of the whole hearts and place the hearts whose centers have been removed on top of the large whole hearts.
Place these on a cookie sheet.
Place a small amount of raspberry jam on the remaining little hearts and place another little heart on top of it.
Place the small hearts on a cookie sheet also.
The cookies should be 1 to 2 inches apart on the cookie sheet.
Bake for about 10 minutes; do not let the cookies brown.
Cool on racks.
After they are cool and just before serving, sift powdered sugar over the top of them.

title: butternuts
directions: Cream margarine with sugar and salt.
Blend in flour until smooth.
Stir in nuts and chocolate pieces.
Shape dough, a scant teaspoon, into small balls.
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheets. Bake in slow oven at 325° for 15 minutes or until firm.
Cool completely before glazing.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put asparagus in casserole dish.
Add soup and milk.
Add chopped egg and place cheese slices on top.
Cover with fried onions or bread crumbs (two slices of toast crumbled).
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, oleo, salt, syrup and vanilla for 15 minutes or to hard crack stage.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 teaspoon soda. Mix well.
Pour over popcorn and mix and mix.
Place in oven at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir one or twice during the hour.
Keep airtight.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potato with mixer.
Melt butter and add to potatoes.
Add sugar and salt. Beat eggs and add vanilla and flour.
Mix thoroughly. Pour mixture in greased casserole.

title: chili
directions: Heat oil in pan; brown meat.
Drain.
In a larger pan, add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: salsa
directions: Simmer ingredients until thick, approximately 2 hours.
Add cornstarch if needed to thicken.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Shape mixture into 2 balls; roll each ball in pecans, then in parsley.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with crackers.
Yield:
2 cheese balls.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and cheddar cheese in small bowl with electric blender on medium speed until well blended.
Mix in all remaining ingredients except pecans; cover.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Shape into ball; roll in pecans. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake for 2 to 3 hours at 325°. Stir every half hour.
Mmmm good!

title: spinach maria
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on box.
Drain.
Melt together cheese and spices.
Add enough mayonnaise to make the cheese pourable.
Mix in with spinach.
Put spinach mixture in casserole dish and top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese. Combine all ingredients.
Roll into balls 1-inch and place on pan.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: grandma miller's relish
directions: Grind the peppers, tomatoes and onions and press out the juices.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 2 minutes, then drain water.
Then put in vinegar, sugar, mustard and salt.
Cook 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: basic cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well;
pour
into
a greased pan or skillet and bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, milk
and salt in double boiler for 1 hour.
Stir in sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine pears and their syrup with cake mix and eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Blend at low mixer speed until moistened.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Spread with broiled frosting while still warm.
Put under broiler until bubbly, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: grandma northern's zucchini cake
directions: Place eggs, oil, zucchini and sugar in a large bowl; blend well.
Stir in nuts.
In a separate bowl, mix together the dry ingredients (remaining).
Combine two mixtures and stir.
Pour into greased and floured pan.

title: easy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add broth and bring to a boil.
Add noodles and cook until done.
Add cheese and broccoli.
Heat until broccoli is done and cheese is melted.

title: open-faced burgers
directions: Mix together.
Spread meat mixture on each half of hamburger bun.
Be sure to spread meat evenly on the bun.
Don't miss the edges of bun, so not to burn edges.
Broil for as long as it takes to cook meat.

title: shocking pink dip
directions: Put cream cheese in small bowl.
Add gelatin and milk to cream cheese.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended and smooth.
Put mixture into serving bowl.
Put bowl into refrigerator to chill until serving time.

title: philly cheese balls
directions: Combine cheeses and 2 tablespoons margarine; mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Mold into balls, using the Cracker Barrel container coated with margarine.
Chill until firm.

title: lime ice cream punch
directions: Beat lime sherbet and ice cream to a creamy consistency.
Add pineapple juice and all the ginger ale; stir.
Serve immediately. More ginger ale can be added.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with stuffing and melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are brown.

title: mock lobster
directions: Put haddock in a shallow pan and almost cover with milk.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or in microwave for 15 minutes.

title: gooey butter bars
directions: Mix together the cake mix, 3 eggs and butter.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Batter will be thick.
Blend remaining eggs (3), powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over top of batter. Bake in preheated 350° oven until top has a brown glaze and pulls away from sides (40 to 50 minutes).
Cool and cut into bars.

title: beef and rice
directions: Cook stew beef until tender.
Mix all soups together. Add cooked beef. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cook Minute rice according to package. Serve in individual servings, placing rice on bottom and soup and beef mixture on top.
Substitute chicken for beef for a different taste.

title: captain crunch
directions: Mix in a big bowl.
Melt Sathers 1 pound 8 ounce chocolate bark candy.
Pour over mixture.
Drop by heaping tablespoonful onto wax paper.

title: snowball jewels
directions: Combine coconut, almond extract, M&M's, sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes, or until edges are very lightly browned.
Using moistened spatula, immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool thoroughly on wire rack.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy large pot over medium heat.
Add onions and saute until deep golden brown, stirring occasionally, about 20 minutes.
Add beer.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add both stocks and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
(Soup can be prepared 1 day ahead; cover and refrigerate. Bring to simmer before continuing.)

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Save 2 tablespoons bacon drippings; cook onions in bacon drippings until tender. Blend in flour, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Add vinegar and water; cook until sauce thickens.
In large bowl mix potatoes, bacon and eggs.
Pour hot sauce over mixture and mix well.
Pour in casserole.
Serve warm.

title: icebox cake
directions: You will also need a large glass cake Pyrex dish.

title: cheese cake easy
directions: Soften cream cheese; add sugar and blend in one egg at a time. Add vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust (oversized 12 inches).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Chill and top with your favorite topping.
Serve.

title: ham and potato bake
directions: Combine onion and butter in 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and cook on High 10 minutes, stirring once.
Remove onion from dish and set aside.
Layer half of potatoes and half of ham in bottom of dish.
Combine flour, salt and pepper and sprinkle half of mixture over potatoes.
Top with half of onion and half of cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
Repeat layering.
Scald milk and pour over casserole; cover and cook until potatoes in center of dish are tender.
Makes about 4 to 6 servings.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain juice from asparagus.
Place 1 can asparagus in bottom of casserole.
Spoon 1/2 can mushroom soup on top of asparagus. Put a layer of cracker crumbs, then grated cheese.
Repeat, cheese will be on top.
Dot with butter and bake at about 350° for approximately 45 to 60 minutes.
(I spoon some of the asparagus juice over the crackers each time so that it isn't so dry.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In heavy gauge saucepan, combine sugar, butter and Carnation evaporated milk.
Bring to a full rolling boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add Nestle peanut butter morsels; stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth.
Add Kraft Marshmallow Creme and vanilla extract; beat until well blended.
Pour into foil-lined 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with peanuts and press into fudge.
Chill until firm.

title: banana split dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass dish, pat graham crackers mixed with butter on bottom of dish.
Mix 2 cups of powdered sugar with 2 sticks of oleo and eggs.
(Mix no less than 15 minutes.)
Pour this mixture over graham crackers.
Pour drained pineapple over and layer with sliced bananas.
Last, put Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mom's health bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; set aside.
Mix sugar, molasses, salt and melted shortening thoroughly.
Add yeast.
Gradually add dry ingredients, reserving some flour to knead.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic and all flour is worked in.
Place in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Mold into 2 loaves and place in greased pan.
Make indentation down center. Cover and let rise for 1 hour or more.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: texas corn bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients, EXCEPT CORN CHIPS, together.
Spoon into a casserole dish that has been sprayed with nonstick oil. Sprinkle corn chips over top. Bake for 45 minutes or until chips are browned.
