title: bread-in-a-jar(great for gift giving)
directions: Instructions must be followed exactly.

title: baked stuffed pumpkin-american indian
directions: Note:
Add green chiles for extra flavor if preferred.

title: cranberry-sour cream jello
directions: Let Jell-O and water jell partially. Add sour cream. Add cranberry sauce.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Moisten potatoes with water.
Shake a few times in plastic bag with mixture. Melt butter.
Place potatoes in a single layer in baking pan with melted butter. Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour. Turn when golden brown.

title: overnight sausage and egg souffle
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Blend together milk, eggs, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
To bake, preheat oven to 350°.
Uncover pan and bake for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve flavored jello in boiling water.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in cold water.
Mix everything together.
Pour mixture into a large bowl.
Chill in refrigerator for 10 minutes.
Cut using cookie cutters.
Eat! Yum! Yum!

title: quick and easy baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place split breasts in bottom of glass 9 x 13-inch casserole. Mix cranberry sauce, dressing and soup mix together; pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with wild rice.

title: basic cole slaw
directions: Toss together all ingredients.
Before serving, stir in 1 cup chopped tomato or apple, if desired.
Makes 4 cups.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl and beat at medium speed for approximately 2 minutes.
Note:
Batter will be very runny.
Pour into a tube pan (greased) and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 5 ingredients, then add next 5.
Stir well.
Add nuts (if desired).
Put into 2 loaf pans or 4 mini loaf pans, greased lightly.
Bake approximately 45 minutes, less for smaller pans.

title: basic cookie dough
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, eggs, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla or butter flavoring.
Add flour, salt and soda. Mix in chips, M&M's or oatmeal.

title: chillighetti
directions: Add salt, onion and chili powder to hamburger.
Cook until onion is tender.
In a 2 1/2-quart casserole add spaghetti and kidney beans.
Add meat mixture.
Combine tomato juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over all; cover. Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.

title: david eyre's pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a mixing bowl, combine flour, milk, eggs and nutmeg.
Beat lightly; leave batter a little lumpy.
Melt butter in a pie pan in oven; pour in batter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and return briefly to oven.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and serve with lemon wedges, confectioners sugar or jelly.
Serves 2 to 4 people.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oatmeal to boiling water; let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add oatmeal.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture, stirring just enough to blend.
Add vanilla. Place in greased and floured 12 x 7 1/2 x 3/4-inch baking dish. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chili
directions: *If you don't have picante sauce, use 1 quart tomatoes, 1 chopped green pepper and 1 small hot pepper.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, nutmeg and butter.
Add eggs; beat smooth. Pour over rhubarb in a 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Top with latticed crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Cream sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla together.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add undrained crushed pineapple and mix well, but do not use electric mixer.
Add diced bananas and nuts.
Batter will be thick.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine sugar, canned milk and marshmallows in a saucepan. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and cook for 5 minutes.
Add butter and chocolate morsels.
Beat until morsels are melted.
Add vanilla and beat until consistency of pudding.
Pour over cake.
Covers 2 layers on tops and sides.

title: vanilla cup custard
directions: Boil the milk, then beat together the eggs, sugar and vanilla. Add the milk slowly; mix well and strain, then pour in baking cups or coffee cups.
Place the cups in a pan with some water in it and bake in an oven at a temperature of 350°.
When baked, remove from the oven and serve cold.

title: quick and easy cheese sauce
directions: Combine soup and milk in sauce pour.
Heat until bubbly. reduce heat.
Add cheese, stir until melted.
Yield:
1-3/4 cups.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice the apples to make a 1-inch layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix thoroughly the sugar, cinnamon and flour and sprinkle over apple layer.

title: pecan lace cookies
directions: Combine eggs
and sugar in a large mixing bowl, stirring well. Combine
flour, baking powder and salt in a small mixing bowl; add
to
egg
mixture.
Mix
well.
Stir
in
vanilla and pecans. Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls 3 inches apart onto aluminum foil lined cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Let cool completely
on cookie sheets; peel off aluminum foil. Store cookies in airtight containers.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: mrs. sarner's oatmeal sand tarts
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add flour, oatmeal and other ingredients.
Roll in little balls and place on cookie sheet. Press with fork to flatten a little.
Bake in moderate oven 8 to 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Roll again later.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli, shrimp
meat,
salt and pepper in 7 x 11-inch baking
pan.
Combine
soup,
salad dressing and lemon juice; cover with
mixture.
Top with cheese and crumbs.
When done spoon over cooked noodles.

title: jumbo shrimp a la greek(garides)
directions: Wash, shell and devein shrimp.
In large skillet, add butter and saute shrimp 30 seconds on each side.
Mix together lemon juice, oregano, garlic salt, pepper and dry mustard.
Pour over shrimp; simmer 1 minute.
Add dry sherry and simmer 2 minutes longer.
With slotted spoon, remove shrimp to a bed of rice pilaf. Boil butter-shrimp mixture about 2 minutes, until reduced to about half.
Pour over shrimp and rice.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain and wash under hot water using a colander.
This removes excess fat.
Return meat to skillet and add all the remaining ingredients.
Cook about 5 minutes until well blended.
Pour into a casserole dish and place in a 350° preheated oven.
Bake for about 1 hour.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix butter and cream cheese over low heat.
Add spinach and lemon juice to cream cheese and butter.
Place artichokes and spinach in shallow baking dish.
Top with 1/2 cup bread crumbs and 1 cup grated cheese.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and cocoa. Bring to a boil and cook for 1 1/2 minutes. Take from heat and add vanilla and oatmeal. Beat the mixture until it starts to get stiff.
Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Let cool and ready to eat.

title: the party salad
directions: Mix together in small or medium bowl. Refrigerate.

title: ground turkey meat loaf(low-fat - no-salt)
directions: In medium-sized bowl, mix oats, egg and water.
Add onion, celery, parsley flakes and thyme.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 turkey and mix.
Add remaining half and mix well.
Form into loaf and place in a shallow baking pan, greased with a few drops of cooking oil. (Grease nonstick pan also.) Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla.
Mix well. Add eggs.
pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; turn to 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix Tater Tots and onion.
Place in a greased casserole dish. Mix soup, milk, sour cream, cheese and margarine.
Pour over Tater Tot mixture and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; combine all other ingredients except cheese and margarine.
Add broccoli and pour into casserole dish. Cut margarine in small pieces and spread over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Place sweet potatoes in a pan and pour boiling salted water over them.	Let stand for 1/2 hour or boil about 10 minutes.
Dry them well and fry in hot oil in a black iron skillet.

title: homemade strawberry split ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, salt and pepper and beat yellows and whites separately.
Add vanilla.
Add salt, half and half, strawberries, bananas, pineapple and Jell-O.
Finish filling enough milk to make 1 gallon freezer.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken which has been salted and peppered.
Bone.
Set aside.
Combine cheese and milk in large saucepan, preferably a double boiler.
Melt cheese.
In broth of chicken, boil spaghetti. When done, add cheese, chicken, chopped black olives and almonds. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer 45 minutes after bringing to a boil.
Good made in a crock and easy.
May add water if too thick.
May substitute chicken for beef.
About 100 calories per cup.

title: molasses custard(or pie)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour, molasses and butter.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Makes three very small custards (or pie); about 3 cups.
Bake in 325° or 350° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients, add eggs and bananas.
Mix until flour is damp.
Add vanilla and shortening.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: rose's poppy seed cake
directions: Put all in large bowl and mix well for 4 to 5 minutes.
Grease and flour a Bundt cake pan and add mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Will be moist.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: matt's favorite banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Stir and toss together the flour, salt and baking soda.
In a large bowl, mix the shortening, sugar, mashed banana, eggs and walnuts.
Add the combined dry ingredients and stir just until the batter is blended.
Pour into prepared pan and bake for 65 to 70 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool in pan for 5 minutes, then turn out onto a rack to cool completely.

title: stuffed pork loin
directions: Hollow pork loin with clean knife sharpener poked through center longways and working loin with thumbs until small rounded hole goes all through length of pork loin (or carefully split open, horizontally with a sharp knife).

title: black bean and rice salad
directions: Mix rice with beans, pepper and salad dressing.
Let marinate overnight in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, place bean mixture on lettuce leaves.
Top with cheese, tomatoes and onion. Then a dollop of sour cream, if desired.

title: banana-nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, oblong 45 to 50 minutes. Cool.
Frost with vanilla butter frosting.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed.
Drain.
Return to pot to keep warm.
In a 2-quart pan, over medium heat, saute onion in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Stir in flour until blended.
Gradually stir in milk, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is slightly thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in Parmesan cheese.
Tear bread into small pieces to make 2 cups coarse bread crumbs.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in large bowl, making a well in the center.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into well.
Stir just enough to dampen all ingredients. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: easy hot buns
directions: Place warm water in a mixing bowl.
Stir in yeast, sugar, salt and margarine.
Add eggs and 2 cups flour.
Combine ingredients with mixer at low speed until all are moistened, approximately 2 minutes.
Add 2 cups of flour and blend until batter is smooth. Fill greased muffin cups a scant half full.
Allow to rise in a warm place until batter reaches top of cups, 30 to 40 minutes. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: mozzarella-crowned pork chops and spaghetti
directions: Heat butter in a large skillet.
Add chops and brown on both sides.
Remove them from skillet and keep warm.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Mix juice, onion and peppers in blender until mashed up good. Mix this and rest of ingredients together good.
Boil to desired thickness (approximately 4 hours).
Pour in hot jars and seal.
I saved old catsup bottles and used these.

title: oatmeal crispies(the best)
directions: Cream margarine and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add salt, flour and soda; mix well.
Fold in oats, nuts or coconut.
Shape into roll.
Wrap in wax paper; chill.
Slice and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: stir-fried oriental vegetables with chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce, cooking sherry, cornstarch, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Add chicken and marinate 10 to 15 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons of oil and Oriental Blend to wok or heavy skillet and stir-fry 8 to 10 minutes on high heat.
Remove vegetables.
Add an additional 2 tablespoons of oil and chicken pieces to wok, discarding marinade.
Stir-fry on high heat for 3 to 5 minutes. Add vegetables to chicken and stir-fry an additional 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve with cooked rice.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef with 1/2 cup chopped onion and drain.
Stir in can of cream of mushroom soup, enchilada sauce, garlic powder and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, while preparing crust.

title: easy-do pot roast
directions: Place foil in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle half of onion soup mix over foil.
Place meat on top and sprinkle remaining soup mix over meat.
Spoon undiluted soup over meat.
Fold foil over and seal tightly.

title: jalapeno rice
directions: Mix together and cook at 350° until hot (25 minutes). Sprinkle with paprika.

title: creamed scrambled eggs
directions: Cook White sauce until thick.

title: vinegar beans
directions: Mix beans and other ingredients together.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.
This is quick and easy and it works!

title: cool lime pie
directions: Cook pie crust according to directions on pie shell.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream and stir until melted. Chill until thickened, about 20 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping. Pour into baked pie crust.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours. Garnish with whipped topping, if desired.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bread and cheese.
Place 1/2 of ingredients in a casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese; add remaining ingredients and sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: goetta
directions: Cook meat, onion, salt and water.
Add oats when meat is done (10 to 15 minutes).
Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer until thick. Chill in pan.
Slice and brown.

title: grandma's cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix yeast, water, sugar and shortening in mixing bowl. Measure dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Mix well.

title: calico beans or bernadette's beans
directions: Saute the first 3 ingredients.
Then add the rest.
Mix and simmer together for about 1/2 to 1 hour in crock-pot.

title: delicious breakfast bars
directions: Spray a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread 1 can crescent rolls on bottom of pan.
Mix all ingredients (except egg white) and spread in pan.
Spread second can of crescent rolls over top.
Brush top with egg white.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar if desired.

title: apple bread
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Set aside.
In a large bowl, place oil, sugar, eggs, vanilla and apples.
Stir into flour mixture.
Add walnuts and mix.
Divide mixture between two greased pans.

title: breakfast on the run
directions: Slice bananas and freeze overnight.
Place ingredients in blender; blend until smooth.
Garnish with nutmeg.
Yields 2 servings.

title: crisp applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift the first 7 ingredients together. Beat margarine, sweetener and egg until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and applesauce alternately; mix well after each addition.
Fold in raisins and cereal.
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet, 1 inch apart.
Bake until golden (15 minutes).

title: manhatten clam chowder
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients with 1/2 of clam juice.
Microwave 7 to 8 minutes, covered, and stir halfway through.
Add tomatoes, shells and rest of juice.
Microwave, covered, for 10 to 12 minutes until shells are tender.
Stir in clams and microwave, covered, for 1 minute.

title: chicken curry
directions: Fry the onions in a large skillet until golden brown; add chicken pieces to the skillet.
Stir until the chicken meat is white.
Add 1 tablespoon salt.
While chicken is browning, add curry powder to the onion and chicken while stirring for a minute. Add 2 to 3 cups of hot water to the chicken; cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Add chopped tomatoes; cook 20 minutes or until how much gravy you want.
Serve over rice.
Reheat at 300° to 400° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and drain excessive grease.
Saute onion and celery in butter or margarine until soft; set aside.
Heat soups and Cheez Whiz.
Add rice and broccoli to vegetables.
Add soup mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ginger ale fruit punch
directions: If frozen orange juice is used, thaw and mix with 3 cans of water in a large container.
Then add all other ingredients, except ginger ale.
Mix well.
Just before serving, add ginger ale. If this punch is served over crushed or small cubed ice, reduce water to 4 quarts.
Food coloring may be added for color scheme.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook roast; cool 24 hours.
Slice paper thin or as thin as possible.
Mix barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Warm until sugar melts.
In crock-pot or roaster, alternate layers of meat and sauce.
(If not enough sauce, add small amount of tomato juice.)
Press into pot until meat is covered.
Bake or cook slow 275° for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve on buns.
Pork can be substituted for beef.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk gradually, stirring constantly to keep from lumping.
Add yolks and flavoring.
Add margarine.
Cook and stir over medium heat, about 10 minutes or until it comes to a boil.
(It won't be thick.) When cool, pour into pie shell and bake at 350° until browned.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Preboil cabbage; drain and chop.
Saute onions, celery and bell pepper in margarine.
Add cabbage and smother.
Add cheese and cook 5 minutes.
Add soup and enough bread crumbs to give consistency desired.
Place in greased casserole dish and cover with more bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heath bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
Put saltines (about 40) close together.
Boil butter, margarine and brown sugar
for 3 minutes after boiling starts.
Pour over crackers, spreading.
Cover completely.
Bake for 5 minutes (no longer).
After baking time is done, spread chocolate bits.
Wait a few minutes for the chocolate bits to melt and frost.
Add nuts evenly and separate them quickly.
Place in refrigerator.

title: rotini salad
directions: Cook rotini according to directions.
Rinse quick under cool water.
Place vegetables, tuna and vinegar in small bowl.
Mix all together.
Put macaroni in and add mayonnaise to hold together.
Refrigerate.

title: mae regan's lemon bread
directions: Lightly oil a regular loaf pan.
Cream margarine, sugar and eggs together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and finely grated lemon rind.
Add nuts.
Bake in 325° oven for about 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and prick top of bread all over with a toothpick.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Toast pecans in margarine on low heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
In a 3-quart saucepan, combine eggs, milk, brown sugar and salt.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture lightly coats a metal spoon.
Cool.
Stir in vanilla, light cream, evaporated milk and whipping cream.
Pour into gallon freezer can.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix sugar, coffee and water.
Add vanilla beans if using. Bring to a boil and simmer 2 hours.
Remove vanilla beans or add vanilla now.
Cover for 24 hours.
Stir in vodka.

title: brunch souffle casserole
directions: Slice 3 sausage links into 1/2-inch pieces.
Reserve for top garnish.
Slice each remaining link into 3 or 4 pieces.
Place sausage pieces into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bread cubes over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over bread.
Beat together eggs, milk, evaporated milk, mushroom soup and seasonings.
Pour over contents of pan.
Cover pan tightly.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Uncover and bake at 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand about 2 minutes to firm up before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and cool completely.
Mix with other ingredients. Chill overnight.

title: louisiana gumbo
directions: Saute onions, bell peppers, celery and garlic until tender.
If using frozen okra, add to onion mixture and continue to cook for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Prepare gravy mixture (flour and oil) until dark brown.
Make sure gravy is thick.

While preparing the gravy, put your pot on with the crab and dry shrimp in the water. Once the gravy mixture and onion mixture is done, add to the water along with the sausage, gizzard, seasoning and tomatoes.
Let cook for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add chicken wings and shrimp and let cook for another hour.
Serve over rice.

title: oreo freak out
directions: Crush Oreo cookies; soften ice cream.
Mix together ingredients folding gently.
Pour into container (dish).
Freeze again until ready to serve.

title: strawberry pinwheel shortcake
directions: Combine sliced berries and sugar, stirring gently.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Gradually add enough milk to form a soft dough, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead 4 or 5 times.
Roll the dough into an 11 x 8-inch rectangle on a lightly floured surface.

title: mix ahead salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite-size pieces in salad bowl.
Break cauliflower and broccoli into flowerets on top of lettuce.
Slice green onions (and some of the tops), onto broccoli and cauliflower.

title: dirt
directions: Mix melted oleo with cookie crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup cookie mixture.
Pat rest down in an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Mix the pudding with the milk.
Add cream cheese; mix well.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Spread pudding mixture over cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top; chill for about an hour.

title: layered salad
directions: Put cut lettuce in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Layer in order given.
Combine 2 cups salad dressing and sugar.
Frost completely. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil.
Make 12 hours ahead and refrigerate.

title: cut-it-short torte
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on package in greased and floured pans.
Cool.
Spread whipped topping over each layer.
Put cherry pie filling on top of the Cool Whip.
Stack one layer on top of the other, after putting the topping and filling on it. The icing for each layer, as well as the top, is the Cool Whip and cherry pie filling.
Chill until set.

title: easter pie
directions: Roll out 1/2 crust for bottom.
Save other half for top.
Mix flour, oleo and cream cheese for crust.
Place 1 crust in bottom of square casserole.
Alternate 2 layers of ham, eggs and cheese. Place other crust on top.
Turn in edges.
Bake at 350° until top browns.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook meat until it falls off bone.
Let cool; pick meat into small pieces.
Add	meat,
tomatoes,
corn,
catsup,
hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce
and
lemon.
Add these seasonings to taste according to the
way
you like.
Let cook slowly for it burns easily.
Stir often.
This	makes
a
lot.	It can be frozen to be used
later.
When preparing meat, remove as much fat as possible. Save stock, can be used later.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Partially cook celery and onion.
Mix all well in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Cook beef and garlic in oil until beef is browned.
Cut beef in strips and add onions.
Stir in soup, water, and soy sauce. Add broccoli.
Cook until broccoli is done.
Pour over egg noodles or cooked rice.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Sift together
in
a
bowl, flour, sugar and soda.
Mix into this
margarine
(or butter) until texture resembles corn meal. Beat eggs and add bananas.	Then add to dry ingredients and
mix until
just
moist.
Bake
40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small ones.

title: broccoli quiche(the impudent oyster)
directions: Arrange broccoli and the cheese in 9-inch pie crust.
Mix mayonnaise, milk and eggs.
Pour over broccoli and cheese. Sprinkle with nutmeg and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain well in a colander.
Heat remaining ingredients together over low heat while broccoli cooks. Place drained broccoli in greased casserole.
Pour remaining ingredients over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: company cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower 10 to 15 minutes until crispy tender; drain well.
Place 1/2 of the cauliflower in loaf pan or round casserole dish.
Spread 1/2 cup sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese; repeat layers.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: super applesauce cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients and beat on medium speed for 4 minutes.
Place in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings. Crumble bacon, reserve 2 tablespoons.
Cook beans until tender. Drain well.
Cook mushrooms and 1/4 cup onions in bacon drippings over medium heat about 10 minutes.
Add bacon, hot cooked beans and pepper.
Put in a 2-quart serving dish.
Microwave cheese spread as on label.
Pour over bean mixture and sprinkle with reserved bacon.
Serves 8.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together.
Spread out in casserole dish.
Crush 1 stack Town House crackers and put on top.
Melt 1 stick oleo and put on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In greased 2-quart casserole dish arrange sliced potatoes in 3 layers.
Sprinkle each layer with 1/3 of the flour, salt, pepper and butter.
(Butter should be dotted.)
Heat the milk to scalding.
Pour over the potatoes.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 60 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: butter coffee cake
directions: Beat first five ingredients until fluffy.
Mix cinnamon, brown sugar and pecans.
Sprinkle 1/2 sugar mixture on bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pudding mixture over it and put rest on top and gently swirl with spatula.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken recipe
directions: Brown chicken in butter or margarine.
Add soup to drippings. Slowly add wine (stir until smooth).
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and cook until tender.
Serve with fluffed rice.

title: hot crabmeat puffs on toast beds
directions: Trim crusts from bread slices: cut into squares or shapes. Butter one side only and toast only the one side.

title: my grandma's chili sauce
directions: Chop the first 5 ingredients fine or grind. Add the remaining ingredients and boil for 2 full hours. Add more seasoning to taste.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch or two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pans).
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl; beat on medium speed 1/2 minute.
Pour into pans.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: czech houska bread
directions: Combine milk, water, sugar, salt and butter in a saucepan and heat until the butter just melts (very warm, but not hot). Combine warm liquid with 1 cup of flour and yeast.
Beat at high speed for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add lemon rind, mace, eggs, raisins and 1 1/2 cups nuts.
Then continue to add remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until satiny smooth.
Let rise until doubles in bulk, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: play clay(not to eat!)
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in plastic bag or airtight container in refrigerator.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Flake corned beef into a bowl.
Add cheese, olives and onion. Mix well.
Add catsup and mix to moisten.
You may need more catsup to develop a spreading consistency.
Slice rolls and butter each half.
Mound corned beef mixture on bottom half of roll and top with the other half of the roll.
Wrap sandwiches in foil and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese melts and mixture is hot.

title: strawberry jam cake and icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add jam and well-beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add raisins and nuts, floured with 2 tablespoons flour. Bake in 2 layers at 350° for 30 minutes or until tested with a toothpick.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.	Chill.	Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: date bars
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon color.
Add sugar. Gradually add vanilla.
Fold yolk mixture into stiff beaten egg whites, using spatula.
Fold in dates, nuts, flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut while hot.
Roll in powdered sugar when cool.

title: mud pie
directions: Press cookies and oleo in pie pan.
Layer softened ice cream, then Cool Whip.
Freeze overnight.
Drip on fudge sauce and slivered almonds before serving.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Prick crust several times with a fork. Line with aluminum foil and fill with dry beans or pie weights. Bake until lightly browned, 10 to 20 minutes.
Place crust on rack to cool completely.
Reduce oven heat to 375°.

title: coconut candy
directions: Melt chocolate and line small muffin cups with chocolate. Mix coconut, potatoes, sugar and flavoring well.
Spoon into each cup.
Cover with chocolate coating.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans. Set aside. Mash sweet potatoes with heavy syrup in a large mixing bowl using a fork or potato masher. Set aside 1/2 cup for icing. Add the cake mix, eggs, oil and cinnamon. Blend with mixer on low speed for 1 minute; stop. Scrape down sides with rubber spatula; mix on medium for 2 to 3 minutes, scraping sides. Batter should be well combined and thickened. Divide batter between pans, smoothing out with spatula. Bake until they spring back when touched with a finger (approximately 28 to 31 minutes). Put on plate right side up. Spread with icing after cooling 10 minutes. Stack on second layer and finish icing.

title: fajitas
directions: Combine orange juice, vinegar, spices and garlic.
Toss chicken in mixture and let soak for 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir-fry chicken with onion and peppers for 10 minutes in hot oiled skillet.
Serve on warm tortillas.
Makes 4 to 6 fajitas.

title: mary's breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up 4 slices of white bread and place in a greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Brown and drain sausage; spread over bread.
Sprinkle with sharp grated cheese.

title: crab puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cut English muffins in half. Spread crab mixture evenly over muffin halves.
Place on cookie sheet in freezer until firm.
Cut into quarters and freeze overnight.
Place on cookie sheet and cook in oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cool and break into pieces.
Mix cream of chicken soup and 1/2 cup of water in saucepan.
Heat until creamy.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine ground round, eggs, bread crumbs, ketchup, water and soup mix.
Mix thoroughly and place in a 10-inch glass pie plate. Shape mixture into a wreath, leaving a 2-inch open area in the center.
Cover with wax paper, rotating dish twice during cooking. Microwave on 70% (Medium-high) 16 to 17 minutes.
Remove any grease that may have collected.
Pour tomato sauce over top; do not cover.
Microwave on 70% for 4 to 6 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Brown hamburger meat with chopped onion; drain.
Add eggs, soup (undiluted), nutmeg and frozen broccoli or spinach that has thawed. Mix all together.
Pour into pie shell, then add cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease baking sheet heavily. Combine sugar, corn syrup and salt in a 3-quart casserole. Stir in peanuts. Microwave at High (100%) until light brown, 10 to 13 minutes, stirring 1 to 2 times. Stir in remaining ingredients until light and foamy. Quickly spread on greased baking sheet. Spread as thin as possible for brittle candy. Cool and break into pieces. Yield: about 2 pounds.

title: hawaiian dip and fruit
directions: Cut pineapple in half lengthwise; loosen insides of both halves with grapefruit knife and remove fruit, leaving the shells. Save one shell and turn upside down to drain.
Finely chop enough pineapple to make 2/3 cup; cut remaining pineapple into 1-inch pieces.
Combine chopped pineapple with cream cheese, chutney, curry powder and mustard.
Spoon mixture into drained pineapple shell and sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Surround pineapple shell with pineapple and other fresh fruit for dipping.

title: hearty turkey soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent. Stir in curry powder and cook one minute longer. Stir in potatoes, carrots, celery, broth, and seasoning to taste and bring to boil over low heat. Stir in peas, turkey, oregano and parsley. Cook until vegetables are barely
tender, but crisp. Combine milk and flour and stir in gently until well blended. The soup should be slightly thickened. Check seasoning.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Boil 1 cup water with 1 cup sugar and cornstarch; boil until clear and thick. Add Jell-O; set aside.
Rinse strawberries; set aside.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cream cheese until smooth. Add Cool Whip.

In large bowl, break up part of cake, then cover with part of cream cheese mixture, then tear apart more of cake, then cover with more of cream cheese. Mix strawberries with Jell-O. Pour over top of cake mixture. Refrigerate.

title: spinach low-fat lasagna
directions: Heat sauce; add garlic.
In a large bowl mix Ricotta or cottage cheese with defrosted or fresh chopped spinach, beaten egg whites, 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese and basil.
In a 15 x 9 x 3-inch pan line the bottom with sauce, then place 4 to 5 uncooked noodles on sauce, then place a layer of mixture on top of noodles.
Then place a layer of sauce, then noodles, then mixture again.
Top with the rest of sauce (generously) and sprinkle with remaining cheese on top of sauce.
Bake in oven 15 minutes at 375°, then turn down to 350° for 30 more minutes.

title: pistachio supreme
directions: Layer One:
Combine butter, pecans and flour.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: horseradish jelly
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar 3 minutes.
Add horseradish and return to boil.
Stir in coloring.
Stir in pectin.
Bring to a full boil, and boil hard for one minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, skim and pour into hot sterilized jelly glasses.
Seal with paraffin.
Makes 3 (6 ounce) glasses.
Good with cooked cabbage or cabbage, apples and onions cooked together.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in white sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients. Pour over a layer of fresh or canned peaches in buttered pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and form into balls about the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coconut muffins
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until browns.

title: black  magic cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder, and salt in a large mixing bowl:
Add eggs, coffee, buttermilk, oil, vanilla, and flavorings.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes (batter will be thin).
Pour into oblong pan.
Bake for 40 or 45 minutes at 350 degrees.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots for 7 minutes; drain.
Layer carrots, onion and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over carrots.
Marinate overnight.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Blend ingredients and store in a tightly covered container.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and stir thoroughly.
Stir in eggs well, but do not beat.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Put 9 or 10 pecan halves on top.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 10 minutes. Reduce heat (325°) for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely before cutting.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: rice veracruz
directions: Saute beef, onions and peppers in oil in a Corning Ware dish. Stir for 5 minutes until brown and onions are tender.
Add tomatoes, consomme, salt and 1/2 the olives.
Bring slowly to boiling.
Stir in rice and cook for 5 minutes, covered.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Uncover, stir in cheese and olives.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: hawaiian pineapple banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in pecans.
Combine ingredients in a separate bowl.
Mix well.
Pour wet mixture into dry mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans.
Bake for about 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes, then cool on wire racks.

title: jolly rice(african dish)
directions: In Dutch oven, heat oil.
Fry chicken.
Add onion and tomatoes to chicken.
(If desired, other vegetables such as green peppers, cabbage or mushrooms may be added.)
Cook vegetables until soft. Add 2 cups of water and the spices.
Cover and cook over low heat, about 25 minutes or until the chicken is soft.
Add 1 1/2 cups or more water and tomato paste; bring to a boil.
Add rice; cover and continue cooking about 15 minutes longer or until rice is done.
Stir often to prevent sticking.
If rice mixture becomes too dry, add more water.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Blend in butter.
Spread 2/3 of the mixture in a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Over this spread blueberries.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: tarragon chicken in wine
directions: Shake chicken in mixture of flour, Nature Seasons and paprika. Brown in margarine/olive oil mixture.
Pour wine and lemon juice over; sprinkle with tarragon, basil and parsley.
Add mushrooms. Simmer 20 minutes.
Turn chicken twice during simmering to distribute seasonings.

title: no guilt chicken pot pie
directions: Mix soup, mixed vegetables and chicken in bowl.
Spoon into 9 inch pie pan.
Combine baking mix, milk and egg in a bowl and mix well.
Spread over prepared layer.
Bake at 400 for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: creamy finger jello
directions: Stir water and jello to dissolve.
Cool to room temperature. Beat milk and pudding for 1 to 2 minutes.
Quickly pour into jello and blend.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: lipton california dip
directions: Blend soup mix with sour cream; chill.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: orange cake
directions: Grease an 8-inch cake pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.

Beat the sugar and egg yolks together so that the mixture foams. Gradually beat in the strained orange juice, almonds and flour. Beat the egg whites into stiff peaks and fold into the mixture. Pour the mixture into the cake pan and bake for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: super quick sticky buns
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a 9-inch cake pan (round), combine margarine, brown sugar and corn syrup.
Spread evenly and sprinkle with nuts.

title: fancy fruit
directions: Drain juice from canned fruit.
Stir in Tang and then mix pudding into juice.
Add canned and fresh fruit into mixture and refrigerate.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix and shape into balls.

title: seven-layer casserole
directions: In a buttered casserole layer rice, ham, onion and broccoli. In separate bowl combine soup, cheese and milk.
Spread over broccoli.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: dolly dates
directions: Cream shortening, salt, vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour and soda and alternately add flour and milk. Add dates and nuts.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, soup and melted margarine.
Mix in chicken and cracker crumbs.
Add small amount of broth, if needed.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle with seed.
Bake at 400° until bubbly and brown.

title: linda kelley's italian veal stew
directions: Trim fat from meat; rinse and put in a pot with oil, garlic and onion.
Let cook until meat is brown (about 20 minutes).
Mix the tomatoes with a cup of water and add to the stew.
Add parsley, salt, pepper, oregano, frying peppers and mushrooms. Cover and let cook until tender and meat is done.
Boil potato cubes in a pot of water until fork-soft.
Drain.
Serve potatoes and stew together.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix well; pour in graham cracker crust.

title: cheese logs
directions: Mix all together with hand and shape into log.
Roll in chili powder.
Makes 3 to 4 logs.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots for 7 minutes; drain.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Let cool at room temperature.
Serve.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter the muffin pans.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In a separate bowl, stir the milk, egg and butter into the oatmeal.
Stir until well blended. Combine the two mixtures and mix well.
Spoon each muffin cup 2/3 full of batter.
Bake for about 20 minutes or until a broomstraw comes out dry when inserted in center.

title: patty's pate
directions: Put melted butter in blender; add peeled onion.
Chop.
Cook together the remaining ingredients (except eggs, bacon and applesauce).
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Mix applesauce, bacon and eggs with butter mixture in blender, then add cooked liver mixture to blender.
Blend together and remove to a serving dish and chill.
Garnish with olives, parsley or your favorite garnish.

title: chicken, broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Chinese noodles, together and pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with Chinese noodles and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Place Veg-All in 1 1/2-quart dish.
In saucepan, melt 1 stick butter and Cheez Whiz.
Pour cheese mixture over vegetables. Crumble Ritz crackers on top of casserole.
Melt 1 stick butter and pour over crackers.
Place in oven at 350° until top is brown.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, evaporated milk and butter in a 3-quart casserole.
Cook on full power for 10 to 13 minutes.
Stir mixture 3 times during cooking time.
Beat in marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla with wire whip until mixture is smooth and creamy. Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.

title: layered tortillas
directions: Mix together salad dressing mix, mayonnaise, milk, and salsa. Combine green onions and chilies, set aside.
Combine cheeses, set aside.
Place one tortilla on a pizza pan or cookie sheet or place in a cake pan depending on the size of your tortilla.
* I use ten inch and end up with two stacks of each.*

Spread dressing mixture thinly over tortillas, sprinkle with the onions and chilies, follow with some cheese. (Hint: If the dressing mixture is spread too thickly, they won't cook through and will be mushy.) Continue layering, making 2 stacks of three or four, using up all ingredients; extra cheese can be sprinkled over the top layer. Bake for 400 degrees for about 20 minutes until cheese melts and top is lightly browned.
Slice into wedges; serve with sour cream, salsa, or picante sauce.

title: holiday mint pie
directions: Mix cookies and hot water.
Spoon into crust and gently spread to cover bottom.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar, milk and peppermint extract.
Fold in whipped topping. Divide mixture in half; stir in food coloring in one half until evenly colored.
Fill pie crust with alternate dollops of white and green mixtures.
Smooth top of pie with spatula.
Chill 3 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut apples, orange and bananas into chunks.
Mix all ingredients and chill for 1 hour.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add curry powder and lemon pepper.
Stir in crabmeat.
Refrigerate several hours.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: 1 bowl chocolate cake
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar; add flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix. Add oil.
Heat 2 minutes.
Add 2 eggs and mix 2 minutes.
Add buttermilk and mix 2 minutes.
Add hot water.
This is real runny. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with your favorite frosting.
Cake is real moist and keeps well in refrigerator.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, butter, shortening, egg, vanilla and almond extracts.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
When removing cookie sheet from oven, gently place sheet on surface to keep cookies from falling.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Combine hash brown potato mix and water.
Stir well.
Let stand covered 15 minutes.
Drain.
Heat tortillas in foil in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Combine hash browns, eggs, sausage, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add egg mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring gently, until eggs are soft. Fill each tortilla with 1/2 cup egg mixture and cheese, picante sauce and sour cream if desired.
Roll up, placing seam side down. Makes 6.

title: barbecued spareribs - chinese style
directions: In a
medium saucepan, combine all ingredients except pork. Bring to a simmering boil.
Place pork in a large shallow bowl or pan. Pour warm marinade over pork. Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.

title: crab casserole
directions: Lightly mix first 9 ingredients.
Transfer to casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: one, two, three salad
directions: Heat 1 can applesauce, then dissolve 1 small box jello (your preference) into the hot applesauce. Remove from heat and add 1 cup 7-Up. Mix well and put in refrigerator to jell.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in margarine.
In large bowl, combine toasted bread and cornbread with sage, poultry seasoning and black pepper.
Add the sauteed ingredients; pour in broth and mix well.
Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes; uncover and bake about 5 more minutes.
Yields 15 to 18 servings.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into a 9 x 15-inch greased baking dish.
Top with buttered cracker or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: nighty nites
directions: Set oven to 350°.
With wire whisk or beater, whip egg whites until foamy, then, adding sugar, a little at a time, beat until stiff.
Fold in vanilla, chocolate bits and nuts.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg.
Add pineapple and 1 cup crumbs.
Sprinkle 1 cup crumbs on bottom of 8 x 8 pan.
Spread mixture on top of crumbs and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top. Refrigerate 12 hours and serve with whipped cream.

title: tuna tabouli(strict fast)
directions: Drain tuna.
Soak bulgur in water 1 hour.
Drain well. Combine with onion, tomato, parsley, oil, lemon juice, vinegar and salt.
Break tuna with a fork.
Fold into bulgur mixture.
Chill. Spoon into salad bowl lined with lettuce.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Add water to jello and let gel a bit.
Add pineapple and let gel a bit again.
Fold in the rest of the ingredients.
Serves 8.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Heat cider with cinnamon and cloves for 15 minutes.
Remove spices and add other ingredients.
(Add 1 quart ginger ale, if desired.)
Reheat.

title: tempting snacks
directions: Mix shortening, cheese, flour and soup mix in a bowl until well blended. Shape into a 12-inch long roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Barely
cover
cabbage in boiling, salted water;
cover and let boil 7 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry ground beef, onion and garlic and drain. Add enchilada sauce and 1/4 can water and simmer. Mix and melt in saucepan the soups, tomatoes, 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese and 1/2 can water. Melt slowly and stir often until cheese is melted. Line bottom of long Pyrex or Corning pan with Doritos nacho cheese. Put 1/2 of meat mixture over the Doritos, then 1/2 of soup mixture over that. Crumble some more of Doritos, then other 1/2 of meat mixture, ending up with other 1/2 of soup mixture. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbles in middle. Remove and sprinkle 1/2 pound shredded Cheddar cheese on top. Serve immediately.

title: mincemeat fudge pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Put penuche quick fudge mix into bowl. Add eggs, water, mincemeat and melted butter.
Beat with rotary beater until thoroughly blended.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 375°
for 40 minutes until filling is set. Cool.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream. Serves 8 to 10. Tastes somewhat like pecan pie.

title: 3 cheese lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in large saucepan.
Drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and let simmer.
In large boiler boil noodles with a teaspoon of oil.
Spray 9 x 13-inch dish with nonstick spray. Cover bottom of pan with sauce.
Spoon on 8 to 10 spoonfuls of cottage or Ricotta cheese.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with 4 noodles.
Repeat sauce, cheese, noodles and sauce.
Sprinkle top with Mozzarella and Cheddar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Place on cookie sheet to allow for overflow.
Cool 10 minutes after removing from oven.

title: cheesy hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: monterey jack triangles
directions: Combine mayonnaise, scallion, lime juice and zest in small bowl.
Set aside.
Remove crust from bread.
Divide cheese between 2 slices of bread.
Top with bread.
Combine butter and parsley. Spread evenly on both sides of sandwiches.
Heat nonstick skillet to medium heat.
Cook sandwiches until brown.
Cool slightly.
Cut into triangles.
Serve with dipping sauce.

title: peanut salad
directions: Prepare Suddenly Salad according to directions and toss with the mushrooms and peanuts.

title: apricot bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; stir in rolled oats and sugar.
Cut in butter (oleo) until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 crumb mix into 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan (pack firmly).
Spread with preserves.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° about 35 minutes, until brown.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: washing fluid
directions: This is excellent for cleaning woolen goods. Will not injure colored fabrics.

title: kielbasa appetizer
directions: Cut kielbasa into 6-inch chunks.
Then boil in water 15 minutes.
Remove from water. When cool or partially cool, cut into half-inch slices.
In baking dish or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, mix the jar of barbecue sauce, the crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges. For a thick sauce, omit juices from pineapple and oranges. Thinner sauce, add juices.
Add the kielbasa slices and stir until they are covered with sauce.
Bake in 375° oven until sauce bubbles.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix and bake in 3 layers at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add vanilla.
Add chips and nuts and stir in flour.
Form into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press flat with sugar coated glass.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in food processor.
Pour milk in large bowl.
Add pudding.
Beat until blended.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir in Cool Whip and 3/4 of crushed cookies.
Garnish with remaining cookies.
Top with gummy worms.

title: pasta with lemon cream sauce
directions: Heat butter in heavy saucepan.
Add carrot strips and lemon rind.
Cook, stirring about 2 minutes.
Add wine.
Cook about 1 minute.
Add lemon juice.
Cook about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cream and bring to a boil.

title: caramel-biscuit ring-a-round
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Generously grease 12-cup fluted tube pan. Combine the first 4 ingredients; heat until margarine melts.

title: bacon-wrapped shrimp
directions: Thaw shrimp if frozen.
Place shrimp in plastic bag.
Set in bowl.

title: white sauce from mix
directions: In large bowl, combine dry milk, flour and salt, mixing well. With pastry blender, cut in butter or margarine until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Lightly pack into large, airtight container.
Store in refrigerator; use within 2 months.
Makes 1 quart mix, enough for 8 cups sauce.

title: arnold palmer's sugared bacon strips
directions: Roll, pat or shake raw bacon in brown sugar.
Place bacon strips in a flat pan with sides.
Bake at 300° until bacon is done, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove with tongs and drain on brown paper bags.
As it cools, bacon will get hard and can be broken into smaller pieces or served whole.

title: dorothy's church dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine; add cake mix and nuts. It will be lumpy; set aside.
Spread pie filling in a 9 x 9-inch Corningware dish.
Sprinkle on lemon juice.
Sprinkle cake mixture on top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until brown.

title: doritos chicken
directions: Place Doritos in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken pieces on top of Doritos.
Mix the chicken soup with Ro-Tel tomatoes and pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruity banana bread
directions: Coat an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan with cooking spray; set aside.
Beat margarine at medium speed with an electric mixer until margarine is creamy.
Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar, beating well.
Add egg substitute, beating until mixture is blended. Combine all-purpose flour and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture.
Beat at low speed until blended.
Stir in mashed bananas and dried fruit.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour until mixture is uniform and fairly coarse.
Stir in salt and milk; form into ball.
Chill.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out each half on floured surface.
Fit into 2 (9-inch) pie plates.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oven beef stroganoff
directions: Place meat, onion and mushrooms in appropriate size baking dish.
In separate bowl, stir together soup, Worcestershire, pepper and bouillon and pour over the meat.
Cover with foil. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until beef is tender.
Remove from oven, stir in sour cream.
Serve over warm, cooked noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix
Jell-O, syrup and sugar;
heat to a boiling point, but do not boil.
Cool and pour over popcorn.
Butter hands to make balls.

title: billy graham's fresh apple cake(a recipe we had fun serving because of the compliments)
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Mix well.
It is stiff.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serve with a sweet white sauce over the top or whipped cream.

title: cranberry and apple casserole
directions: Put apples, sugar and cranberries in buttered casserole dish. Mix oatmeal, brown sugar, flour, nuts and margarine.
Crumble over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Make white sauce with margarine, flour and milk and seasoning. Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add eggs and shrimp.
Mix lightly.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Garnish with additional egg slices and parsley. Makes 6 servings.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake cookies at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes. Baked cookies will be soft.
They will puff while baking and flatten while cooling.
Cool slightly, then remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: no guilt brown hot fudge sunday
directions: Mix brownie mix as directed on back, except use the same amount of applesauce that it directs for oil and use 2 egg whites in place of the whole egg.
Cook brownies and let cool.

Cut a piece of the brownie and top with 1/2 cup fat-free ice milk, 2 tablespoons Cool Whip, 2 tablespoons light hot fudge and a cherry. (The applesauce takes the fat out of the brownie mix, except for 2.5 grams in the mix.)
Tastes great, just as a brownie, too.

title: passover fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine with chocolate.
Let cool.
Beat eggs and salt until lemon colored.
Add sugar and cooled chocolate mixture.
Add cake meal, a little at a time, beating well.
Add nuts.
Pour into pan. Bake about 25 minutes.
Cut while hot.

title: angel food cake supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 375° (quick moderate).
Have egg whites at room temperature.
Sift an ample amount of Softasilk cake flour onto a square of paper.
Measure and sift together 3 times, cake flour and 7/8 cup sugar.
Measure into large bowl, remaining ingredients except sugar.
Beat with wire whip until foamy throughout.
Add gradually, 2 tablespoons at a time, 3/4 cup sugar.
Beat about 10 seconds after each addition.
Continue beating after the last addition until meringue is firm and holds stiff straight peaks when wire whip is gently lifted out of meringue (this requires considerable beating).
Place flour-sugar mixture in sifter and sift about 3 tablespoons over the entire surface of meringue.
Fold gently with wire whip or rubber scraper until flour-sugar mixture disappears using about 8 to 10 complete folding strokes and turning the bowl a quarter of a turn with each stroke.
Repeat this folding process until all of the flour and sugar is folded in.
Then scrape down the sides of the bowl with rubber scraper and fold 8 to 10 more strokes or until mixture is completely blended.
This mixture will be very thick.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook celery and onions until tender.
Break cornbread up into pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pan and be sure to have enough juice.
Add more if needed.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chili-sausage supper
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir meat, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender; drain off fat and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Add more water if necessary.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Cream cheese until smooth; add pineapple, onion, green pepper and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts and continue to mix.
Shape into ball and refrigerate overnight.
May roll in extra nuts before serving, if desired.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: lemon angel food cake
directions: Slice angel food cake in three layers.
Mix lemon juice and grated rind with milk.
Spread layers with lemon mixture.
Cover top and sides with lemon mixture.
Ice top and sides with cool whip.

title: homemade chicken salad
directions: Dice chicken, eggs, celery and onion.
Mix.
Add poultry seasoning.
Mix together.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix.
Add more mayonnaise if needed.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: christmas gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and molasses.
Stir dry ingredients together and add.
Chill.
Roll out not too thin.
Bake at 350° until dry, not crisp.
Makes enough dough for many shaped cookies.
Frost, if desired.

title: waldorf cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add liquid, then dry ingredients alternately, a little at a time.
Fold in 1 teaspoon vinegar and 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over all cereal and let cool.
Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add buttermilk and cooled bran mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Optional:
Add raisins that have been plumped in boiling water and drained.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together margarine or butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Combine both mixtures.
Crush Oreos.

title: dried apple or stack cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
(Add eggs one at a time.) Measure and sift dry ingredients; add to egg-sugar mixture alternately with milk.

title: oven fried chicken coating
directions: With wire whisk, beat eggs and milk so that all the whites are mixed in. Mix all dry ingredients together and pour into a 1/2-gallon paper or plastic bag. Moisten chicken with egg mixture. Put one piece at a time into the bag and shake until coated. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes or until juices are no longer pink when cut.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix and place in refrigerator several hours before using.
The child may eat it after finished playing with it.
Store remaining in refrigerator for several days.

title: steak supreme
directions: Heat lard in skillet.
Press meat into skillet to about 1-inch thickness.
Brown on both sides.
Add a can of mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Cover tightly; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Stir together sugar, oleo, cocoa and milk.
Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add oats, vanilla, peanut butter and raisins and/or coconut, if desired, to mixture while hot.
Drop on waxed paper or spread for squares.
Cool.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine in pan the sugar and 2 cups water.
Bring to a boil or until sugar is melted. Let cool. When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together. Stir well and freeze in a gallon container or 2 (2-quart) containers until slush forms, about 8 hours. Stir slush to mix well.
Serve from punch bowl or pour into cups and enjoy.

title: cucumber with laban
directions: Mint gives this summer salad a particularly refreshing taste. Break the laban curd with a spoon and stir until smooth. Combine with cucumbers.
Work garlic to a paste with salt and mix it with a spoonful of laban before adding to the cucumber mixture. Add mint.

title: reeses peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and peanut butter. Add sugar. Whip in chunks of frozen Cool Whip. Fold in chopped Reeses cups. Spoon into pie crusts and freeze. Thaw about 15 - 20 minutes before serving.

title: bacon poles
directions: Cut each slice bacon into 3 pieces.
Wrap around Twigs.
Cook in microwave for 4 to 5 minutes or until bacon is done.
Use microwave oblong dish with paper towel on bottom and top.
Roll in Parmesan cheese.
Will freeze well.

title: layered hamburger bake
directions: Cook noodles in a large amount of water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Brown meat in skillet; drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic salt, pepper, and the cooked noodles.
Set aside.
Stir together cream cheese, sour cream, milk, and onion.
In 2 qt. casserole, layer half of the beef-noodle mixture, half of the cream cheese mixture, all of the spinach, and remaining ground beef-noodle mixture.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Uncover and spread remaining cream cheese mixture on top.
Sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
Bake 10 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sugar cookies(heritage recipe)
directions: Cream powdered sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar before stirring in creamed mixture.
Roll out and cut as you wish.
Bake on greased pan at 375 degrees for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: feed 'em a lot cake
directions: Bake cake and cool.
Leave in pan and place each ingredient on cake as listed.
Scatter coconut on top.

title: cheesecake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and set aside.
Place a rack 1/3 of the way up from the bottom of oven.
Preheat oven to 350°. Beat cream cheese and butter until soft and smooth.
Beat in the vanilla, sugar and cornstarch until the batter is smooth.
Reduce to low speed and beat in eggs, one at a time, blending after each addition.
Add heavy cream while beating.
The mixture will be thin and smooth.
Beat in lemon juice.
Pour into prepared pan. Place that pan in a larger pan.
Into the larger pan, pour hot water to a depth of one inch.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in butter until tender (about 10 minutes).
Stir in seasonings, eggs and cheese.
Separate dough and place in a 10-inch pie plate.
Press dough over bottom and sides for crust.
Pour in vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: peppermint ice
directions: In microwave, melt vanilla bark

in a large bowl, checking and stirring each minute. Remove as soon as bark can be stirred smooth, vanilla bark burns easily. Crush the candy and stir into the melted bark. Add coloring. Spread thinly in largest baking sheet. Refrigerate. Break into pieces of various sizes and shapes. Store in refrigerator.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: After the red has been eaten, scrape out the pink down to the light pink color.
Peel off the rind and cut the other into strips, then into thinner strips.
Place in open pan with sugar (according to pear preserves recipe).
Cook until thickened into preserves. Spoon into jars while hot and seal.

title: layered salad
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch or larger bowl, layer in order given.
Cover and let stand 8 to 12 hours before serving.

title: coconut crunch cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, shortening and egg.
Add the dry ingredients to the mixture.
Add the vanilla, oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: turkey-delicious
directions: Put all in a pan and bring to boil.
Simmer so onion and celery cook some.
Thicken.
Serve over rice or potatoes.

title: tex-mix dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish, spread bean dip on bottom.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together and pour on top of bean dip.
Chop green onions on top of that. Next, spread chopped avocados. Sprinkle lemon juice on avocados.
Sprinkle black olives and ripe tomatoes. Cover with grated cheese and put sliced jalapeno on top.

title: venison or beef roast
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Batter in flour.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in frypan.
Brown roast on all sides.
Mix mushroom soup, onion soup and vermouth.

title: coconut lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure the flour and mix with butter and 1/4 cup brown sugar thoroughly.
Press firmly into bottom of lightly greased oblong pan (9 x 13-inches).
Bake for 10 minutes. Mix eggs, 2 cups brown sugar and salt together thoroughly.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Spread evenly over the partially baked bottom layer.
Bake about 25 minutes.
Top will be lightly browned.
Cut in 3 x 1-inch bars when cool.
Makes 28 bars.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Stir in sour milk. Sift all the dry ingredients.
Combine two mixtures, creating a cake batter.
Fold in 2 cups rhubarb.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and dot with butter.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: amish dressing
directions: Into large bowl put bread cubes, potatoes, parsley and carrots.
Add 6 eggs well beaten. Add 1 pt. or more of cooked diced chicken and mix in the dressing. Bake in a well buttered pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gold medal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine both sugars and butter until light and fluffy (about 5 minutes).
Add eggs and vanilla.
Scrape bottom and sides of bowl and mix to combine ingredients.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and wheat germ to the butter mixture.
Mix on low speed just until combined.
Hand stir/fold in nuts.
If you have parchment paper (not waxed paper), line cookie sheets.
Using a small cookie scoop, place them on a cookie sheet.
Bake for about 15 minutes. If baking two sheets at the same time, rotate 1/2 way through baking time.
Transfer to a cooling rack when done.

title: mixed bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in bacon fat.
Combine undrained beans, cooked onion and remaining ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: crumb cobbler
directions: Melt margarine. Pour in 1 can pie filling. Crumble 1 box of Jiffy cake mix on top, then repeat process. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until brown.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Pour flour, salt and pepper in bag and shake.
Add chicken and shake until well coated.
Melt Crisco in heavy skillet.
Add chicken and brown on all sides. Remove from heat and add water.
Cover with tight lid or foil, then bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: umpqua salmon chowder
directions: Combine water, onion, potatoes and celery.
Cover, simmer 20 minutes.
Add salmon and cook 10 minutes more

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water; add lemon juice.
Stir in berries; cool.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with cake. Cover with 1/2 of berry mixture.
Cover with topping.
Add another layer of berry mixture and cover with remaining topping. Refrigerate until set.

title: crunchy pops
directions: Peel the bananas. Then cut them in half.
Put an ice cream stick into the end of the bananas.
Put the pops in the freezer for an hour.
Take out the pops. Spread honey on each pop with a table knife.
Pour some rice cereal on the wooden board.
Roll each pop in the cereal.
Enjoy.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, chilies and Ro-Tel and set aside. Fry hamburger and onion; drain. In 13 x 9-inch pan, pour half of the sour cream. Break half of the tortillas on top of this. Put all hamburger and half of the cheese on top of this. Next, break up remaining tortillas, then put them, the rest of the sour cream mixture and remaining cheese on top of that. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cake that won't last
directions: Put all ingredients into a large mixing bowl and let set for 2 minutes. *Using a spoon only, mix well, but DO NOT BEAT! Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hungarian short ribs
directions: Brown ribs in 2 tablespoon oil, mix tomato sauce, mustard, worcestershire sauce, sugar, and vinegar.
Add 1 can water.
Pour over meat, add onions.
Simmer 2-2 1/2 hours.
Add one more cup of water and then noodles.
Cook 20 minutes more.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli, onion, celery and carrot in chicken broth until tender.
Add cream cheese, then add instant potatoes.
If it thickens too much add a little milk.

title: velvet pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Make sure milk is just warm.
Add a small amount of milk at a time, then a small amount of flour at a time, until you have used the milk and flour, beating well all the time.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole or baking dish. Salt and pepper pork chops and place on top of rice mixture. Cover tightly with foil and cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs. Stir in cocoa, flour, vanilla and salt.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool.
Spread marshmallow cream over cooled brownies.

title: zucchini apple pie
directions: Toss together zucchini, lemon juice and salt.
Cook until tender.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, cream of tartar, nutmeg and flour in a bowl.
Add the zucchini and mix well.
It will be runny.
Dump the filling into a 9-inch crust; dot with butter.
Add top crust and bake at 400° for 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chocolate covered strawberries
directions: Wash strawberries.
Pat thoroughly dry.
Allow to stand at room temperature for 2 hours.
Leave stems and leaves intact.
Melt chocolate chips with shortening over a double boiler.
Holding strawberries by the stem, dip 3/4 into chocolate coating all around.
Allow to drip and place on a plate covered with wax paper. Place in refrigerator to cool.
May be done 2 to 3 hours in advance.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples in a 9-inch buttered pie plate or 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Combine sugar, flour, oats and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Press mixture over apples.
Bake in moderate 350° oven 45 to 50 minutes or until top is brown. Chopped pecans can be added to topping.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: paella #1
directions: Place mussels in large bowl.
Add enough cold water to cover. Add cornmeal and salt.
Cover and refrigerate overnight; drain well.
Rinse and drain again.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls in pizza pan.
Add cooked, crumbled sausage, hash browns and cheese.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over the top.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
May be frozen and heated in microwave.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter for 15 to 20 minutes until clear.
Stir in milk. Put half of onion mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with half of crackers and sprinkle half the cheese over cracker crumbs.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in large rectangle pan.
As soon as cake is removed from oven, punch holes throughout surface of cake with a fork.
Pour soda over cake slowly so it will seep through.
Pour jello mixture over cake in the same manner.
Set in refrigerator to cool.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip. Spread mixture over cake and return cake to refrigerator.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: carob or chocolate sauce
directions: Mix together in saucepan the first 3 ingredients.
Stir in gradually the boiling water.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla; stir until blended.
Serve warm.
Excellent over ice cream.

title: green bean and bacon casserole
directions: Fry bacon in skillet.
Remove and crumble and set aside.
Add bread cubes to bacon drippings.
Stir.
Cook on medium heat 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Combine beans, bacon and soup in 1-quart casserole.
Mix well.
Top with bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili(nebraska style)
directions: Brown ground beef together with onion and bell pepper.
Drain any fat.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil and simmer for 1 hour.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind	vegetables
and
drain.
Add
salt,
sugar
and vinegar.
Cook
10 minutes after it starts boiling.
Add salad dressing and
mustard.
Seal in jars.
Put in cold pack canner or pressure cooker for 5 minutes to get jars to seal.	You may use all green pepper or add more hot, if you want it real hot. Good as a dip, too.

title: rich coconut pie
directions: Cook sugar and Karo until it spins a thread.
Pour over beaten eggs and melted oleo.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hash browns and ham casserole
directions: Mix everything together, except oleo, cornflakes and Mozzarella cheese.
Put into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix oleo and cornflakes together.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake for another 20 to 25 minutes.

title: orange pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour and salt; cut in Crisco with pastry blender or two knives until mixture is uniform (mixture should be fairly coarse).
Sprinkle with water, a tablespoon at a time; toss lightly with fork.
Work dough into firm ball.
Roll out floured surface to a circle 1/8 inch thick and about 1 1/2 inches larger than inverted pie plate.
Ease dough into pie plate.
Fold under rim to make double thickness.
Trim and flute edge.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut shortening in with cutter or knives.
Add yeast.
Add milk gradually.
Mix well and roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter or roll and shape by hand.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: stir-fry
directions: Chop meat and vegetables.
Set aside.
Heat wok or frypan. Add oil.
Add chopped carrots and onion and stir for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining vegetables.
Stir until they are tender but do not overcook.
Push vegetables to the side.
Add meat, ginger, pepper and soy sauce.
Stir until done.
Stir meat and vegetables together.
Serve with brown rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet-sour beef stew
directions: Brown meat in hot oil.
Add next 6 ingredients, 1/2 cup water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cover and cook over low heat until meat is tender, about 2 hours.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water; add to beef mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Serve over noodles.

title: good rice casserole
directions: Brown rice in oleo.
Add hot broth.
Combine well.
