Place in covered Pam sprayed casserole dish (9 x 13-inch) and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Add onion; mix together.
Cover and cook 30 minutes more.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Grease a baking dish.
Mix ingredients and turn into the dish. Cover with buttered crumbs and cook until brown and heated through.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "heavenly" chocolate
directions: Bake brownies as directed on package.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Place one layer of brownies in a deep glass dish. Sprinkle with crushed candy bar; top with chocolate pudding and then Cool Whip.
Continue layering until all ingredients are used. Keep refrigerated.

title: oven stew
directions: Place vegetables, meat and seasoning in large Dutch oven or roasting pan.
Sprinkle tapioca on top and pour V-8 juice over the top.
Bake at 350° for 3 1/2 hours.
Stir a couple of times.
If juice is drying up, add more V-8 juice.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; add sugar.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
In morning, add grapes and pecans.
Combine whipping cream.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Heat oil in 4 quart pot.
Add onion, garlic, carrots and celery.
Saute until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes with liquid breaking up tomatoes.
Stir in broth and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in beans and cabbage; simmer 10 minutes longer.
Stir in zucchini and macaroni.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 (2 cup) servings.

title: turkey cashew casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add soup and broth.
Season with pepper.
Add turkey and mushrooms.
Simmer for a few minutes. Pour into a one-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with noodles and cashews.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until it bubbles.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook pasta.
Combine all other ingredients and heat.
Mix together.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients except chips and cheese. Spoon into 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle chips and cheese on top. Bake at 390° for 30 minutes.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and add Crisco, sugar and beaten egg. Now add 4 cups flour (don't add anymore).
This dough will seem thin.
Put into the refrigerator for a short while and it will thicken.
When you are ready to use them, take from refrigerator and put 3 small balls of dough to make cloverleaf rolls into greased muffin pans.
If too thin to form balls, take spoon and dip into each muffin pan.

title: punch
directions: Mix juices together.
Add ice and sherbet and top with balls of sherbet.

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in water with salt to season; cook until tender but not mushy.
Mix cheese soup and tomatoes.
Put drained potatoes in casserole dish and pour cheese-tomato mixture over them.
Heat in oven until bubbly.

title: hawaiian fruit flowerpot
directions: Mold Jell-O into shape of flowerpot and place on salad plate. Place 3 slices of banana above pot and arrange papaya, pineapple, melon and lettuce curls.
Place shredded coconut on lime Jell-O and add touches of maraschino cherries on both the pot and fruit arrangement.
Add Cool Whip touches in several places on the fruit.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco.
Sift flour once and measure. Sift measured flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder together.
Add eggs one at a time to creamed mixture.
Add flour alternating with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour in a greased and floured tube pan.
Cook 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
Turn off oven and let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Frost cake, if desired.

title: brownies--the best
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and beat until blended.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (do not overbake).
Cool and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut stems; remove seeds from peppers.
Parboil peppers for 2 minutes and drop into cold water.
Combine tomatoes and meat with enough crumbs to make a thick stuffing.
Heat stuffing in frying pan with oil and butter.
Season to taste.
Fill peppers and put into pan just large enough to hold them upright.
Pour in 1 cup hot water and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dream rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease muffin tins.
Put mixture in tins.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 12.

title: ginger snaps
directions: Combine crisco, sugar, and egg in mixing bowl, beat until fluffy. Add molasses and beat well.

Sift dry ingredients together, add to sugar mixture and mix well. Chill dough until easily handled. Shape into 1 in. balls. Roll in sugar; place 2 in. apart on grease cookie sheet. Bake 12-15 min at 350°. Yield 4 doz.

title: broccoli vegetable casserole
directions: Toss croutons with butter and set aside.
Cook broccoli 1/2 done.
Leave a little crisp, drain.
Combine soup and cheese until cheese is melted.
Stir in broccoli.
Put in baking dish and cover with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbling.

title: salsa
directions: In a food processor, chop tomatoes separate, then add chopped onions.
You can add more jalapeno peppers if you like it hot. Mix all other ingredients together with chopped vegetables.
Store in a glass jar.

title: leita rose's velvety egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly; add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Heat milk to boiling point.
Slowly add hot milk to egg mixture, stirring constantly and blending well.
Bake pie shell for a few minutes before filling.
Leave pie crust on oven rack while filling. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes, reduce heat to 425° and continue baking for 10 minutes.

title: 3 bean salad bowl
directions: Cook green and wax beans as package labels direct.
Drain; let cool.
In large salad bowl, lightly toss with kidney beans, onion and green pepper.
In jar shake oil, vinegar, Worcestershire, sugar, garlic, salt and pepper until well mixed.
Discard garlic. Pour dressing over beans; mix to coat well.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Serve on salad greens.

title: rice pudding
directions: In mixing bowl, beat the eggs and add sugar, salt, vanilla and nutmeg.
Mix well and add scalded milk and stir well.
Place the rice in a 2-quart baking dish. Pour the egg mixture over rice and stir to blend.
Place the baking dish in a cake or similar pan and pour 1-inch or less of hot water in the larger pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pistachio pie
directions: Beat together pudding mix and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add nuts.
Put into pie shell.
Freeze 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with chopped nuts on top.

title: outstanding oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, vanilla and egg in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: rave reviews coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding, water and eggs; add oil in large mixer bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in coconut and walnuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.
Fill and top with coconut-cream cheese frosting.

title: vegetable-cheese bake
directions: In a saucepan combine frozen vegetables and boiling water. Bring to a boil again.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain well. Meanwhile, melt butter in a sauce pan.
Blend in flour; cook for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk.
Simmer, stirring, until smooth and thickened.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Mix in vegetables, onions and pimento.
Spread into buttered 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Good served with baked ham or pork chops.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add flour and oatmeal, one cup at a time, mixing after each addition.
Add raisins, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for about 13 minutes.
Cool well before storing.

title: louisiana pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil for one minute. Pour about half of this mixture over the baked cake; return to oven for 30 minutes.
Remove cake from oven.
Turn out on cooling rack with cookie sheet underneath.
Pour remaining half of glaze over cake, catching unused in pan beneath.
Use this to reglaze. Continue until glaze is used completely up.
Allow to cool completely before placing on serving plate.
Serve plain or with a dollop of ice cream.
Gets rave notices all the time.

title: mr. jackson's barbecue sauce
directions: This
sauce
is
for
large
amount
of
barbecue.
Mr. Jackson used to cook barbecue for quite a few dinners, and was on special request for really important barbecue events.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix coffee, baking soda and chopped dates and let stand.
Mix sugar, butter, egg, nuts, flour, salt and vanilla altogether and mix with coffee/date mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured loaf pan.

title: mystery pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Add nuts and pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.
This recipe makes two pies.

title: quick casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cocktail wieners 1
directions: Heat the jelly and mustard until dissolved.
Cut wieners into thirds and add to sauce.
Pour into chafing dish to serve.
(Beef wieners hold their shape better.)

title: banana waffles
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, lemon rind and salt in a large bowl. Beat egg yolks, milk, melted butter and mashed bananas together in a bowl.
Add all at once to dry mixture; stir just enough to moisten.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; fold into batter.
Let batter stand for 5 to 10 minutes to develop banana flavor.
Bake in waffle iron according to manufacturer's directions.
Serve with Apricot-Banana Sauce.
Yields 4 large waffles.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar in a large bowl and let stand 10 minutes.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend into the apple-sugar mixture the oil and egg, then add dry ingredients, stirring until just blended.
Fold in raisins and walnuts.
Spread evenly in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Mix together all ingredients with fork or pastry blender until consistency of cornmeal.
Add just enough milk to mix.
Divide into 8 balls of dough.
Roll out each and fill with 2 tablespoons apple butter.
Fold over and seal edges by pressing with fork. Fry in Crisco and butter until brown.

title: graham cracker pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites, baking powder, vanilla and sugar until stiff. Fold in graham cracker crumbs and pecans.
Spread mixture in a 9-inch buttered pie plate.
Bake for 25 minutes (no longer) at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream, sweetened with vanilla and sugar. Easiest to spoon out of pie plate rather than cutting pie-shaped wedges.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water for 5 minutes.
Cook pie filling with 1 3/4 cups water, sugar and egg yolks.
When thick add gelatin and cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites and pineapple.
Spread over graham cracker mixture.
Chill.
Serve with topping or ice cream.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in a 3 or 4-quart saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat; allow to cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg. Beat well.
Sift together the flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add these to first mixture.
Mix well and chill thoroughly.
Form in 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute diced celery, onion and green onions.
In a large bowl, mix diced chicken, pimentos, mushrooms and mayonnaise together. Add sauteed vegetables and toss thoroughly.
Line baking dish with squares of buttered bread.
Spread half of the mixture over toasted bread squares.
Top the chicken mixture with buttered toasted bread squares.
Place rest of chicken mixture on toasted squares.
Beat eggs, then slowly add milk; blend well.
Pour egg/milk mixture over the top of casserole.
Spread mushroom soup over all.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top; bake 45 minutes at 325° or until cheese is bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Let sugar and apples stand 30 minutes.
Bake in 8-inch square pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool ten minutes.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Do not overbeat.
Pour 1/2 of the batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Pour 1 can of blueberry pie filling (or other flavor) over batter.
Pour other 1/2 of batter on blueberries.
Mix 6 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle on top of cake.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: unbaked tart shells
directions: Combine confectioners sugar, wafer crumbs, ground almonds and cocoa in a bowl.
Sprinkle in milk, mixing until ingredients are moistened and cling together.
Shape into walnut size pieces.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla.
Stir continuously with a wire whisk over medium heat until slightly thick. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Serve hot over biscuits.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Layer turkey in 9 x 13-inch sprayed pan.
Pour soup over turkey.
Add layer of peas and small onions.
Cover with layer of stuffing mix.
Heat milk and oleo and pour over top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon applesauce jello(kids love this!)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and red hots in 1 cup boiling water; add another cup boiling water until candies completely dissolve. Place in refrigerator to cool.
Add applesauce and stir right before Jell-O has set.
Do not put in a mold.
Refrigerate in serving bowl.
Can add whipped cream or decorate top, if desired.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and set aside.
In a large skillet, or wok, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium heat.
Add vegetables and garlic.
Stir-fry 3 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Remove from skillet.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil.
Add chicken; stir-fry for 4 minutes.
Return vegetables to skillet.
Stir broth mixture and add to skillet.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings; 210 calories per serving.

title: lobster newberg
directions: Use double boiler.
Gradually add cream to finely mashed egg yolks.
Melt butter in double boiler and add flour.
Add cream gradually and stir to boiling point but do not boil.
Add egg yolks and lobster.
Keep over hot water until thoroughly heated. Add sherry, salt and pepper.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter and milk over low heat.
In a large bowl, combine nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Spread in wax paper lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours.

title: beefwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sliced onion, tomato and relish.
Shape into 8 flat beef patties.
On half of patties, place the sliced onion, tomato and 2 tablespoons relish.
Put another beef patty on top and seal meat around edges.
Place on broiler pan.
Broil for 6 minutes on each side.
Makes 4 Beefwiches.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Roll into 1 inch balls.
Put 1/2 cherry on top and bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Makes 5 dozen.

title: jennifer's mood maker mimosa
directions: Mix cold orange juice and champagne together.
Pour into stemmed glasses and serve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn.
Dice tomatoes and onion.
Mix.
Add garlic salt and black pepper.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Great with fish.

title: pineapple chicken(po lo chi)
directions: Dredge chicken pieces in mixture made of the cornstarch, salt, water and soy sauce. Set aside.

Saute the onions, celery and water chestnuts in oil. Vegetables should be crisp, not cooked soft. Remove from pan. Saute the chicken until brown. Add the vegetables, pineapple and the juice to the chicken and simmer until thoroughly heated.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 to 6 portions.

title: green bean and artichoke casserole
directions: Add bread crumbs, cheese and garlic powder in a bowl.
Save juice from artichokes.
Slice artichokes and place in casserole. Place beans on top, then add bread crumb mixture.
Continue to make layers.
Add liquid (combine juice with olive oil).
Place in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cranberry squares
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine melted oleo with well beaten eggs.
Add sugar, flour, nuts and cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 48 to 50 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: pineapple-coconut cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, butter and sugar; beat in egg. Stir in pineapple. Cover and chill for 2 hours. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pineapple-apricot cream cheese tart
directions: Prepare crust as package directs.
Center crust in a 9-inch removable bottom tart pan, pressing firmly against bottom and sides of pan.
Fold down edge; prick with fork.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.
In a 1-quart saucepan, bring 1 1/2 cups water to boil.
Add apricots.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes; drain and cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix and bake in 2 loaf pans for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325° or 350°, depending on your oven.

title: cheryl's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well on medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Slowly add flour.
Add eggs.
Chill overnight.
Roll thin and brush with egg white.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Cut with desired cookie cutter.
Press nut on top.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sterling's chili rice
directions: In a large skillet or deep chicken fryer, heat to medium the bacon fat.
Add meat and garlic.
Cook this until red color disappears from meat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 2 hours.
Add more water as needed.

title: sister mabel's caramel corn
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil, stirring and cooking about 5 minutes or until mixture reaches 260° or hard ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda quickly and thoroughly. Pour at once over popped corn in large roasting pan.
Stir until all kernels are coated.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring 3 times during baking.
Turn on wax paper or towel and allow to cool. Store in tight container.

title: raspberry fudge balls
directions: Combine cream cheese and chocolate, mixing until well blended. Stir in crumbs and preserves.
Chill several hours or overnight. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in almonds.

title: "my they're good, how did you make them" brownies
directions: Mix according to package directions.
Add chocolate chips and bake as directed.

title: butterscotch pecan dessert
directions: In a bowl, cut the margarine into the flour until crumbly; stir in 1/2 cup pecans.
Press into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Coat the beef and brown in hot fat.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add rest of ingredients except potatoes and carrots.
Cover and simmer 2 hours. Then add potatoes and carrots and cook until vegetables are done, about 45 minutes.
This is a spicy dish!

title: low-fat peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar and eggs, then add peanut butter and vanilla. Stir in flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Roll rounded tablespoonfuls into balls, then crisscross with fork dipped in flour or powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
48 cookies, 2.2 g. fat each.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil butter, cream and sugar for 7 minutes on medium heat. Remove from heat and stir in marshmallow cream, peanut butter and nuts.
Stir until thick.
Spread in large pan.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Refrigerate overnight if possible.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: cola ribs
directions: In small bowl, combine the salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Rub mixture over the surface of the ribs.
In a large pot or Dutch oven, heat the oil over medium-high heat and brown the ribs on all sides.

title: pizza crust
directions: Measure water into bowl.
Sprinkle with yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in sugar, salt and olive oil.
Add 2 cups of the flour and beat until smooth, then add as much of the remaining flour as needed (about 1/2 cup) to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a floured board and knead until smooth.
(Use the rest of the flour for this.)
Place dough in a large, greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk.
Makes 2 pizza crusts.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Put tomatoes in a pot and bring to a boil.
Add butter, sugar, salt, cinnamon
flavor.
Cook
over
a
low fire for 10 minutes. Mix flour
and water; make a smooth mixture.
Add to the tomatoes, stirring
occasionally.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice and water until rice is tender.
Let cool about 10 minutes.

title: quick spice potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes; dot with butter and season with spices to taste.
Bake at 500° until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Slice and peel apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl and beat at medium speed for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: freda's chocolate pie
directions: Prepare crusts.
Bake and let cool.
Heat milk with beaten egg yolks.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir into milk.
Stir constantly.
When thick, add margarine and remove from heat.
Stir well.
Let cool and pour into pie shells.
Prepare meringue and brown.

title: chocolatetown chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and baking chips.

title: braunschweiger dip 1
directions: Blend well.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Very good on snack crackers.

title: gourmet meat balls
directions: Mix well and shape into meat balls.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cora belle's chicken tetrazzini
directions: Sear in butter the onion, bell pepper and celery.
In a casserole, layer spaghetti, chicken, soup and seared ingredients. Cook 30 minutes at 375°.
Then sprinkle with cheese and brown.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
In separate pan, warm cans of soup (do not add water).
Add tomatoes and cheese.
Blend until cheese is melted.
Add hamburger and mix.
Pour over 1/2 bag of Doritos in baking dish.
Bake approximately 10 minutes at 350° until bubbling hot.
Serve with rest of chips.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar together.
Melt margarine and peanut butter together, then mix with crackers and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1 package chocolate chips on top.
Put under broiler just long enough for chocolate to melt, then spread evenly over top.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: bell pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions fine.
Mix ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: breaded cubed steaks
directions: Dip steaks in beaten eggs and then coat with bread crumbs. Fry in Wesson oil on medium heat until done.
Drain well.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Make graham cracker crust in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cheese and powdered sugar in large bowl.
Whip cream in small bowl.
Fold whipped cream into cheese mixture.
Pour over crust.
Add pie filling to top and refrigerate.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beef, onion and crushed bacon in small amount of shortening in skillet.
Stir until lightly browned.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole and bake at 325° until bubbly hot.

title: fruit icy
directions: Mix first five ingredients in a blender until evenly crushed. Add fruit; mix until blended.
Fill glasses.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Saut onion in oil until tender. Remove from pan and set aside. Brown meat and drain. Add salt, pepper, Accent, soup and
onion to meat and stir. Pour into baking dish. Spoon green beans over top of meat, then top with potatoes. Bake about 40 minutes.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Divide mixture into 8 portions; shape into croquettes.
Roll in cracker crumbs. Place on a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan; cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Combine butter and paprika; drizzle over croquettes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden.
Garnish croquettes with chives, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese along bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown ground beef and add taco seasoning mix according to package directions.
Spread taco meat mixture over cream cheese.
Pour salsa over ground beef and spread evenly.
Top with grated cheese. Just before serving, bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until cream cheese is softened.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: hawaiian style pork chops
directions: Salt and roll chops in flour.
Brown in hot oil. Combine vinegar, ketchup and juice; pour over chops.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Garnish with pineapple.

title: mint patties
directions: Thoroughly blend butter, corn syrup, extract and salt.
Add sugar; mix with spoon and hands until blended smooth.
Divide mixture into thirds; knead desired food colorings into two portions.
Leave one white.
Shape into small round balls; flatten with tines of fork onto waxed paper-lined baking sheets.
Let dry several hours.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: gooey cheesecake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread in bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the cream cheese; beat in eggs, then sweetened condensed milk and vanilla. Spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned and set.
Mixture will thicken upon cooling.

title: lemon lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add 1 cup cold water; set aside and cool.
Add pineapple, milk, cottage cheese and nuts. Stir often until set.

title: norbert's favorite orange rice and chicken
directions: Combine water, orange juice, onion, butter, pecans and salt in 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Add rice and mix well.
Coat chicken with Shake 'n Bake as directed on package and arrange over rice mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands. Spoon won't work as well! Put into freezer safe dish. Pack down real good.
Put in refrigerator.

title: swiss steak
directions: Place steak in deep Pyrex dish.
Cover with lemon juice. Alternate layers of potatoes and onions; top with tomatoes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Top with lemon slices, if desired.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Use broth from chicken.
Make dumplings with flour, egg and hot water.
Drop by teaspoon into chicken broth.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: fajita in a pita
directions: Combine salad dressing and soy sauce in a 1-quart casserole. Add chicken. Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade, reserving marinade.
Grill chicken, covered, over medium-hot coals for 5 minutes on each side.
Cut chicken into strips and keep warm.

title: lemon lush
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, walnuts and flour together. Spread on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake for 15 minutes. Mix together the lemon pudding mix and milk.
Fold in cream cheese and one-half of the Cool Whip.
Pour over walnut crust and top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: butter baked rice
directions: Boil water with salt and pour over rice.
Let soak 30 minutes. Drain water.
Melt butter in saucepan on medium heat.
Add rice and cook until butter is almost absorbed (about 5 minutes).
Place in baking dish with lid.
Sprinkle with garlic and seasoned salt.
Add chicken broth.
Sprinkle parsley.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes at 325°.
Fluff with fork.
Add slivered almonds and cook 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: spinach nuggets
directions: Place frozen spinach and dried onion in a 1 1/2-quart casserole with water.
Cook, covered, in a microwave on High for 9 to 11 minutes, stirring once.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Drain well. In the same casserole, stir together hot spinach mixture and butter or margarine until butter melts.
Add stuffing mix and Parmesan cheese.
Stir in eggs.
To make shaping the spinach mixture easy, drop small mounds onto a baking sheet lined with wax paper.
Freeze about 10 minutes to firm up the mixture; then shape the mounds into 1-inch balls.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Top with Ritz crackers mixed with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange  slush
directions: Peel, quarter and seed orange. Put in blender and blend well.

title: seven layer bean dip
directions: Mix beans with salsa.
Top with small layer of cheese.
Spread sour cream on top.
Add sliced olives on top, then more shredded cheese.
Top with sliced green onions and chopped tomatoes.

title: toasted cheese rounds
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on rye bread rounds.
Broil until golden brown and puffy.
Serve immediately.
Makes 20.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Mix thoroughly on medium speed with mixer.
Spread in a greased 8-inch square dish.
Microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: vongali siciliano
directions: Scrub clams with stiff brush; rinse in running water until all sand is removed.
Place garlic, oil and parsley in large pot. Heat 3 minutes; add water, a little salt, pepper to taste and clams.
Cover.
Steam over medium heat about 20 minutes or until shells open.
Place clams in deep plates.
Serve hot with clam broth.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, strawberries, oil and pecans.
Stir until all are moistened.
Grease two loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch) or three small ones.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: chocolate almond brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and butter; cook and stir until the sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking without stirring to 300° on the candy thermometer.
When the syrup makes hard brittle threads, remove from heat.
Melt into it, stirring very rapidly, the chocolate, vanilla, soda and almonds.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
When cool enough to handle, pull the edges to thin it and overlap it on a second greased cookie sheet.
When cold, break into pieces.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds of candy.

title: easy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In a cake pan, melt butter.
Mix in sugar. Top with pineapple. Spoon prepared cake mix over pineapple and bake as directed. Serve hot or cold.

title: 1 minute fudge frosting
directions: Place ingredients into saucepan.
Bring slowly to full rolling boil.
Stir constantly and boil 1 minute.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until thick enough to spread.
If frosting becomes too thick, add approximately 1 tablespoon cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding mix together. Don't drain pineapple. Mix together until pineapple are covered with pudding mix. Stir in Cool Whip, marshmallows and pecans. Makes 1 medium bowl. For large bowl, double ingredients.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix the meat, cheese, bread crumbs, eggs and seasonings. Season to taste.
When mixing all together, add cold water, approximately 1/4 cup.
Mix well and form into balls.
Grease large baking pan with olive oil.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: smokey clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon until crisp and brown; remove to paper towel. Drain and set aside.
Spoon 2 tablespoons drippings in heavy saucepan.
Saute onion and celery in bacon drippings for 5 minutes or until softened.
Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Set clams aside.
Add clam liquid, water and potatoes in saucepan.
Bring to boiling, cover and boil gently about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Crumble drained bacon; reserve.
Stir together 1/4 cup of the milk and flour in a small bowl until smooth.
Stir into saucepan with remaining 1 3/4 cups milk and the half and half. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in reserved clams, salt and pepper.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Ladle into heated soup bowls.
Sprinkle with bacon and parsley.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: another low-fat brownie
directions: In a large bowl, mix margarine, sugar and vanilla.
In smaller bowl, mix flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Pour second bowl into large bowl.
Fold in egg whites.
Spray an 8-inch pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 280° for 45 minutes.

title: tex mix(cow patty)
directions: First Layer:
Mix first 3 ingredients and spread on a large plate.

title: unfried fries
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Toss potatoes with cayenne and oil. Spray baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Place potatoes in baking sheet and bake 40 minutes, turning once.
Sprinkle with parsley, garlic and salt.
Toss.
Bake 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: maple-potato-apple casserole
directions: *If fresh sweet potatoes or yams are not available, use 1 large can.

title: giant raisin bran cookies
directions: Stir together Raisin Bran cereal, flour and soda.
Set aside.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini noodles.
Cut tops off broccoli and cut broccoli and green onions into small pieces.
Mix vegetables and noodles together.
Pour Italian dressing on top.
Add salt and pepper. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; chill 1 hour.
Before serving, add more Italian dressing.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add Bisquick and mix well. Chill at least one hour.
Stir in peanut butter chips and shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: scooter's chili dip
directions: Saute the meat in just enough fat to cover the bottom of the skillet.
When meat is browned, add the rest of the fat and the flour.
Add heated consomme, stirring.
Simmer for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Increase heat and stir continually until mixture thickens.
Place mixture in the top of double boiler, add cheese in small chunks, stirring until melted.
Serve in a chafing dish with Fritos or tortillas.
Serves 25 to 30.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, cheese, onion and salt and pepper. Add potatoes and mix well.	Pour into buttered 9 x 13 baking dish.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Boil eggs.
Chop up all other ingredients in big bowl.
Add eggs and macaroni; stir well.

title: dressing for cucumbers
directions: Mix well and pour over sliced cucumbers. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring oleo, sugar and syrup to a boil.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Pour Special K into a large bowl, add syrup mixture and stir well.
Spread mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan or an 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over bars.

title: delicious drumsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper in bowl or Ziploc bag.
Dip drumsticks into margarine and coat thoroughly; roll in flour mixture or shake in bag to coat. Arrange in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, until done, about 50 minutes.

title: strawberry-cheese salad
directions: Combine in a bowl the strawberry gelatin and boiling water. Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add pineapple and banana.
Mix until blended.
Spoon half of gelatin mixture into 8-inch square pan at room temperature.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream and walnuts.
Mix well until blended.
Spread evenly over set gelatin. Pour remaining gelatin mixture over cheese mixture.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares and serve on crisp lettuce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Sift together cinnamon, flour and baking soda; add sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Mix in pineapple, walnuts, carrots and half of coconut.
Mix well; pour in baking dish that has been greased and dusted with flour.
Sprinkle the rest of the coconut on top of cake.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Turn down to 350° and continue baking for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: papa's potato soup
directions: Peel 7 medium sized potatoes.
Slice and boil.
Add one quart water for soup.
Slice one large onion; put in with potatoes to boil.
When cooked done, add 3 to 4 slices of cheese (break off in chunks).
Add one can of evaporated milk.
Add salt and pepper. Beat with hand mixer until soupy.

title: holiday beef
directions: Salt and pepper on eye of the round roast (any size you wish). Wrap in heavy foil.
Seal carefully and rewrap again.
Roast 3 hours at 350°.
Undo foil, jab holes in meat and pour the sauce over all and roll meat thoroughly in sauce.
Re-wrap roast.
Cook for another hour with sauce.
Good hot or cold.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: In a large skillet, melt 1 tablespoon margarine and add sliced celery and onion.
Saute until tender but not brown.
Combine the soup and water, mixing well.
Add this to skillet and stir.
Add drained tuna, cashews and 1 cup of chow mein noodles and toss lightly.
Put in ungreased casserole.
Put remaining 1 cup noodles on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and garnish with mandarin oranges.

title: del crest dip
directions: Mix cheeses.
Top with chopped pecans, or form cheese into ball and roll in pecans.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° until firm, approximately 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool at least 1 hour.
(Top usually cracks.)
If nuts are desired place on top of pie before baking.

title: mocha white cake
directions: Make cake as directed, except stir 2 tablespoons powdered instant coffee into mix before adding water.
Ice with Mocha Butter Icing (following).

title: hot asparagus roll-ups
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Flatten bread.
Blend cream cheese and bacon.
Spread mixture on bread.
Lay asparagus on each slice and roll up.
Brush with butter and place under broiler until golden brown.
Toast on both sides.
Cut in half for smaller pieces.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of two loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch) or 3 loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Mix sugar and shortening in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Stir in zucchini, water and eggs. Mix in flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves, vanilla and baking powder.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into pans.
Bake until wooden picks inserted comes out clean.
Bake 60 or 70 minutes.
If you don't have zucchini, you can use pumpkin and fix the same way.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Dump in pie filling, pineapple and juice.
Add cake mix; spoon melted butter on top.
Sprinkle coconut top; add chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven hash browns(add ham pieces for casserole.)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use 1 cup crushed chips or cornflakes for topping.
Bake in an 11 x 17-inch dish for 1 hour at 375°.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Cook wild rice.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.

title: light chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Add enough milk to make spreadable.

title: chicken and mushroom casserole
directions: Add all ingredients in large saucepan.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish and top with Confetti Biscuits (recipe in Breads, Rolls & Pastries Section).

title: cold watercress soup
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes in 2 quarts of water.
Add onion to water and potatoes.
Add watercress and bouillon cubes; boil up for about 5 minutes.
Puree in blender or food processor until smooth.
Chill.
Serve cold with a dollop of sweet cream and a shake of dried dill.

title: pecan pie(my husband's favorite)
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in pecans.
I put a design of pecan halves on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Serves 8 or 1.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Unroll the Pillsbury dough evenly onto a 11 x 17-inch ungreased cookie sheet.
(You can use two smaller baking pans.) Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove crust from oven and cool completely.

title: orange glazed pumpkin cake
directions: Beat sugar and Crisco until fluffy.
Mix in pumpkin, eggs and water.
Combine all other ingredients, mixing well, then add to sugar and Crisco mixture.
Pour into tube or Bundt pan that has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until wooden pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and completely cool on wire rack.
Drizzle glaze over cake.

title: one dish chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Mix stuffing and 1/2 cup of boiling water; spoon dressing across center of a 3-quart shallow baking dish.
Place chicken on each side of stuffing.
Sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Mix soup, parsley and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.

title: my sister-in-law mary's ice cream cake
directions: Melt vanilla ice cream.
Mix with frozen pink lemonade concentrate.
Slice a chiffon cake into 3 layers.
Spread ice cream mixture onto bottom layer and onto middle layer.
Put together; freeze on a plate wrapped in aluminum foil.
Serve when needed with whipped cream and crushed pineapple on sides and top.

title: manhatten meat balls
directions: Mix together all of the ingredients except the apricot preserves and barbecue sauce.
Roll the meat mixture into walnut size balls and fry in butter.
Drain.
Heat together the preserves and barbecue sauce.
Serve.

title: brownies
directions: Put all the ingredients together and mix it together; then pour in a greased baking sheet.
Put in oven at 350° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine 1/4 cup margarine with the next 5 ingredients, mashing well.
Place in a 9-inch square casserole.
Combine the rest of ingredients, including remaining 1/2 cup margarine.
Pour over sweet potato mixture.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Beat egg and add to creamed mixture.
Combine dry ingredients.
Next dissolve 2 teaspoons baking soda in 1/4 cup boiling water.
(This will foam up.)
Add applesauce and dry ingredients to creamed mixture, then add boiling water and baking soda to mixture and stir in well. Pour batter into greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter and chocolate in small saucepan and melt, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture into a small bowl; add sugar, flour, milk, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Beat mixture at moderate speed 5-7 minutes until thick and creamy (scrape bowl occasionally with spatula).
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake 40-45 minutes until filling is firm.

title: bean dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together and put in a 8 x 8 baking dish. Bake at 325 degrees until bubbly.

title: canned soup
directions: Combine soup and water in 1-quart ovenware casserole.
Cover and cook in microwave for 3 to 4 minutes or until hot.
Recipe makes 2 servings.

title: texas-style chili
directions: This recipe is moderately hot.
Cut back on chili powder if you like very mild chili.

title: brisket roast
directions: Combine onion, celery and garlic salts with liquid smoke. Pour over roast and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Bake in slow oven (250°) 4 to 5 hours.
Let cool and slice thin.
Add your favorite barbecue sauce and bake 1 hour.

title: easy choice baked chicken
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch baking pan with Pam.
Line bottom with chicken.
Cut cheese slices.
Place on top of chicken.
Pour soup on top of chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing over soup.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Delicious! Serves 4.

title: chicken creole
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan.
Saute chopped onions and bell peppers in fat.
Add other ingredients.
Let cook until thick, adding a little flour if needed.
After mixture thickens, add peas and mushroom soup and bacon broken into small pieces.
Let simmer 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and english peas
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender.
Drain well.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese, salt, pepper, eggs and chopped onion while broccoli is draining.
In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, place half the broccoli; over this layer place all of the peas and water chestnuts.
Pour half of soup mixture over the peas and then add the remaining broccoli.
Finish with soup mixture.
Top with cracker crumbs and drizzle butter over the crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Brown the onions in 1/2 stick of butter.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter for the cornflakes.
Mix the hash brown potatoes, mild Cheddar cheese, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and the onions (after browning) together.
Place in a casserole dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Mix the butter and cornflakes together and put on top.
Cover the dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Get out an 8-inch square baking pan. Combine 8 tablespoons (1 stick or 1/2 cup) butter, brown sugar and vanilla; beat together until thoroughly mixed.
Press the mixture evenly in the bottom of the pan; bake for 20 minutes.
Remove from the oven and cool in the pan on a rack.

title: english pea and shoe peg corn salad
directions: Stir together and boil for 1 minute the first 5 ingredients. Set aside until cold.
Mix all the above together.
Pour the liquid mixture over the vegetables and let it set overnight.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and place in cold water.
Place one potato at a time on a wooden spoon.
Slice down at 1/2-inch intervals across the potato.
Return potatoes to cold water.
Place in baking dish. Combine oil, basil and salt; brush on potatoes.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cheese.
Continue roasting for 10 minutes or until done.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute first 2 ingredients.
Add 2 cans mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz, broccoli and rice.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Add all ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: baked pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Good served with ham.
Serves 6.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Saute together the onion, celery and bell pepper. Combine all ingredients. Place in a 9 x 13 casserole.

title: fried rice
directions: In a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add eggs and cook, stirring, until set.
Remove from skillet; set aside.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon of oil to skillet and heat.
Add ham, green onions and bean sprouts.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Stir in eggs. Add rice and stir to mix the ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine.
Heat through; serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: lemon honey
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, 10 minutes or until thickened.
Let cool.
Yield:
2 1/2 cups.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the first 6 ingredients.
Stir in dry ingredients.
(Dough can be refrigerated or frozen if not using right away.)
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: mom's baked beans
directions: Cook and drain bacon.
Mix all ingredients together except for the brown sugar.
Use enough King's syrup just to thicken beans. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Combine soups and broth.
Stir in cheeses, turkey, spaghetti and mushrooms; mix well.
Pour into greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle top with paprika.

title: grandma's perfect pie crust(makes 2 generous crusts)
directions: Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Add 4 tablespoons ice water. Stir quickly and handle as little as possible forming into 2 balls. Roll out the size of your pie pan (about 12 inches).
When baking a crust without filling, prick it well with a fork before baking at 425° until golden (5 to 7 minutes).

title: marinated noodles and cabbage
directions: Break up noodles in noodle mix.
In a mixing bowl combine oil, vinegar, sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt, dash of pepper and seasoning packet from noodle mix; stir to dissolve seasonings.
Stir in broken noodles, cabbage, chicken, onion and sesame seed.
Cover; chill several hours.
Before serving, stir in almonds.
Garnish with green pepper rings.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, peanut butter, 1/2 cup melted margarine and 2 eggs until dough clings together.
Press 2/3 of the dough into an ungreased pan.
Set aside rest of the dough for the top.
Mix together in a large bowl the chocolate chips, Eagle Brand milk, 2 tablespoons margarine, salt, coconut, chopped nuts and vanilla.
Spread this mixture over dough in pan evenly.
Then sprinkle remaining dough over the filling and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars 2 inches square.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and roll into balls.
Brown in frying pan.
Do not cook all the way.
Drain on paper towel, then simmer last 4 ingredients until blended.
Place meatballs in crock-pot and pour sauce over them.
Cook on low until ready to serve.

title: never fail never harden frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients. Beat with electric mixer until fluffy.

title: rebaked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done; cut each one in half.
Using a fork, scrape the potato in a large bowl, leaving the peeling for re-use. Combine potatoes, butter, sour cream, cheese, topping, salt and pepper.
Put mixture back in peeling and bake at 350° until hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and pull into pieces.
Save broth.
Layer chicken in casserole.
Cover with sour cream and the soups.
Melt margarine in the broth.
Mix in dressing mix and spread on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chow mein butterscotch noodles
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Add other ingredients.
Use a tablespoon to drop on waxed paper.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sift together flour with other dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk, then yeast mixture.
Stir until all flour is moistened.
Knead on floured board 1 or 2 minutes.
Roll out or drop on a greased pan or tins.
Store in refrigerator until needed.
Pre-bake rolls 6 to 8 minutes or bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375° to 400°.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: saucy chocolate chip cake
directions: Add to first mixture, beat until thoroughly mixed and smooth. Pour into a greased 12
x 9 x 2 inch pan.
Sprinkle with topping.

title: fruity pizza
directions: Prepare cookie mix as directed and bake on pizza pan.
Let cool.
Prepare icing by mixing cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip.
Cool in refrigerator overnight if possible, then spread over crust.
Slice fruit over icing in a circle.
Mix lemon juice, orange juice, sugar, cornstarch and water and bring to boil; let stand and cool.
Pour over fruit.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except hamburger, well and save 1/4 cup to spoon over meat when in pan.
Add hamburger and mix well again. Place in pan and spoon 1/4 cup of mixture you saved over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken breasts until they are thin.
Lay out flat and sprinkle with parsley.
Top each breast with a slice of cheese, then a half slice of ham.
Roll up tightly.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine all liquids and add all at one time to dry mix.
Stir only until dry mixture is moistened but not smooth.
Fold in strawberry preserves.
Do not beat.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full of batter and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Yields 24 muffins.

title: strawberry satin pie
directions: Cover bottom of cooled baked crust with almonds.
Fill with chilled Creamy Satin Filling.
Slice 2 1/2 cups of the strawberries in half, reserving a few perfect whole berries for center.
Arrange berries atop filling.

title: linguine with pesto sauce
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
While pasta is cooking, blend all other ingredients in food processor or blender until smooth.
Toss with cooked pasta.
Serve warm or cold.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Use large enough pot so everything can be mixed in it.

title: apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add 1 Tbsp. of flour and one tsp. sugar. Heat, stir constantly, just long enough to thicken.
Cool.
Add 1/2 c. mayonnaise and remainder of ingredients.
Pour over fruit and store in refrigerator one day or night before serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl. Blend in bread. Pour mixture into a 13 x l9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: fried jelly pies
directions: Sprinkle counter top with flour.
Place 1 biscuit on counter. Sprinkle some flour on biscuit.
Roll out dough with a smooth glass or rolling pin to about a 4 to 5-inch circle.
Careful not to make holes in the dough.
Place a tablespoon jelly or jam in center.
Wet fingertip in a cup of water and wet edges of biscuit dough.
Fold dough over.
Take a fork and dip it in the flour, then crimp around edges of dough with fork.
If dough sticks to fork, dip fork in flour.
Fry in all vegetable shortening over medium-high heat.

title: green peppers stuffed
directions: Mix all ingredients after browning beef and onion.
Put in covered casserole and cook 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and cook about 15 minutes longer.
Canned spaghetti sauce can be added for extra flavor.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Prepare fruit with 1 cup sugar.
Melt butter in a 2 1/2 to 3-inch deep glass dish.
In a separate bowl, mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Mix well.
Pour over melted butter (do not stir).
Pour prepared fruit on top (do not stir).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles, drain.
Melt margarine; add onion, bell pepper, and mushrooms.
Saut until tender.
Combine tuna, tomato, lemon juice, salt, pepper, sauteed vegetables, and mayonnaise.
Add noodles and milk.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400 degrees about 20 minutes.
Serves 6-8.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef as directed on seasoning packet.
Simmer until liquid is almost absorbed.
Use rice as the base, layer in casserole dish.
Next add a layer of meat, beans and cheese.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbly and cheese melts. Serve with taco sauce and sour cream as desired.
Can be served with a salad and bread as a complete meal.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Whip egg; mix with salt and flour.
Coat pork and fry in oil until brown and crisp; drain well.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: In a bowl, combine peaches, oranges, pineapple and marshmallows.
In a small bowl beat cream cheese, yogurt and sugar until smooth.
Pour over fruit and toss to coat.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Yield 4 servings.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with sour cream (thin with 1 tablespoon milk if it doesn't spread easily).
Layer the onion and add layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken and collards
directions: In a large skillet, saute chicken in small amount of oil.
When lightly browned, remove and cut up into small pieces; set aside. In pan drippings, saute onion and cut up collards (raw) for a few minutes.
Add 1 to 2 cups water and other ingredients.
Place chicken back on top and cover.
Let it simmer until all is tender; add more water if needed.
Use as much collards as you desire.

title: eva's pumpkin custard
directions: Mix all together with mixer or in blender and pour into a baking dish.
Put water in baking pan and set bowl of custard in it.
Place in 300° oven for about an hour.
Insert knife in cooked custard.
If the custard is completely cooked, the knife will be clean when removed.

title: never fail pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, then vanilla and lemon flavor.
Sift dry ingredients and add to butter mixture. Add milk and mix for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: apple cake with walnuts
directions: Combine brown sugar, white sugar, eggs, cinnamon, baking soda, vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add the flour, chopped apples and walnuts.
Pour in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: *You can substitute apple pie spice or cinnamon.

title: low-fat cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and chunk potatoes; put in a pan and boil until done. Drain.
Heat soup and cheese until cheese is melted.
Put potatoes in bowl and pour cheese mixture over potatoes.

title: israeli vegetable salad
directions: Wash and dry vegetables.
Peel cucumbers, radishes and carrots.
Dice all the vegetables and mix in a bowl.
Add parsley, salt and pepper.
Toss.
Sprinkle with olive oil and toss again. Add lemon juice and serve.

title: savory skillet potatoes
directions: In a large bowl, toss potatoes, onion and savory herb with garlic soup mix until potatoes are well coated.
In 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat and cook potato mixture, covered 5 minutes.
Remove cover and cook, stirring frequently an additional 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Makes about 6 servings.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake the cake in 3 or 4 layers.
Before you make layers, mix the icing.
Chill icing before putting on cake.

title: fish casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Flake fish with fork.
Empty soup into bowl.
Soften cream cheese with sour cream and add slowly to soup. In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternating layers of crushed potato chips, fish and sour cream mixture.
Bake 20 minutes.
I usually double recipe.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix in shortening and eggs.
Add vanilla and chopped apples.
Batter will be stiff. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost when cool with Caramel Frosting following.

title: raspberry vinaigrette dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in jar, cover tightly, shake well. Chill at least 1 hour before using.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and water.
Blend in mayonnaise.
Add other ingredients, except onion rings.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with onion rings. Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 7-inch pan.
Add the ingredients in the order given in layers.
Do not mix.
Do not remove cake from pan the first day or it will crumble.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes. Serves 12.

title: cookie cups
directions: Freeze cookie dough for at least 1 hour or until firm. Preheat oven to 350°.
Turn a muffin tin upside down and spray outside of each cup with Pam.
Evenly cut dough into 1/2-inch slices and place one on top of each cup.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes. Dough will bake around the cup.
Cool 5 minutes and remove.
Fill cookie cup withy ice cream, yogurt, pudding and cut up fruits.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in a 375° oven for 45 minutes, or until tender. Cool slightly.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out each potato half, leaving a thin shell.
Put the pulp into a small mixer bowl.
Add cream cheese, chives, basil, salt and pepper; beat until smooth.

title: meat sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk coffee cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, soda and vanilla.
Put in 3 (9-inch) pie pans.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli just until tender; drain and cut into bite-size pieces.
Spray large Corning Ware dish with Pam.
Place cut up broccoli on bottom of dish.
Mix onion, soup, mayonnaise and beaten eggs together.
Blend well.
Pour 3/4 of mixture over broccoli; sprinkle cheese over top of that, then pour on remaining soup mixture and top with stuffing mix.
Add dots of butter on top of crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Save some cheese to sprinkle over top.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Put in bowl in order given.
Beat well and bake in muffin tins at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Yields 16 cupcakes.

title: macaroon kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter, softened cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk, almond extract and orange juice.
Beat well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in 3 cups flaked coconut.
Cover dough and chill about 1 hour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in remaining coconut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned on bottom.
Remove from oven and press a chocolate kiss into center of each cookie.
Allow to cool 1 minute.
Carefully remove cookies from sheet and cool until chocolate kisses are firm. Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: spicy vegetable cup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve in chilled glasses. Makes 3 servings.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together.
Cut in shortening until mixture has coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk all at once.
Stir until dough stays together.
Knead well for 1 minute on floured breadboard.
Pat out dough 3/4-inch thick.
Cut in rounds. Place on a cookie sheet with a bit of oleo on each.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: baked zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place vegetables and herbs in ovenproof casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover; bake for 45 minutes or microwave on light power for 12 minutes.
Remove cover last 15 minutes.
Add cheese.
Return to oven.
Serve with hot French bread as a vegetarian meal or as side dish.

title: curried tuna salad for 2
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain and chill.
Dice apple.
In a salad bowl, mix apple with lemon juice until coated. Add celery, raisins, onion and macaroni.
Add tuna, broken in chunks.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix Parmesan cheese and margarine together to form batter. Dip chicken into batter and roll in cracker crumbs.
Bake.

title: l. a. trump's chocolate tea cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy, 2 to 3 minutes.
Beat in melted chocolate. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix in flour.
Turn batter into parchment paper lined, 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cake will be puffy and toothpick inserted will be clean when tested.
Let cake cool in pan.
Invert cool cake onto plate.
Peel off paper lining.
Sift powdered sugar over top of cake.
Use paper doilies to create lacy sugar design.
Makes 16 squares.

title: mustard dip
directions: Mix all until well blended; serve chilled with raw vegetables, meats, cheese, hamburgers or pretzels.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla. Cream until smooth.
Measure flour, soda and salt in another bowl.
Sift together.
Add several spoons at a time and mix well until all dry ingredients have been mixed with creamed mixture. Mix last two ingredients until well mixed.
Chill 1 hour.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and 1 tablespoon sugar in a large bowl with a wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whip topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl. Add pudding mixes; beat with wire whisk for 1 minute (will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk until well mixed.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours. Garnish with more whipped topping, if desired.
Store in refrigerator.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tbsp. milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Gently stir in Cool Whip. Spread on bottom of crust. Pour 1 cup cold milk into bowl. Add pumpkin, pudding mixes and spices. Beat with wire whisk until well mixed (mixture will be thick). Spread over cream cheese layer. REFRIGERATE 4 hours or until set. Garnish with additional cool whip, if desired. Store leftover pie in refrigerator. Makes 8 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad(especially for summer)
directions: Mix all together and place in cup cake papers in muffin tin and freeze.

title: broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook vegetables per instructions.
Melt 1/2 margarine and all cheese.
Mix melted cheese with cooked vegetables.
Put mixture into casserole dish; sprinkle with crushed crackers.
Drizzle with the remaining melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, uncovered, until nicely browned.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix the flour, salt, black pepper and baking soda.
Cut shortening into flour mixture.
Add eggs and water.
Mix until mixture does not stick to hand or spoon.
Can add more flour, if needed.

title: oreo pie
directions: Mix 1 cup Oreo crumbs, pecans, sugar and margarine until crumbs are moistened.
Press into pie pan with spoon.
Pour chocolate syrup or caramel syrup on crust.
Put ice cream or yogurt in crust. Add remaining crumbs to top.
Press lightly.
Freeze for 4 hours.

title: kraut dog
directions: Heat your wieners in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from microwave; slice in half lengthwise.
Heat your skillet; add 1/2 cup butter.
Lay your sliced wieners face down and brown; also lay your bun face down and heat.
Heat your kraut also in skillet, enough to warm up.
Place wieners on bun.
Place kraut over wiener and add grated cheese over top of kraut and microwave for approximately 2 minutes to melt cheese.

title: tom's noodle stuff
directions: In a large skillet saute garlic and onion in olive oil until onions are transparent.
Prepare pasta.
Add ham, peas and white wine to taste and cook until mixture is very hot.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all, with fingertips, until well blended, if stiff, add water enough to moisten.
Place mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Top with ketchup if desired the last 15 minutes of cooking.)

title: quick pound cake
directions: Cream
butter and
sugar
until
fluffy
with
electric mixer. Add eggs, one at
a time, beating after each addition. Then
add flour gradually
and
flavor.
Mix	at
