speed. Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour
mixture into pan and cook in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: oven parmesan chicken
directions: Combine cheese, flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in egg mixture.
Coat with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Breast, leg and thighs may be used.

title: chicken divine
directions: Place 2 slices beef on each chicken breast.
Roll up, then wrap with bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Mix mushroom soup with sour cream.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread bean dip on serving plate.
Top with mashed avocados. Mix sour cream, Miracle Whip and taco seasoning until well blended.
Spread on top of avocados.
Top with remaining ingredients as desired.
Serve with taco chips.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Add hamburger.
Stir until browned.
Add other ingredients.
May chop tomatoes up or cook whole.
Dice potatoes in small pieces.
Cook on low until potatoes are soft. Great over rice.

title: chicken wings deluxe
directions: Mix soy sauce, brown sugar, mustard and garlic salt together; blend well.
Marinate chicken wings in sauce for 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Serve warm.

title: 10 minute fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and pudding.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly to a soft ball stage.
Stir in peanut butter. Remove from heat and beat in butter.
Beat until smooth and pour in buttered dish.
Cool and cut.

title: hamburger-green bean casserole
directions: Cook beef with onion, drain well. Spread on bottom of 9x13 baking pan. Layer beans, then soup, cheese. Top with tater tots. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until potatoes are done.

title: indian casserole
directions: Cook turkey, onion and peppers.
Add other seasons, tomatoes, hominy and cheese.
Pour into buttered casserole baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
You can use ground beef and cheese of your choice.

title: hot buffalo wings
directions: Cut wing tips off at joint and discard.
Cut each wing in half at joint.
On rack in broiler pan, arrange wings.
Broil until half done, then sprinkle hot pepper, cayenne pepper and salt and pepper.
Continue to broil until done.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine ingredients in heavy skillet or saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Stir with wire whisk or fork.
Add butter or margarine after you remove from stove.

title: sherry sponge cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add almonds; mix 8 yolks and then add sugar, sherry or another 1/2 cup orange juice along with 1/3 cup orange juice.
Add dry mixture; mix together.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Put in ungreased baking pan (spring-form). Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Cool for 45 minutes.
Garnish with powdered sugar, orange zest and orange slices.

title: martha's cabbage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot. Cook over low heat for 2 hours. It is best prepared a day ahead.

title: day old lemon crumb cake
directions: From Silverado, go west on Monticello Road, left onto Silverado Trail, south, turn right at Third Street and it's on your left.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift flour, pepper and salt.
Work in butter or margarine. Grate cheese; work until smooth.
Add to flour mixture until smooth.
Roll out and cut into 1/2 inch strips.
(Can also be cut with cookie press.)
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Blend 2 cups
sugar, eggs, cream cheese and 1 teaspoon lemon juice until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Put this mixture into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until middle stops jiggling when shook.
Cool for 10 minutes, then cream together sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar and lemon juice.
Put on top and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Heat milk to scald, but do not boil.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Slowly add this to milk.
Mix gently.
Pour into shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then turn oven down to 325° and cook 25 minutes longer.

title: great chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients well and place in a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan OR 2 (8-inch) round cake pans.
Bake Bundt/tube cake for about 45 minutes OR 8-inch round pans for 30 to 40 minutes in a preheated 350° oven. Test with toothpick for doneness. Cool; remove from pan.

title: easy chicken salad
directions: Mix together with desired amount of mayonnaise and refrigerate.

title: cooked squash
directions: Wash squash and slice, unpeeled.
Place in pan; slice onion. Add squash; cook in enough water to make tender.
Add 2/3 cup milk and 1 tbsp butter; let simmer just a few minutes.
Add salt, pepper and serve.

title: quick german meatballs(porcupines with gravy)
directions: Mix mushroom soup, water and stroganoff mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and form into 1 1/2-inch balls (makes 18 to 20 meatballs).
Drop raw meatballs into soup mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover and return to oven to brown tops.
Voila....meatballs with gravy.

title: rum coconut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° in 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes and remove.

title: heritage barbecue beef sandwich
directions: Bake roast, salted with cup of water, covered, at 350° approximately 4 hours or until tender.
Remove roast from broth. Remove all fat.
Shred beef.
Add barbecue sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Put on warm sesame seed hamburger buns.

title: "never fail" riz biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in a small amount of lukewarm water, then pour into buttermilk.
Sift together the dry ingredients and make dough by adding oil and buttermilk mixture.
Roll out dough and cut into biscuits.
Let raise for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in order listed in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Whip Miracle Whip, sugar and milk.
Spread Miracle Whip mixture over other layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix layers thoroughly before serving.

title: punch(makes 1 gallon)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add all ingredients into a gallon jug.
Fill to the top with water.

title: sugar cookies(large recipe)
directions: Mix together margarine and sugar, add eggs, then remaining ingredients.
Roll out and cut into shapes desired.
May be decorated if desired.
Bake at 375° for approximately 12 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together & stir well.
Store in air tight container.
To serve, mix 1/3 tsp fulls with hot water to taste.

title: fish brine
directions: Drop chunks of fish into brine.
Leave overnight.
Dry thoroughly with paper towels.
Put in smoker for 8 to 10 hours.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Start heating oven to 325°.
Place spareribs that have been cut into single ribs into shallow open pan.
Cover with foil. Roast 1/2 hour.
Pour off fat.
Roast 1/2 hour longer.

title: snicker krispies
directions: Melt margarine and Snickers (that have been chopped) until creamy.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Pat into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares and serve.
Great for snacks.

title: deviled almonds
directions: In heavy skillet, mix almonds, butter and salad oil.
Cook and stir over medium heat until golden.
Remove almonds and drain on paper towels.
Combine celery salt, salt, chili powder and cayenne; sprinkle over hot almonds.
Stir to coat.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: smoky salmon cheese spread
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 teaspoons liquid.
Remove bones and flake into small pieces.
Combine reserved liquid, cream cheese, salmon, onion and liquid smoke.
Blend thoroughly.
Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked beans
directions: Chop onion into fine pieces and mix ingredients.
Place in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until boiling.

title: tandoori chicken
directions: Remove skin from cut-up chicken; prick skin and salt well.
Mix all ingredients into the yogurt except food coloring, cumin seed and butter.
Put large gashes into the chicken and smear yogurt mixture well into the chicken.
Cover with remaining yogurt mixture and let stand 8 to 10 hours.
(Can be prepared night before.) Remove the chicken from the yogurt paste but don't throw away as you will baste the roasting chicken with it.
Heat oven to 400° and put chicken on a well-greased pan and cook for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and baste well first with yogurt mixture and then a paste of the cumin, red food coloring, butter and a little chili powder and lemon juice.
Return to oven.
Do this 3 to 4 times while baking.
This takes 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve on bed of yellow rice garnished with lemon wedges, sliced tomatoes and onion rings.

title: lentil and brown rice soup
directions: In large kettle, combine the broth, lentils, rice, tomatoes, reserved juice, carrots, onion, celery, garlic, basil, oregano, thyme and bay leaf; bring to boil and simmer the mixture, covered, stirring occasionally for 45 to 50 minutes or until rice and lentils are tender.
Discard bay leaf and season with vinegar, salt and pepper to taste.
Good with cut up smoked sausage added last 10 minutes.
Makes about 1 pound.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blueberry boy bait
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, baking powder, salt, butter, milk and eggs.
Blend at low speed until dry ingredients are moistened.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large pan.
Dredge chicken through.
Put rest of ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix well.
Place buttered chicken, skin side up, on rice mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: congo squares
directions: Cream together melted shortening and brown sugar.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° until done.
Cool in pan.

title: un-mexican haystacks
directions: In large mixing bowl or food processor, combine cream cheese, mayo, onions, green pepper, Worcestershire, garlic powder, Tabasco and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Stir in ham.
Place a tortilla on a large round plate.
Spread a thin layer of ham mixture over tortilla.
Repeat layers, ending with ham mixture on top of entire stack.
Sprinkle chopped nuts or chopped parsley on top layer of stack.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Cut into wedges/small cubes.
Serve with a decorative toothpick inserted in each piece.
(Place picks in a row.
Makes slicing with electric knife easiest.)

title: scalloped potatoes(microwave dish)
directions: Put milk in a 2-cup measure (glass).
Cook, covered with plastic wrap, for 2 to 3 minutes.
Put a layer of ham on bottom

title: toasted salted pecans
directions: Melt butter
in
saucepan.
Add
pecans and shake until each half is
well
buttered.
Place in 350° oven and bake for about 7 minutes
or
until	golden	brown.	Pour out on brown paper and sprinkle salt all over.

title: delightful no-cook fudge
directions: Whip together cream cheese, milk, vanilla and salt.
Add sugar and chocolate alternately.
Roll into balls and press a pecan half into each center to flatten.

title: sour cream drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar and eggs.
Stir in sour cream and vanilla.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Chop up chicken breasts.
Mix all ingredients except almonds. Bake in buttered casserole dish with almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini delight
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in a casserole dish.
Add zucchini, peppers and onions in layers.
Add tomato sauce. Sprinkle with bread crumbs, oil and Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and bake for approximately 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sour milk loaf cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and nutmeg.
Alternate with the sour milk.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle the brown sugar on top of batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: lucky casserole
directions: Combine meat, 3/4 cup cheese, crumbs, milk, onion and egg; mix lightly.
Shape meat mixture into 24 (1 1/2-inch) balls.
Combine potatoes, beans, remaining cheese, flour, salt and pepper.
Place in buttered 11 3/4 x 7 1/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Combine tomato sauce and sage; pour half of sauce over potato mixture. Bake in a preheated 350° oven, 20 minutes.
Place meat balls on potato mixture; top with remaining sauce.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 6 servings.
Try it; it's better than best!!

title: pan handler pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, meal, butter, coconut, vanilla and pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Combine ground meats, bread, onion, parsley, egg, salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and nutmeg in a large bowl.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll into ball.
Just before serving roll into pecans, sunflower, walnuts or whatever you choose.

title: italian beef stew
directions: Brown beef
in
oil
in
a
large saucepan.
Add onion, celery and garlic.
Saute a few minutes.
Add tomatoes (cut in pan), potatoes,
parsley
flakes, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: no-fat chocolate cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
Dump in 9-inch square pan, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Can be doubled for large pan.
Sweet.

title: microwave broccoli casserole
directions: Microwave broccoli 10 minutes or until tender.
Microwave 1 bag of Minute rice per instructions on box.
Combine broccoli, soup and rice.
Top with cheese and then bread crumbs.
Microwave 3 minutes on High.

title: fried corn
directions: In skillet, melt margarine; add corn and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer until desired doneness.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Boil with the garlic cloves until tender.
Drain.
Mash; add thyme, milk and butter or margarine.
Add salt and pepper to taste

title: mashed potato doughnuts
directions: Blend Crisco, egg and milk.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Combine the 2 mixtures with mashed potatoes and mix thoroughly.
Roll on lightly floured surface and cut with floured doughnut cutter.
Fry in Crisco at 365° for 3 to 5 minutes. Drain.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Beat peeled persimmons with mixer until fairly smooth, then add soda and stir.
Set to one side.
Beat egg with milk until fluffy.
Sift flour, salt and spices together.
Combine egg and flour mixtures and blend.
Add nuts, raisins and butter.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serve warm with whipping cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat and mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of celery soup, and Cheese Whiz in saucepan.
Meanwhile, cook both packages of chopped broccoli separately.
Mix cooked broccoli with soup and cheese mixture.
Add onion and Minute Rice.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees in 2-qt. casserole dish.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Add all ingredients into a large pot and cook over medium-low heat at least 2 hours. Add meatballs if you choose to. The longer you cook the sauce the better it tastes. Just make sure it does not burn on bottom. This sauce tastes as if it really were homemade.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Put butter in dish, in oven, so it will melt while oven is pre-heating.
Then add onion, rice, mushroom soup, evaporated milk, cheese and broccoli on top.
Put in oven like is.
Leave in for 30 minutes, take out, stir everything together, put aluminum foil over dish and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in water.
Add salt and pepper when done.
Tear apart when cool.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel and rinse potatoes.
Cut in slices 3/4 the way down the potato.
Put in baking dish, forming the potato slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with oleo.
Sprinkle on parsley or chives.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Remove, put cheese on top and bake for 10 minutes more.
Check with fork for doneness.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Grease 9 x 13 x 2 inch pan and pour 1 cup of sauce on bottom. Put 1/3 of uncooked lasagna over sauce.
In large bowl mix together cheeses and thawed spinach.
Alternate layers of cheese mix, sauce and noodles, ending with sauce.
Add parmesan cheese over all.
Pour 1 cup water around the edge.
Seal with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Let set 10 minutes before cutting.
Can be frozen without water.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Cook rainbow rotini as directed on package.
Chill with ice cubes and refrigerate for perhaps 1 hour.
Drain any water accumulated from ice cubes.
Cut crab meat into small pieces and add rest of ingredients, mixing well. (Add salad dressing to taste.)
Chill at least 1 hour before serving or even overnight; gives it a nice flavor.

title: creamy black pepper dressing or dip
directions: Whisk all ingredients until well combined.
Chill thoroughly before serving.
Makes 3 cups.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 475° until golden brown.

title: lima bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook hambone with water and tomatoes for 1 hour.
Add barley, veggies and beans.
Cook until tender (about 2 hours) on low heat.
(May need to add additional water.)

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Reserve 1 cup of dry cake mix.
In large bowl, combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
Press crust mixture evenly into bottom and 3/4 way up sides of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In same bowl, blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add 3 eggs and reserved cake mix.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
At low speed, slowly add milk and lemon juice.
Mix until smooth. Pour into crust.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes until center is firm.
Top with filling.

title: turkey buffet
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise and water.
Add to chicken mixture.
Turn into greased casserole.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: sunshine swizzle punch
directions: Empty the Crystal-Lite into a large punch bowl. Add the chilled club soda and limeade concentrate. Stir until completely dissolved. Spoon the sherbet into punch just before serving. Makes 18 servings, 1 cup each.

title: s'mores bars
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 pan. Cover with graham crackers.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Grease cookie sheet. Flour hands and pat down dough. Poke holes in dough with fork.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Place chips on top; let melt. Spread and cut when cool.

title: pizza salad
directions: Cook pasta and run under cold water.
Drain & mix with remaining ingredients.

title: winter vegetables with horseradish and dill
directions: Steam all vegetables separately for 8 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Melt butter; stir in horseradish, vinegar, dill, salt and pepper to taste.
In a large pan, toss vegetables with butter mixture.
Keep vegetables warm, covered, in a 200° oven.
Place in casserole to serve.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, peppers and salt in large container. Cover with ice cubes and let sit for 3 hours or more; drain well.
Cook together sugar, vinegar, celery seed, turmeric and cloves until boiling.
Pour over cucumber mix.
Bring all to a full boil at least 1 minute.
Jar and seal.

title: meringue tortes
directions: Beat together until frothy the egg whites and cream of tartar. Gradually beat in sugar, a little at a time.
Beat until very stiff and glossy.
Drop by small spoonfuls in a circle on brown paper on baking sheet.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Then turn oven off and leave in oven until oven has cooled.
Serve filled with ice cream and fresh berries.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise, salt, sugar and onion. Mixture may be refrigerated until ready to make sandwiches.
To assemble sandwiches, remove crust from bread.
Use cookie cutter to desired shape, preferably not much larger than a round slice of cucumber.

title: texas beef skillet
directions: In a skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is brown and onion tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, rice, green pepper, chili powder and garlic salt.
Add 1/2 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer covered for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese.
Cover and heat until cheese melts.
Sprinkle chips around edges.
Serves 6.

title: currant wine sauce
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan over low heat.
Add jelly and stir until it melts.
Add wine; stir to blend and cook just long enough to heat sauce.
(Cranberry juice may be substituted for wine.)

title: jam cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg together.
Add buttermilk. Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Add jam and mix well. Bake in a greased and floured cake pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches in a moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes or until done.
Or bake in two greased and floured 8-inch layer cake pans in a moderately hot oven of 375° for 25 minutes.
Spread with Seafoam Frosting.

title: crisp molasses cookies
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together.
Cream margarine and sugar. Beat molasses and egg into creamed mixture.
Gradually stir in flour mixture.
Batter will be very soft.
Using teaspoons, drop batter onto greased, floured cookie sheet.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool on wire rack and store in tightly covered tin box.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: flank steak marinade(miscellaneous)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Marinate flank steak 4-6 hours, turning occasionally.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Thoroughly mix together all ingredients.
Turn into a slightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Serve warm, cut into squares or wedges.

title: beef soup with dumplings
directions: Cook meat until tender and remove from the broth.
Add water until you have 2 quarts of broth.
Make dumplings by mixing beaten egg and milk into flour until about the consistency of pancake batter.
Drop from a teaspoon into the boiling broth to form small dumplings.
Cook for 3 or 4 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in a large dishpan.
Cream butter, peanut butter and sugar; add vanilla, eggs and syrup.
Mix in rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop by large spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets, about 6 to a sheet, and flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350°
for 12 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until sugar melts. Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour in milk.
Alternately add flavoring. Mix well. Place in tube pan in cold oven on 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: starberry punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine ice cream, strawberry soda and ginger ale.
Mix until a creamy liquid.

title: plain or chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, margarine and shortening.
Add milk. Sift flour, soda and cocoa together. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture. Add eggs, one at a time.
Put into greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crock-pot beef burgundy(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Dice bacon and fry in large skillet.
Remove bacon and put in crock-pot.
Dredge meat in flour and brown in bacon grease.
Add onions, carrots, tomato and the rest of the ingredients to the crock-pot along with meat.
Cook on low all day.

title: chewy sugar cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Roll out; use a cup or cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Frost, if desired, or sprinkle with sugar.

title: ic pilaf(savory rice)
directions: Remove the skin from the liver and chop up finely.
Fry the liver in 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Put to one side.
Put rice in hot water and let it cool.
Wash it in plenty of cold water.
Put 8 tablespoonfuls margarine in a pan and fry in it the pine nuts and onion until the onion is transparent.
Add the rice to this and fry for 10 minutes.
Add black pepper, cinnamon, mixed spices, 3 cups of water, currants, salt, sugar and finally chopped tomatoes or tomato sauce.
Cover with a lid.
Boil until the rice has absorbed the water and then turn down the heat and cook gently.
When the rice is done, add the fried liver.
Mix in the finely chopped dill. Fluff up the rice while serving.

title: all american cheese soup
directions: Cook but do not brown onion, celery, carrot and butter.
Mix flour with chicken broth, then add to vegetable mix.
Add half & half, seasonings and cheese.
Cook and stir till cheese is melted and soup is heated through.
Do not boil.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix all together (vegetables).
Mix in jar and shake well; sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Will be good in refrigerator up to 2 weeks.

title: mock tuna salad
directions: In food processor, place drained beans and grind until smooth. In bowl, mix the remaining ingredients with the bean paste. Tastes better if used the next day. Tastes just like tuna salad.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and cheese until blended.
Add Bisquick gradually. May have to adjust amount of Bisquick.
Roll into marble size balls and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Break up hash browns in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine onions, soup, sour cream, cheese and one stick of melted butter.
Spread over hash browns.
Mix corn flakes and 1/2 stick of melted butter. Spread over casserole and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: date nut brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Mix eggs, flour, salt and milk. Add chocolate, vanilla, nuts and dates.
Grease and flour a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix flour, soda, sugar and spices together.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add pumpkin, eggs, oil and water.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put the bread cubes in a large bowl along with raisins and cover with the scalded milk.
Meanwhile, melt the butter; beat the eggs, then add the ingredients to the bowl along with the sugar, vanilla and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour into a suitable baking dish, then put that in a large pan and add enough hot water to reach up the outer sides of the baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with Lemon Sauce.

title: rice and beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in enough water to cover.
Boil until tender and whole, adding salt meat and garlic when almost tender. Add cream, onion and seasonings.
Wash rice and add to beans. Cook over gentle heat until liquid is absorbed.
Stir gently with a fork and add a little water from time to time, until rice is cooked.
Serve hot with a meat dish.
N. B.
Beans may be made tender in a pressure cooker.

title: kugelis
directions: Beat milk and eggs.
Cook onions until soft.
Mix everything together.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.
Serve with sour cream.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Mix pineapple-cheese (set aside).
Mix sugar and flour and add. Spread in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Spread crackers over top.
(Crush in hand.)
Melt 4 ounces butter over top.

title: braunschweiger spread
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with Hi-Ho crackers.

title: breakfast egg and sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage and drain. Scramble eggs. Add grated cheese, milk and bread, broken up in pieces. Mix all together. Salt and pepper. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 450°.

title: garlic toast
directions: Mix thoroughly and spread on both sides of Rite diet bread, rye bread or split buns (hot dog or hamburger).
Arrange on cookie sheets and bake in 250° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Turn every 1/2 hour or so.
Cool on paper towels and store in airtight coffee cans.
Freeze or store on shelf.
Can be warmed up in slow oven for spaghetti or salads or cut smaller for croutons.

title: caramel-orange biscuit ring
directions: Combine butter, juice, orange peel and sugar in 8-inch round glass dish.
Microwave 3 to 3-1/2 minutes or until bubbly and slightly thickened, stirring once or twice.
Sprinkle with raisins.

title: cinna s'mores
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently. Remove from heat. Butter rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch. Pour Cinnamon Grahams cereal into large bowl. Pour marshmallow mixture over cereal. Stir until evenly coated. Press mixture into pan with buttered back of spoon. Cool at least 1 hour or until firm. Drizzle with melted Nestle morsels. Cool until chocolate is firm. Cut into 24 bars. Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: broccoli cheese pizza
directions: Defrost frozen bread dough in microwave 5 minutes.
Turn and defrost 2 more minutes.
Spread out onto greased 13-inch pizza pan.
Brush vegetable oil over dough.
Sprinkle with a dash of oregano, basil and garlic salt.
Spread broccoli and mushrooms evenly over crust and top with grated cheeses.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut and serve.

title: christmas salad
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges.
Simmer fruit with water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a mold on 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate to congeal.
Yields 20 servings.

title: chocolate cream dessert
directions: In a bowl, cut butter into the cake mix until crumbly. Add the egg. Mix well. Press into a greased 13 x 9 x 3-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until set. Cool thoroughly on wire rack.

title: easy spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, stirring until it crumbles; drain well. Stir in tomato sauce, water, onion flakes, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and pepper.
Bring to a boil over medium heat. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add spaghetti sauce and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions and drain.
Spoon meat sauce over cooked spaghetti and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef in bacon fat.
Drain off fat if desired. Brown onions; add beef and onions to beans.
Add tomato soup, water, catsup, chili powder and pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: barbecue sauce(for pig pickin')
directions: Mix and keep warm over low heat.
This is Ross' secret recipe.

title: angel cookies
directions: Now make it with regular or pudding cake mix.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all together.
Grease and flour pan lightly.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick microwave fudge
directions: Microwave chips and Eagle brand 2 1/2 minutes, stir. Microwave 2 1/2 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts and stir.
Put into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: 20 minute dinner rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased muffin tins. Bake for 20 minutes at 450°.
Makes 6 rolls.

title: cranberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; chill until slightly thickened. Break up cranberry sauce with fork.
Stir into jello with celery and nuts.
Fold in sour cream.
Chill until firm.

title: dump cake
directions: Spoon pie filling evenly in bottom of oblong pan.
Spread pineapple over cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Pour melted margarine evenly over ingredients. Sprinkle on coconut and nuts.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: fruity pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Pinch seams together.
Bake at 375° until light brown.

title: fruit pie glaze
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch over medium heat until mixture thickens and becomes clear.
Continue cooking for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from
heat and add Jell-O. Stir until dissolved.
Add fresh fruit and pour into crust. Refrigerate.

title: microwave pizza casserole
directions: In a 2 quart casserole dish, microwave beef until done.
Drain thoroughly, add remaining ingredients except cheese, mix well. Cook 17 minutes on High, stir twice during cooking.
Sprinkle cheese over casserole and cook 1 minute or until melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix everything together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or more.

title: thick 'n rich hot fudge sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate and butter;
stir
in
remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, about
minutes or until mixture is slightly thickened.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage leaves.
Let stand 5 minutes and drain.
Season meat; add onion, rice and egg.
Roll a portion of filling into each cabbage leaf.
Fasten with toothpick.
Place in large oven pan.
Pour over tomato soup and juice.
Bake in oven, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: shrimp dunk
directions: Mix all together and let set overnight.
Serve in sourdough bread.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Season with salt, paprika and pepper.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook for 2 minutes.
Add onions, green peppers and garlic.
Cook 6 minutes.
Drain juice from tomatoes (reserve tomatoes).
Add enough chicken broth to juice from tomatoes to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Add liquid to chicken, bring to a boil. Add rice and tomatoes.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand until all
liquid is absorbed (approximately 5 or 6 minutes).
Add grated cheese to each serving.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine, add flour and eggs.
Beat well and add vanilla, nutmeg and buttermilk.
Mix and pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool completely before serving.

title: nuga cake
directions: Flour raisins to keep from sticking together.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, milk, egg yolks, raisins and vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Makes 3 or 4 layers.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Chop candy bars and combine all ingredients.
Finish filling freezer container with whole milk.
Freeze.

title: trail mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together; makes about 4 cups.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add egg, well beaten and the butter. Beat well and bake in buttered muffin tin for 25 to 30 minutes in hot oven (450°).

title: linda's egg rolls
directions: Brown and drain meat. Season with spices. Chop potatoes, carrots and onions into small pieces, especially potatoes and carrots. Add to meat. Cook on low while chopping canned items. Chop to medium size. Mix all ingredients together. Season to taste with spices. Simmer on low for about 30 to 40 minutes until potatoes are soft. Drain in colander. Cup wraps in 1/2 diagonally. Separate. Place 1 large tablespoon mixture in center edge of wrap. Fold sides over and roll up. Seal with a drop of water along the seam. Place on wax paper. Do not let the wrapped rolls touch each other. For best results, chill or freeze before deep-frying.

title: american ice cream
directions: Mix flour and sugar thoroughly.
Add milk slowly and cook over hot water 8 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add to egg, cook 2 minutes and cool.
Add cream, salt and vanilla.
Pour into freezer can and freeze using 8 parts ice to 1 part salt.
Makes about 1 1/4 quarts.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: super bowl football
directions: Brown ground beef and green pepper; drain.
Stir in soup mix, oregano, red pepper and tomato sauce.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Divide pastry.
Roll into 10 x 12-inch rectangle.
Lay one rectangle on ungreased baking sheet.
Spoon filling onto rectangle, leaving 2-inch border and mounding slightly in center.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry ice cream
directions: Blend cherry pie filling, Eagle Brand milk, sugar, vanilla and enough milk to fill freezer container to fill line.
Freeze.

title: beef goulash
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add meat, but do not brown it.
Add all remaining ingredients using enough water so meat is halfway covered.
Cover skillet and simmer about 2 hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Stir together the salad dressing, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat; season with salt and pepper.
Drain and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 of onion and cheese over meat.
Cover with 6 tortillas.
Add beans and remainder of tortillas.
Mix soup and tomatoes; pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining onion and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef in half of the oleo. Add remaining butter, mushrooms, onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Saute until onions are tender. Add Worcestershire sauce. Stir in flour, then chili sauce. Just before serving, blend in sour cream. Serve hot over noodles.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening.
Beat egg well.
Add vinegar and water to egg.
Add to flour mixture.
Roll out between sheets of waxed paper.
Makes four 9-inch crusts.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Mix sugar and salad oil.
Combine all ingredients; let set 24 hours.
Be sure liquid covers kraut even if you have to add water. When ready to use, put in colander and let drain.
Save liquid for the leftovers.
Keeps well for several days.

title: orange surprise shakes
directions: Mix and blend milk, orange juice and sweetener tablets.
Chill in refrigerator, then shake until mixed.
Pour into tall glasses and garnish with mint leaves.
(Low-fat.)
Makes 2 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix gelatin, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Beat together the egg yolks (save egg whites), lime juice and water.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat just until it boils. Remove from heat.
Stir in grated peel.
Add food coloring sparingly.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.

title: old timey flour bread
directions: Mix shortening and water with half of flour, stirring with fork until flour is well mixed.
Add remaining flour as needed to make a dough that can be handled with hands.
Grease griddle (pan) with bacon grease.
Heat (not too hot). Pat dough out medium thin. Cook on slow heat.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread rice evenly in pan.
Place chicken pieces on rice and sprinkle with salt, pepper, oregano and parsley. Spread chicken soup and water on top. Sprinkle with paprika.
Wrap foil over top of pan and seal tightly.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Do not look at chicken while baking.

title: dilly bread
directions: Sprinkle dry yeast over warm water.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm.
Combine in mixing bowl with sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, egg and yeast mixture.
Add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well.
Cover and let rise until doubled.

title: ham delight rolls
directions: Night before serving, in baking pan, split rolls in half. Put layer of ham; top with cheese. Melt margarine, poppy seeds, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and onion together and pour over rolls. Next day, bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken cutlets with mushrooms and sherry
directions: Dip chicken in bread crumbs and brown in frying pan with oil and margarine. Drain and arrange in ovenproof dish. Cut up mushrooms and saute in drippings from chicken. Add some sherry for flavor.
Pour over chicken.
Combine sour cream, mushroom soup and some sherry in frying pan. Stir until bubbly and pour over mushrooms.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 45 minutes, covered, until bubbling.
Serve with rice.
This dish can be prepared in the morning and baked at dinnertime.

title: chili enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a skillet cook ground beef until brown. Drain off oil.
Add beans and heat thoroughly.
Spoon about 1/3 cup of mixture on center of each large tortilla.
Add some cheese. Roll up.
Put in baking dish.
Spoon chili on top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 20 minutes.

title: orange-date bars(for diabetics)
directions: Combine dates, sugar, oil and juice in a saucepan.
Cook for 5 minutes to soften dates.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients. Spread into an oiled 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.
Makes 36 bars.

title: bloomin' onion
directions: Select a well-rounded onion.
Peel outer skin off.

Leave root intact; cut off any hanging roots, Using small, sharp knife, divide onion into four sections by making 2 cuts crosswise, beginning at the top and cutting toward root, stopping about 1/2-inch away.
Cut each section twice.
Place onion in bowl of enough boiling hot water to cover it and leave for 5 minutes.
The sections, or "petals" will begin to open.
Remove onion from hot water and immerse into ice water, which will further the opening.
Drain well by turning upside down on paper towel.
Put flour into paper bag; add onion and shake gently to coat with flour.
Roll floured onion in beaten egg to cover.
Put cracker crumbs or coating in paper bag; add onion and shake gently to coat.
Refrigerate 1 hour before deep frying in oil to golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes.
Cooked onion can be kept for a time in warm oven.

title: miss shirley's apricot cookies
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese, sour cream and lemon juice. Add flour; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
To finish, pinch walnut size ball of dough.
Roll in powdered sugar until very thin.
Put 1/2 teaspoon purchased apricot filling on edge.
Shape into crescent shapes.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: barbecued beef
directions: In a large Dutch oven pan, place roast and seasonings.
Fill with enough water to cover.
Bring to a boil and cook until meat is tender and will pull apart easily.
Shred the meat and serve with banana pepper rings on Italian roll.
(More water can be added if meat seems dry.)

title: amish kraut salad
directions: Combine drained and rinsed kraut with onion, pepper and celery.
Combine sugar, hot water, oil and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight; drain and serve.

title: potato stacks
directions: Melt morsels; stir in potato sticks and peanuts.
Spoon out onto wax paper; let cool.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Mix all above ingredients well.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese and cream with margarine.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Roll in small balls.
Put on cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: hungry jack jackpots
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add barbecue sauce, onions and brown sugar; set aside.
Separate biscuits in each of 10 ungreased muffin cups.
Press dough up sides to edge of cup and spoon meat mixture into jackpots. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together. Sift together the next 4 ingredients. Add to other mixture. Stir well. Add oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts. I also add coconut, raisins and dates or anything my family likes. Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes. This makes a big batch of cookies.

title: black cherry fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and save.
Mix first 3 ingredients and walnuts in a large bowl.
Make dressing in a separate bowl. Add bananas right before serving.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Shred lettuce in bottom of bowl.
Add celery, onion, green pepper and peas in layers.
Spread salad dressing over peas. Sprinkle sugar over dressing.
Sprinkle grated cheese on sugar. Sprinkle top with bacon bits.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Toss just before serving.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate (375°) oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: spinach quiche(makes 2 quiches)
directions: Precook pie shells according to directions and set aside. Thaw spinach and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in butter until soft. Place in food processor the spinach, onion, garlic, cream cheese, Ricotta, Feta and 1/2 cup Mozzarella.
Pulse 2 to 3 times.
Add eggs and dill; pulse to mix.
Do not overblend. Divide into 2 pie shells; top with 1/2 cup Mozzarella each.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until puffed and golden.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck, then drain.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.

title: haystacks
directions: Mix peanut butter, syrup, and sugar and bring to a boil. Pour over corn flakes.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper or cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: christmas rock cookies
directions: Dredge fruit with flour; mix all together.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar and salt gradually.
Beat until stiff.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Place in oven.
Turn oven off.
Leave until oven has cooled or overnight.

title: favorite icebox cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar and mix well.
Add egg, coconut, milk and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Divide dough into 2 parts, shape into long rolls about 1 inch in diameter.

title: peach delight cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed, except substitute peach syrup for water.
If there is not enough syrup, finish with water.
Bake as directed in three cake pans.
Let cool completely.
Mix Cool Whip, yogurt and peaches that have been cut into small pieces.
Spread between layers and on top.
Refrigerate.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Delicious with strawberries, peaches or fresh apples.

title: crawfish and sausage jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage in heavy pot.
Remove sausage and drain on paper.
Add celery, onion, bell pepper and garlic to pot and saute until tender.
Remove from pot.
Add oil.
When oil is hot, add rice and stir until light brown.
Add crawfish and cook for 3 minutes.
Add sausage, vegetables, green onions, water, Worcestershire, Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is done.
Serves 6.

title: walking taco dip
directions: On a large flat dish, spread beans, then guacamole, then layer the rest of the ingredients as given.
Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, powdered sugar, margarine and graham cracker crumbs with your hands in large bowl.
Form into small balls.
Put on waxed paper on cookie sheets.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: shish kabobs(sticks can be purchased at supermarket)
directions: Melba toast, crackers, English muffins, bread:
Cut in fingers, rounds, squares, triangles, any small shape.

title: zucchini squash  bread
directions: Sift together in large bowl: flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Blend in cooking oil, eggs, sugar, grated zucchini and vanilla. Mix well and pour into two (2) greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Add enough water to clam liquid to make 2 cups; reserve.
Fry pork in large kettle over medium heat until crisp and golden. Remove with slotted spoon and set aside.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons fat and saute onion until tender, about 5 minutes. Add potatoes, clam liquid, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.
Add clams, milk and butter.
Reheat, but do not boil.
Sprinkle with pork and parsley.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: coconut peach upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in 10-inch round microwave baking dish.
Add coconut and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Arrange peach slices on top of mixture.
Mix cake batter as directed, spread over peaches. Microwave on Low for 7 minutes.
Turn.
Cook on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let stand 1 minute. Turn onto serving plate.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix beef with cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into 4 thick patties.
Heat butter in skillet; quickly brown meat patties on both sides and remove from pan.
Add flour to drippings in skillet and blend.
Add wine and consomme slowly; stir until thickened and smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; return patties to sauce.
Simmer, covered, until done, 5 minutes or more to taste.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: snicker bars
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch pan and freeze.

title: sicilian potato bake
directions: For a main dish add ham slices.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all and mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cook meat or seafood by sauteing quickly (hot or mild sausage needs to be crumbled).
Briefly saute vegetables.
Following package directions on egg roll wrappers.
Fill and roll.
Deep fry.
Serve hot with soy sauce (Kikkoman),
Chinese mustard or sweet and sour sauce.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 400°.

title: homemade hot fudge sauce
directions: In a small saucepan melt butter over medium heat.
Add Hershey's syrup and Eagle Brand milk.
Stir over medium heat constantly while mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Be very careful mixture does not stick or burn.
Cook approximately 5 to 10 minutes.
Let cool on back of stove.
Serve warm over pound cake and/or ice cream.
Will stay fresh in fridge 1 week.
Can be frozen.
May be reheated in microwave.

title: cherry balls
directions: Drain cherries from juice (save juice).
Set aside.
Mix oleo, powdered sugar, flour, salt and vanilla together.
Add enough water to get the mixture the texture of a pie crust.
Make little balls and flatten in hand.
Roll 1/2 of a cherry inside dough. Bake at 350° until light brown (approx 10-12 minutes). After they cool, roll into icing mixture (recipe follows) completely covering the balls.
Place on wax paper to dry.
Makes 5 dozen, depending on size.

title: potato pizza
directions: Mix the milk, Cheddar cheese soup and the hamburger that has been browned.
Add the onion and potatoes.
Mix together.
Top with the tomato sauce.
Add the sugar.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and oregano.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove, top with cheese and bake 15 minutes more.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Simmer in a large pot for a minimum of 90 minutes before serving.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together; shape into loaf in loaf pan and bake about 2 hours in moderate oven (375°).
Baste with sauce.

title: melba sauce
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over low heat, heat raspberries and red currant jelly until raspberries thaw and mixture is hot.
In cup, mix cornstarch with 1 tablespoon water until smooth; stir into berries.
Over medium heat, cook berries, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens slightly; boil 1 minute.
Press through strainer.
Serve warm over ice cream or poached peaches or pears.

title: baked chicken drummettes
directions: Mix ingredients, pour over drummettes and soak overnight. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: stove top rice pudding
directions: Mix rice and milk; cook on low for 1 hour, stirring often. Remove from heat.
Add sugar, vanilla and nutmeg, if desired. Serve warm or cold.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix dry goods in medium bowl.
Soften shortening in the baking pan in the oven at 300°.
Pour shortening and milk into the bowl of dry goods.
Stir.
Either knead, roll and cut out biscuits or spoon them out into pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden on top.
(Clabber Girl recipe.)

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cook eggs in simmering water 20 minutes.
Cool under running water.
Peel, then cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks; set whites aside.
Put still warm yolks into a plastic food storage bag with all remaining ingredients, squeezing bag to mix well. Refrigerate filling and egg whites separately.
Fill egg whites just before serving.
Cut off one corner of the bag and press filling into cooled egg whites.
Sprinkle finished eggs with paprika if desired.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In baked pie shell, slice berries in half. Save some whole ones to place on top.
Put sugar, cornstarch, salt, lemon juice and food coloring in pan on low heat.
Pour boiling water into pan.
Stir to keep from lumping. Cook until semi-thick and clear. Pour over all your berries. Chill.
May be topped with whipped cream.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Combine the flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts.
Beat the eggs and add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Fold in zucchini and pineapple that has been drained.
Bake at 350°.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry meat until crisp; drain all but 1/4 inch of grease from pan.
Add desired chopped onion and fry.
Mix flour, sugar, vinegar and water.
Add to meat and onion in pan; cook until thick, then add potatoes.
